        <!-- ENERGY SECTOR -->
        <div class="sector-content-panel block" id="energy">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Installed Capacity & Mix</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Total capacity: <strong>452 GW</strong> (Jan 2025) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Coal: <strong>211 GW (47%)</strong>, operating at ~55% capacity factor <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Renewables: <strong>203 GW (45%)</strong> ‚Äî solar 92 GW, wind 48 GW, hydro 47 GW <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Gas: <strong>25 GW (6%)</strong>, nuclear: <strong>8 GW (2%)</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Biomass & other: <strong>5 GW (1%)</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Renewable Energy Growth</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Target: <strong>500 GW RE by 2030</strong> (65% of total capacity) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>2024-25 additions: <strong>27 GW solar, 5 GW wind</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>RE generation share: <strong>21%</strong> (up from 17% in 2020) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Grid integration capacity: <strong>~160 GW RE (35% total)</strong> without major storage <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>RE curtailment: <strong>~3-5%</strong> in high-wind states during low-demand hours <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Demand & Distribution</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Annual consumption: <strong>1,625 TWh</strong> (2024-25) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Peak demand: <strong>243 GW</strong> (summer 2025), growing 6-8%/year <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>AT&C losses: <strong>14.8%</strong> (improved from 22% in 2015) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>DISCOM financial health: Cumulative losses <strong>~‚Çπ1.1L crore</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li>Per capita consumption: <strong>1,255 kWh/year</strong> (global avg: 3,300) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Grid Infrastructure</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Transmission lines: <strong>4.6L circuit-km</strong> (765 kV, 400 kV, 220 kV) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Green Energy Corridors: <strong>13 GW transmission capacity</strong> added for RE zones <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Smart meters: <strong>11 crore installed</strong> (target: 25 crore by 2027) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Distribution system: <strong>~70% electromechanical meters</strong> still in use <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Renewable integration: <strong>&lt;5 GW battery storage</strong> operational <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Fossil Fuel Dependencies</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Coal imports: <strong>280 MT/year</strong> (20% of consumption) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>Fossil fuel subsidies: <strong>‚Çπ1.2L crore/year</strong> (oil, gas, coal) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Coal plant average age: <strong>~12 years</strong> (global avg: 15 years) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>Stranded asset risk: <strong>~60 GW coal capacity</strong> underutilized (&lt;50% PLF) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>LNG regasification: <strong>48 MTPA capacity,</strong> ~70% utilization <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Decentralized & Emerging</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Rooftop solar: <strong>~12 GW installed</strong> (target: 40 GW by 2026) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>PM Surya Ghar scheme: <strong>1 crore households</strong> target, 300W/household <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Green hydrogen: <strong>0.1 MT production</strong> (target: 5 MT/year by 2030) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>EV charging infra: <strong>~15,000 public stations</strong> (target: 100K by 2030) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>Agricultural pump solarization: <strong>~5L solar pumps</strong> installed <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Milestones</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Grid Flexibility & Storage</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>10 GW battery storage</strong> operational (2x current capacity) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>5 GW pumped hydro</strong> projects commissioned <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>RE curtailment &lt;1%</strong> in high-wind states (down from 5%) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50% transmission capacity</strong> for RE-rich zones added (Green Corridors Phase III) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Real-time grid balancing</strong> enabled by 20 crore smart meters <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Distributed Energy Systems</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>25 GW rooftop solar</strong> deployed (100% YoY growth) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50L households</strong> under PM Surya Ghar (50% of 1 crore target) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>10 microgrids</strong> operational in off-grid regions <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>2M solar pumps</strong> replacing diesel (agricultural decentralization) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Virtual power plants:</strong> 1 GW aggregated capacity from DERs <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Demand-Side Management</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>5 GW peak demand shifted</strong> via time-of-use tariffs <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>10M smart appliances</strong> enrolled in demand response programs <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50 industrial clusters</strong> adopt thermal energy storage for load shifting <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Agricultural load shifting:</strong> Solar pumps + battery ‚Üí daytime operation <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EV charging infrastructure:</strong> 50K public stations with V2G capability <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Fossil Subsidy Reform</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ50K crore/year redirected</strong> from fossil subsidies to RE (40% reduction) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Carbon pricing pilot:</strong> 5 states levy ‚Çπ500/tonne CO‚ÇÇ on coal power <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Stranded asset plan:</strong> Early retirement for 20 GW &lt;50% PLF coal plants <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Just transition fund:</strong> ‚Çπ10K crore for coal region reskilling <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No new coal PPAs</strong> signed in 10 states with &gt;150 GW total capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">DISCOM Financial Health</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>AT&C losses &lt;12%</strong> (down from 14.8%) via smart meter rollout <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50% DISCOMs</strong> achieve ACS ‚â• ARR (cost recovery) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Open access adoption:</strong> 5 GW capacity under green power trading <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Direct benefit transfer:</strong> 20% of subsidies delivered via DBT (not tariff cross-subsidy) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tariff rationalization:</strong> 10 states adopt cost-reflective pricing <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Data & Market Infrastructure</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Green hydrogen auctions:</strong> 1 MT/year capacity contracted <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Energy storage obligation:</strong> 5% of RE capacity mandated by 10 states <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grid code updates:</strong> 50% RE penetration capability certified <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Carbon accounting:</strong> GHG inventory published quarterly by CEA <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Open data platform:</strong> Real-time RE generation and grid load public <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ö° Energy Flow Cascade: From Generation to Useful Service</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Visualizing where energy gets lost in the power system ‚Äî from fuel input to transmission to distribution to actual useful electricity</p>
                <div id="energy-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: Economic Survey 2025-26, CEA Grid Data. Interactive diagram shows energy flow from fuel ‚Üí generation ‚Üí transmission ‚Üí distribution ‚Üí consumption ‚Üí useful service.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Must-run coal PPAs:</strong> 25-year contracts lock DISCOMs into buying coal power regardless of RE availability <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Stranded asset politics:</strong> Early coal retirement politically toxic‚Äîworkers, state revenues dependent</li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOM-politician nexus:</strong> Free/cheap power promises drive losses, no accountability for financial health <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Open access gaming:</strong> Large consumers exit grid, leaving DISCOMs with fixed costs + low revenue base</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>RE = unreliable myth:</strong> 21% RE generation share with &lt;5% curtailment disproves narrative, but persists <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Coal as baseload religion:</strong> Flexible gas/hydro ignored; 55% coal PLF shows excess capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Subsidy = welfare:</strong> Fossil subsidies framed as pro-poor; RE subsidy = rich subsidy</li>
                            <li><strong>Battery cost fear:</strong> "Storage too expensive"‚Äîunaware costs dropped 90% since 2010 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>SLDC skill gap:</strong> State Load Dispatch Centers lack RE forecasting expertise <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grid operator inertia:</strong> Trained for thermal scheduling; RE integration requires new protocols</li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOM engineering deficit:</strong> Staff sized for meter reading, not smart grid management</li>
                            <li><strong>Installation labor shortage:</strong> Solar/battery installers trained &lt;10% of requirement <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>RE curtailment blackbox:</strong> No public data on when/why wind/solar curtailed‚Äîgrid operator opacity <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOM loss attribution:</strong> AT&C losses aggregated‚Äîcan't isolate theft vs. technical loss vs. billing error</li>
                            <li><strong>Subsidy tracking gap:</strong> ‚Çπ1.2L crore fossil subsidy spread across 8 ministries‚Äîno consolidated dashboard <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grid stability mythology:</strong> No real-time RE impact data published‚Äî"reliability" claims unfalsifiable</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>PPA sanctity paradox:</strong> Coal contracts sacred, but RE PPAs renegotiated when tariffs fall <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Cross-subsidy trap:</strong> Agricultural free power funded by industry tariffs‚ÄîDISCOMs can't charge cost-reflective prices <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Storage policy vacuum:</strong> No regulatory framework for battery/storage as asset class‚Äîunclear revenue model</li>
                            <li><strong>RE obligation toothless:</strong> RPO/RESO targets missed; no meaningful penalties for non-compliance <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>DISCOM creditworthiness:</strong> ‚Çπ1.1L crore losses = banks won't lend for RE procurement <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Coal plant sunk costs:</strong> "Too big to fail"‚Äîstate govts pressure DISCOMs to offtake to avoid NPA write-offs</li>
                            <li><strong>Rooftop solar upfront barrier:</strong> ‚Çπ3L for 3kW system‚Äîno consumer finance products at scale <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green bond gap:</strong> Only 2% of power sector debt green-labeled‚Äîno climate risk pricing <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Power exchange illiquidity:</strong> &lt;5% generation traded on exchange‚Äîno price discovery for flexibility <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Balancing market absence:</strong> No real-time market for grid balancing‚ÄîSLDCs manually dispatch</li>
                            <li><strong>Demand response desert:</strong> No aggregators, no time-of-use pricing for most consumers‚Äîzero demand flexibility <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ancillary services void:</strong> Coal plants paid capacity charges even at 55% PLF‚Äîno penalty for inflexibility</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Transformation Vision</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-4"><strong>Energy systems where renewables are dispatchable, grids are intelligent, demand is flexible, and fossil subsidies redirect to clean alternatives.</strong></p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What Changes</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>From curtailment to storage:</strong> RE surplus stored (batteries/hydro), not wasted‚Äîdispatchable on demand <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From supply-follows-demand to demand-follows-supply:</strong> Time-of-use pricing shifts load to solar hours <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From coal baseload to flexible grid:</strong> Coal plants cycle down during solar peak, battery fills evening gap <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From subsidy inertia to subsidy swap:</strong> ‚Çπ1.2L crore fossil subsidies redirected to RE/storage/efficiency <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From centralized monopoly to distributed choice:</strong> Rooftop solar + battery = grid independence option</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Breakthrough Moments</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>First state hits 50% RE integration</strong> without blackouts‚Äîproof of concept demolishes "reliability" myth</li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOMs auction demand response</strong> instead of peaker plants‚Äîconsumers paid to shift load <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Battery costs &lt; coal peaker capex</strong>‚Äîstorage becomes default for peak capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Carbon price pilot shows revenue neutrality</strong>‚Äî‚Çπ500/tonne on coal funds RE jobs, not budget burden</li>
                            <li><strong>Rooftop solar + EV pairing</strong>‚Äîcommuters charge at work (solar peak), discharge at home (evening peak)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. MARKERS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Quantitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>RE curtailment rate</strong> by state (target: &lt;1% by Year 3) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Battery storage capacity</strong> vs. 10 GW target (GW installed quarterly) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Coal plant load factor</strong> trajectory‚Äîdeclining PLF = RE displacing coal <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Smart meter rollout</strong> vs. 25 crore target (% coverage) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Rooftop solar CAGR</strong>‚Äîtrack 12 GW ‚Üí 25 GW pathway <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Fossil subsidy allocation</strong>‚Äîyear-over-year change from ‚Çπ1.2L crore baseline <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOM AT&C losses</strong>‚Äîstate-wise tracking toward &lt;12% <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green hydrogen production</strong> vs. 5 MT/year target <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Qualitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Grid operator rhetoric shift:</strong> SLDCs discussing "RE integration" not "RE problem"</li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOM procurement strategy:</strong> RFPs for storage+RE bundled vs. standalone thermal</li>
                            <li><strong>Policy innovation diffusion:</strong> States replicating energy storage obligations, carbon pricing pilots</li>
                            <li><strong>Coal sector narrative:</strong> Transition plans published, not denied‚Äîjust transition funds created <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Consumer awareness:</strong> Time-of-use tariff adoption rates, demand response enrollment</li>
                            <li><strong>Media framing:</strong> "Subsidy reform" not "subsidy removal"‚Äîclimate investment narrative</li>
                            <li><strong>Financial sector behavior:</strong> Banks offering lower rates for green bonds, RE project finance</li>
                            <li><strong>Regulatory agility:</strong> SERCs updating tariff orders for DER integration, V2G frameworks</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7. STRATEGIES -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-600">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Intervention Pathways</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Grid Flexibility Infrastructure</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 3-5% RE curtailment; grid cannot absorb variable generation <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Deploy 10 GW battery storage via viability gap funding (VGF) auctions <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>Commission 5 GW pumped hydro storage (shovel-ready projects prioritized)</li>
                            <li>Mandate energy storage obligation (ESO): 5% of RE capacity bundled with storage</li>
                            <li>Green Energy Corridor Phase III: 50% transmission capacity expansion for RE zones</li>
                            <li>Real-time balancing market: SLDCs procure ancillary services from battery aggregators</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Demand-Side Flexibility via Smart Grids</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Zero demand response; peak load grows 6-8%/year <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Accelerate smart meter rollout to 20 crore (80% coverage) via RDSS funds <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Time-of-use tariffs for all metered consumers‚Äîhigher rates 6-10 PM, lower 10 AM-2 PM</li>
                            <li>Demand response aggregator licensing: 10 companies enroll 10M smart appliances</li>
                            <li>Agricultural load shifting: Solar pump + battery ‚Üí daytime irrigation (free solar hours)</li>
                            <li>EV charging infrastructure with V2G: 50K public stations as grid batteries <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Fossil Subsidy Swap</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> ‚Çπ1.2L crore/year subsidizing fossil fuels <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Phase out ‚Çπ50K crore/year coal subsidies ‚Üí RE development fund (40% reduction over 3 years)</li>
                            <li>Carbon pricing pilot in 5 states: ‚Çπ500/tonne CO‚ÇÇ on coal generation‚Äîrevenue to just transition fund <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>Agricultural power subsidy reform: Direct cash transfer replacing free power (pilot in 3 states)</li>
                            <li>Cross-subsidy rationalization: Industrial tariffs reduced 20%, agricultural tariffs cost-reflective + DBT top-up</li>
                            <li>Green hydrogen subsidy: ‚Çπ10K crore over 3 years to achieve $2/kg production cost <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Distributed Energy Resources (DER) Acceleration</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Rooftop solar stalled at 12 GW; target 40 GW by 2026 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>PM Surya Ghar financing: ‚Çπ30K subsidy/household + 0% EMI loans via PSU banks <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Net metering 2.0: Gross metering with banking for 1 year‚Äîresolve DISCOM-consumer disputes</li>
                            <li>Group net metering for apartments: Single 100kW array serves 50 flats (regulatory framework)</li>
                            <li>Virtual power plants (VPP): Aggregate 1 GW rooftop solar + home batteries for grid services</li>
                            <li>Microgrid licensing: 10 off-grid clusters (50-200 households) solar+battery+diesel hybrid</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Stranded Asset Transition Plan</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 60 GW coal capacity at &lt;50% PLF; ‚Çπ3L crore sunk cost <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Early retirement scheme: 20 GW coal plants &lt;50% PLF decommissioned; ‚Çπ10K crore transition fund <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>Reskilling program: 50K coal workers trained for solar/wind O&M, battery installation</li>
                            <li>PPA renegotiation framework: Allow DISCOMs to exit must-run clauses for &lt;40% PLF plants</li>
                            <li>Coal-to-solar site conversion: Repurpose retired coal plant land/transmission for RE parks</li>
                            <li>State revenue replacement: Coal cess revenue diverted to RE manufacturing zones in coal states</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. DISCOM Financial Turnaround</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> ‚Çπ1.1L crore DISCOM losses; no capital for RE procurement <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Smart meter AT&C reduction: 20 crore meters ‚Üí 12% AT&C losses (‚Çπ20K crore annual savings) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Direct benefit transfer pilot: Subsidies to consumers' bank accounts, not tariff‚Äîeliminates leakage</li>
                            <li>Cost-reflective tariff roadmap: 10 states commit to ACS ‚â• ARR within 3 years (SERC-monitored)</li>
                            <li>Green open access expansion: 5 GW corporate RE procurement‚ÄîDISCOMs earn wheeling fees</li>
                            <li>Performance-linked DISCOM incentives: ‚Çπ5K crore fund for states achieving AT&C &lt;12% + ACS‚â•ARR</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Data Infrastructure for Grid Intelligence</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> No real-time RE impact data; curtailment opaque <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Open grid data platform: Real-time RE generation, curtailment, load by state‚Äîpublic API access</li>
                            <li>RE forecasting systems: SLDC-level 24-hr solar/wind forecasts (90% accuracy target) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li>Fossil subsidy tracker: Consolidated dashboard across ministries‚Äîquarterly public reporting</li>
                            <li>DISCOM performance portal: AT&C, ACS/ARR, tariff gaps by state‚Äîcitizen-accessible</li>
                            <li>Carbon accounting integration: CEA publishes quarterly GHG inventory by fuel type <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Externalities</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Fossil subsidies:</strong> ‚Çπ1.2L crore/year propping up coal/oil/gas‚Äîopportunity cost for RE <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOM losses:</strong> ‚Çπ1.1L crore cumulative debt‚Äîtaxpayer bailouts every 5-7 years <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Health externality:</strong> Coal pollution = ‚Çπ1.4L crore/year health costs (World Bank estimate) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Stranded asset risk:</strong> ‚Çπ3L crore in underutilized coal plants (&lt;50% PLF) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>RE curtailment waste:</strong> 3-5% of RE generation lost = ‚Çπ5K crore/year foregone investment value</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Benefits</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>AT&C reduction:</strong> 14.8% ‚Üí 12% saves ‚Çπ20K crore/year (smart meters) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>RE cost advantage:</strong> Solar ‚Çπ2.5/kWh vs. coal ‚Çπ4.5/kWh‚Äî‚Çπ40K crore/year savings at 500 GW <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Avoided coal imports:</strong> 280 MT/year at $120/tonne = $33B forex savings over 10 years <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Job creation:</strong> RE+storage deployment = 1M jobs by 2030 (vs. 300K coal jobs) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grid reliability gains:</strong> Reduced outages = 2% GDP boost (World Bank productivity metric)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ31 trillion</strong> ($358B) green energy infrastructure by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>$150 billion</strong> battery storage market by 2030 (10-20 GW annual additions) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>$20 billion</strong> green hydrogen electrolyzer capacity by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ2 trillion</strong> rooftop solar market (40 GW target) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>$80 billion</strong> EV charging + V2G infrastructure by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. INVESTMENTS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üíµ Investments: Capital Allocation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capex (Capital Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Battery storage deployment:</strong> ‚Çπ80K crore (10 GW @ ‚Çπ8 crore/MW) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Pumped hydro storage:</strong> ‚Çπ35K crore (5 GW @ ‚Çπ7 crore/MW) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green Energy Corridors III:</strong> ‚Çπ25K crore (transmission for RE zones) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Smart meter rollout:</strong> ‚Çπ40K crore (20 crore meters @ ‚Çπ2,000/meter) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Rooftop solar acceleration:</strong> ‚Çπ50K crore (PM Surya Ghar + net metering infra) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EV charging + V2G:</strong> ‚Çπ15K crore (50K stations @ ‚Çπ30L/station) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grid data platform:</strong> ‚Çπ500 crore (real-time monitoring, API infrastructure)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Capex:</strong> ‚Çπ2,45,500 crore (~$30B) over 3 years</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Opex (Operational Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Just transition fund:</strong> ‚Çπ10K crore/year (coal worker reskilling, state revenue replacement) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>SLDC capacity building:</strong> ‚Çπ500 crore/year (RE forecasting training, grid operators) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Demand response incentives:</strong> ‚Çπ2K crore/year (consumer payments for load shifting) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>DISCOM performance fund:</strong> ‚Çπ5K crore/year (AT&C reduction, cost recovery incentives) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Subsidy redirection:</strong> ‚Çπ50K crore/year (fossil ‚Üí RE, offset by subsidy phase-out) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Data platform maintenance:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore/year (open grid data, DISCOM portal)</li>
                            <li><strong>Green hydrogen subsidies:</strong> ‚Çπ10K crore/year (production cost gap funding) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Total Opex:</strong> ‚Çπ77,700 crore/year (~$9.5B/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">Note: 65% of capex (‚Çπ1.6L crore) recoverable via storage revenue, wheeling charges, and AT&C savings. Opex largely offset by ‚Çπ50K crore/year fossil subsidy redirection. Net fiscal cost &lt;‚Çπ30K crore/year (0.1% GDP).</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Urgency-Ranked Priorities</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Partner-driven interventions addressing hidden dynamics, not adding capacity. Ranked by leverage potential.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Storage Obligation Mandate</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">5% of RE capacity bundled with storage‚Äîeliminate curtailment bottleneck. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Grid Flexibility Deficit</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> 500 GW RE target by 2030 unachievable without storage; current 3-5% curtailment = ‚Çπ5K crore/year waste <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Fossil Subsidy Swap Framework</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Redirect ‚Çπ50K crore/year from coal subsidies to RE fund‚Äîrevenue-neutral climate action. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Fossil Lock-in</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> ‚Çπ1.2L crore/year fossil subsidies = 10x RE budget; every year delay locks in coal capacity for 25+ years <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Demand Response Infrastructure</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Time-of-use tariffs + 10M smart appliances‚Äî5 GW peak load shifted. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Demand Inflexibility</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Cheapest flexibility resource; smart meters already being deployed‚Äîjust needs tariff + software <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Open Grid Data Platform</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Real-time RE generation, curtailment, load public‚Äîend opacity. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Data Blackbox</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Low-cost intervention (‚Çπ500 crore); enables evidence-based policy, third-party innovation, accountability <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Rooftop Solar Financing</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">PM Surya Ghar + 0% EMI loans‚Äî25 GW distributed capacity. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Upfront Cost Barrier</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> High impact but slower scale-up; requires consumer behavior change + DISCOM net metering cooperation <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-energy-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Energy">[1]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Stranded Asset Transition Plan</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Early retirement for 20 GW &lt;50% PLF coal plants‚Äîjust transition fund. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Coal Sunk Cost Fallacy</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Politically sensitive; requires state-level negotiation + worker reskilling programs (3-5 year timeline) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="transport">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Transport System Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Vehicle Fleet & Motorization</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>330M+ total vehicles</strong> (2024, 12% annual growth) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>240M two-wheelers</strong> (73% of fleet); 40M cars (12%) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Vehicle density: <strong>253 per 1000 population</strong> vs global average 182 <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Only <strong>1.5M EVs</strong> sold in 2023 (8% penetration in new 2Ws; 2% in cars) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Avg vehicle age: <strong>11 years</strong> (scrappage policy not enforced) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Public Transit Deficit</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>25% modal share</strong> for public transit in metros vs 60% in global cities <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>945 km metro</strong> operational (14 cities); 1,100 km under construction <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li>Only <strong>63 of 4,000+ ULBs</strong> have city bus services (15 buses per lakh population vs 60 global std) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100% bus subsidy dependency:</strong> No city recovers operational costs from fares <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li>Transit ridership declining: <strong>-8% annually</strong> as vehicle ownership rises <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Active Transport Crisis</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>48% trips are cycling/walking</strong> distance (&lt;5km) but infrastructure missing <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li>Only <strong>200 km cycling lanes</strong> exist across all Indian cities <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>60% pedestrian trips</strong> have no footpath; forced to walk on roads <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>1.5 lakh road deaths/year</strong>; 60% pedestrians/cyclists (10x global rate) <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li>Street design: <strong>&lt;5% road space</strong> for pedestrians vs 40-60% for motorized traffic <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Freight & Logistics</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>65% freight by road</strong> vs 30% rail (inverse of global best practice) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>4.8M heavy trucks</strong>; 90% are BS-IV or older (high emissions) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Last-mile delivery: <strong>70% by diesel 3-wheelers</strong> in cities (no EV penetration) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Freight electrification: <strong>&lt;1% trucks,</strong> 5% 3-wheelers <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Logistics cost: <strong>14% GDP</strong> vs 8% global average (inefficiency penalty) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Emissions & Health Burden</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>20-35% urban PM2.5</strong> from vehicles (60-80% at local hotspots) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-dust-mitigation-2017" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB Dust Mitigation 2017">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>290 MtCO2e/year</strong> from transport (12% national emissions; fastest growing sector) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>NO2 exposure: <strong>Delhi 40 ¬µg/m¬≥</strong> vs WHO standard 10 ¬µg/m¬≥ (vehicles primary source) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                            <li>Health costs: <strong>‚Çπ80,000 Cr/year</strong> from vehicular pollution deaths, DALYs <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-dust-mitigation-2017" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB Dust Mitigation 2017">[178]</a></li>
                            <li>Congestion penalty: <strong>‚Çπ1.5 lakh Cr/year</strong> in lost productivity (Delhi, Mumbai, Bengaluru) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">EV Transition Progress</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>1.5M EVs sold</strong> in 2023 (8% 2W penetration, 2% cars, 5% 3W) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>12,000 public chargers</strong> (0.004 per EV vs 0.1 global standard) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ25,938 Cr FAME-II subsidy</strong> (2019-2024); ‚Çπ10,900 Cr utilized <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Battery costs: <strong>$130/kWh</strong> (down from $1000 in 2010); target $100/kWh for parity <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li>Satellite validation: <strong>200 EVs = 1.1% NO2 reduction</strong> (California study transferable) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Milestones</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Public Transit Transformation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>40% modal share</strong> in 10 target metros (vs 25% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>500 km new metro</strong> operational + 50,000 new city buses added <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100 cities</strong> with operational bus services (vs 63 baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>30 buses per lakh</strong> population target in 10 pilot cities <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Fare box recovery: 60%</strong> operational costs (from 0% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Active Transport Safety</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>2,000 km protected cycling lanes</strong> in 20 cities (10x baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>80% footpath coverage</strong> for all arterial roads in target cities <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50% reduction</strong> in pedestrian/cyclist road deaths (vs 1.5L baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Vision Zero adoption</strong> in 10 metros (zero road death commitment) <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>20% road space reallocation</strong> from cars to pedestrians/cycles <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">EV Penetration & Charging</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>30% EV penetration</strong> in new 2W sales; 15% cars; 40% 3W <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100,000 public chargers</strong> deployed (8x baseline); 0.03 per EV ratio <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>5,000 electric buses</strong> in 50 cities (fleet electrification model) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>2.88 ¬µg/m¬≥ PM2.5 reduction</strong> from EV transition (satellite-verified) <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ100/kWh battery cost</strong> achieved (parity threshold) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Freight Modal Shift</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>45% freight by rail</strong> (from 30% baseline); 55% by road <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>10,000 electric trucks</strong> operational (long-haul pilot corridors) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50% last-mile electric</strong> in 20 cities (3W cargo conversion) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Logistics cost: 11% GDP</strong> (from 14% baseline) via efficiency gains <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Dedicated freight corridors:</strong> 3,000 km operational (decongesting highways) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Emissions & Air Quality</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>15% vehicular PM2.5 reduction</strong> in 10 target cities (satellite-validated) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50 MtCO2e avoided</strong> annually from transit/EV shift (17% baseline reduction) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NO2 exposure: 25 ¬µg/m¬≥</strong> in Delhi (from 40 baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ30,000 Cr health costs avoided</strong> from reduced vehicular pollution <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Congestion penalty: ‚Çπ1 lakh Cr</strong> (from ‚Çπ1.5L baseline) via demand management <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Policy & Demand Management</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Congestion pricing</strong> operational in 3 metros (London/Singapore model) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Parking reform:</strong> ‚Çπ200/hr peak rates in 10 CBDs (demand curb) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Vehicle scrappage: 5M old vehicles</strong> retired via incentive scheme <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Shared mobility: 20% trips</strong> via app-based ride-sharing in metros <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>TOD policy:</strong> 50% new housing within 1km of transit in 10 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üöó Transport System Flow: Vehicle Types to Emissions</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Visualizing how 330M+ vehicles across categories generate PM2.5, NO2, and CO2 emissions, creating health burden and climate impacts</p>
                <div id="transport-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: NITI Aayog ZEV Roadmap 2022, CPCB Dust Mitigation 2017, MoHUA NMT Policy 2022. Interactive diagram shows vehicle fleet ‚Üí fuel combustion ‚Üí pollution types ‚Üí health/climate outcomes.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Car ownership aspiration:</strong> Vehicle = status symbol‚Äîpolicy battles car lobby vs public good <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Transit as last resort:</strong> "Only poor use buses"‚Äîmiddle class demands parking, not transit investment</li>
                            <li><strong>Fragmented ownership:</strong> Transport (MoRTH), Urban (MoHUA), Rail (MoR)‚Äîno single system owner</li>
                            <li><strong>Auto industry capture:</strong> FAME subsidies benefit manufacturers; user behavior unchanged (12% growth continues)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"Cars = development" myth:</strong> GDP growth measured by vehicle sales, not mobility efficiency <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>"Transit is charity" belief:</strong> Buses seen as welfare, not revenue service‚Äîsubsidy dependency normalized</li>
                            <li><strong>"Pedestrians don't matter":</strong> 1.5L deaths/year (60% walkers/cyclists) accepted as inevitable <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>"Tech will solve it":</strong> EV hype distracts from transit/land use‚Äî330M EVs still = congestion</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Transit planning gap:</strong> Only 63 of 4,000+ ULBs have bus services‚Äîno in-house capacity to operate <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Street design incompetence:</strong> Engineers trained for vehicle speed, not safety‚Äîno pedestrian design curriculum</li>
                            <li><strong>Enforcement collapse:</strong> Avg 1 traffic cop per 2,000 vehicles‚Äîhelmet/seatbelt laws unenforced <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Data blindness:</strong> No city tracks transit ridership, modal share, or trip patterns‚Äîplanning by hunch</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Modal share unknown:</strong> 25% public transit estimate unverified‚Äîno city has origin-destination surveys <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Health-transport disconnect:</strong> ‚Çπ80K Cr health costs from vehicles not attributed in road project appraisals <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Congestion costs invisible:</strong> ‚Çπ1.5L Cr/year loss not tracked‚Äîno economic case for demand management <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EV impact unmonitored:</strong> TROPOMI satellite can verify NO2 reduction but not integrated into policy <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Parking mandates kill transit:</strong> 2 parking spaces/flat mandatory‚Äîguarantees car dependency <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Road widening reflex:</strong> Every congestion problem "solved" by adding lanes‚Äîinduced demand ignored</li>
                            <li><strong>No vehicle restraint:</strong> Parking free/cheap; no congestion pricing; vehicle growth unchecked (12% annually) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Scrappage policy toothless:</strong> 11-year avg vehicle age; no mandatory retirement‚Äîpollution continues <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>0% fare box recovery:</strong> Buses 100% subsidy-dependent‚Äîno city breaks even; expansion impossible <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Metro cost explosion:</strong> ‚Çπ300 Cr/km vs ‚Çπ150 Cr global‚Äîoverbuild + land acquisition delays</li>
                            <li><strong>FAME subsidy capture:</strong> ‚Çπ26K Cr allocated but benefits manufacturers, not users‚Äîsales still 8% penetration <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Road budgets car-centric:</strong> 95% funds for highways/flyovers; &lt;5% for cycling/walking infrastructure <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Charging infrastructure chicken-egg:</strong> 12K chargers for 1.5M EVs‚Äîrange anxiety blocks adoption <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Battery cost barrier:</strong> $130/kWh still 30% above parity ($100)‚ÄîEVs premium-priced <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Fossil fuel price distortion:</strong> Diesel subsidized for trucks‚Äîrail freight uncompetitive (30% vs 65% road) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Used vehicle dumping:</strong> No scrappage enforcement‚Äîold high-emission vehicles resold, not retired <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Transformation Vision</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-4"><strong>Mobility where public transit is the first choice, active transport is safe, freight moves by rail, and vehicle emissions approach zero through electrification and shared mobility.</strong></p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What Changes</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>From car-aspiration to transit-pride:</strong> Middle class chooses metro over car‚Äîbus ridership rising, not falling <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From subsidy-dependent to fare-sustainable:</strong> Buses recover 60% opex from fares‚Äîexpansion self-funded <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From parking mandates to parking caps:</strong> CBDs charge ‚Çπ200/hr; new housing built transit-adjacent, not car-dependent <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From road widening to road diets:</strong> 20% space reallocated to pedestrians/cycles‚Äîspeed reduced, safety improved <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From FAME manufacturer subsidy to user incentive:</strong> EV buyers get charger installation + toll-free lanes‚Äîadoption accelerates <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Breakthrough Moments</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Congestion pricing adopted:</strong> Delhi/Mumbai/Bengaluru charge zone entry‚Äî‚Çπ50K Cr revenue funds metro expansion <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Vision Zero commitment:</strong> 10 metros pledge zero road deaths‚Äîstreet design standards rewritten for safety <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Freight modal shift policy:</strong> Carbon tax on road freight; rail subsidy‚Äî45% freight by rail achieved <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Satellite-verified EV impact:</strong> TROPOMI shows 1.1% NO2 drop per 200 EVs‚Äîvalidates health benefit case <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>TOD becomes default:</strong> 50% new housing within 1km transit‚Äîcar dependency designed out <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. MARKERS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Quantitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Public transit modal share:</strong> 40% in 10 target metros (from 25% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bus ridership trend:</strong> +5% annual growth (vs -8% baseline decline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EV penetration:</strong> 30% new 2W sales, 15% cars, 40% 3W (vs 8%, 2%, 5% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Cycling lane km:</strong> 2,000 km in 20 cities (from 200 km baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Road deaths reduction:</strong> 50% drop in pedestrian/cyclist deaths (from 1.5L/year) <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NO2 satellite tracking:</strong> 1.1% reduction per 200 EVs verified via TROPOMI <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Freight rail share:</strong> 45% by rail (from 30% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Congestion penalty:</strong> ‚Çπ1 lakh Cr (from ‚Çπ1.5L baseline)‚Äî33% reduction <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Qualitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Transit narrative shift:</strong> Media covers "metro overcrowding" not "bus subsidy burden"‚Äîdemand signal</li>
                            <li><strong>Parking policy reversal:</strong> 3 metros repeal parking mandates; adopt ‚Çπ200/hr CBD pricing <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Vision Zero adoption:</strong> 10 cities officially commit to zero road death target <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Street design curriculum:</strong> Engineering colleges add pedestrian safety modules (capacity shift)</li>
                            <li><strong>Community mobilization:</strong> Resident groups demand protected cycling lanes in planning approvals</li>
                            <li><strong>Corporate fleet electrification:</strong> E-commerce cos pledge 100% EV last-mile delivery by 2026 <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Scrappage enforcement:</strong> States start impounding 15-year+ vehicles; resale market collapses <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>TOD planning default:</strong> New master plans mandate 50% housing within 1km transit <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7. STRATEGIES -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-600">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Intervention Pathways</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Transit-First Policy Package</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 25% modal share; 0% fare recovery; -8% ridership decline <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Deploy 50,000 new buses in 100 cities (30 buses/lakh target); electrify 100% new fleet</li>
                            <li>Bus priority corridors: dedicated lanes on 500 km arterials‚Äîreduce travel time by 30%</li>
                            <li>Fare reform pilots in 10 cities: dynamic pricing, monthly passes‚Äîtarget 60% recovery</li>
                            <li>Integrated ticketing: single card for bus/metro/bike-share‚Äîreduce friction, boost ridership</li>
                            <li>Service frequency standards: 5-min peak, 15-min off-peak on trunk routes‚Äîreliability drives adoption</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Vision Zero Street Redesign</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 1.5L deaths/year; 60% pedestrians/cyclists; no footpaths <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>2,000 km protected cycling lanes: physical separation, not paint‚ÄîAmsterdam standard</li>
                            <li>Complete streets pilots: 20 cities reallocate 20% road space to pedestrians/cycles</li>
                            <li>Speed limit reform: 40 km/h default in cities; automated enforcement via cameras</li>
                            <li>Footpath mandate: 80% coverage on all arterials; tactile paving for blind; street lighting</li>
                            <li>Street design manuals updated: pedestrian safety as primary criterion, not vehicle speed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. EV Acceleration via Infrastructure</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 8% 2W penetration; 12K chargers for 1.5M EVs; range anxiety <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>100,000 public chargers deployed: 1 per 3 km in cities; highway corridors every 50 km</li>
                            <li>Mandate EV charging in new buildings: 20% parking spots; building codes updated</li>
                            <li>Battery-swap pilots for 2W/3W: 500 swap stations in 10 cities‚Äî5-min refuel</li>
                            <li>FAME subsidy shift: from manufacturer to user‚Äîcharger installation + toll-free EV lanes</li>
                            <li>Corporate fleet mandates: 30% EV procurement for govt/PSUs by 2027‚Äîdemand certainty</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Demand Management Pricing</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Parking free; no congestion pricing; 12% vehicle growth unchecked <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Congestion pricing pilots: Delhi/Mumbai/Bengaluru charge ‚Çπ100-500 zone entry‚ÄîLondon model</li>
                            <li>Parking reform: ‚Çπ200/hr peak CBD rates; abolish parking mandates in TOD zones</li>
                            <li>Vehicle ownership tax: annual ‚Çπ10K levy on 2nd+ car‚Äîrevenue funds transit expansion</li>
                            <li>Fuel tax escalator: ‚Çπ5/liter annual increase earmarked for EV charging infrastructure</li>
                            <li>Congestion revenue earmarking: 100% to transit/cycling‚Äîself-funding virtuous cycle</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Freight Modal Shift Policy</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 65% freight by road; 30% by rail; 14% GDP logistics cost <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Carbon tax on road freight: ‚Çπ50/ton-km (50% exemption for EVs)‚Äîrail becomes competitive</li>
                            <li>Dedicated freight corridors: 3,000 km operational; decongest highways, reduce truck crashes</li>
                            <li>Last-mile electric 3W mandate: 50% of city deliveries via EV cargo vehicles by 2027</li>
                            <li>Truck platooning pilots: automated convoys reduce fuel 15% + emissions on 5 corridors</li>
                            <li>Rail freight subsidy: ‚Çπ5K Cr to upgrade terminals, electrify routes‚Äîtarget 45% modal share</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. TOD & Land Use Integration</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> New housing car-dependent; parking mandates guarantee sprawl <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>TOD policy mandate: 50% new housing within 1km of metro/bus corridor in 10 metros</li>
                            <li>Parking mandate repeal: 3 cities abolish minimums; adopt maximums (0.5 spaces/unit in TOD)</li>
                            <li>Transit land value capture: 50% property tax increase in TOD zones funds metro expansion</li>
                            <li>Mixed-use zoning reform: residential + commercial within 15-min walk‚Äîreduce trip length</li>
                            <li>Street connectivity standards: max 100m block length; no gated communities in TOD zones</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Satellite-Verified EV Impact Tracking</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> EV health benefit unmonitored; TROPOMI satellite not integrated <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>TROPOMI NO2 monitoring: monthly tracking in 20 cities‚Äîvalidate 1.1% drop per 200 EVs</li>
                            <li>Integrate satellite data into NCAP: link EV penetration to air quality targets‚Äîco-benefit visible</li>
                            <li>Public dashboard: show NO2 heatmaps overlaid with EV adoption zones‚Äîcommunity accountability</li>
                            <li>Health cost attribution: calculate ‚Çπ30K Cr avoided deaths from EV shift‚Äîjustify subsidy</li>
                            <li>Policy feedback loop: if NO2 reduction lags EV sales, trigger charging infrastructure audit</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Externalities</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Health burden: ‚Çπ80,000 Cr/year</strong> from vehicular PM2.5, NO2 (0.3% GDP) <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Congestion penalty: ‚Çπ1.5 lakh Cr/year</strong> lost productivity (Delhi, Mumbai, Bengaluru) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Road crashes: ‚Çπ3 lakh Cr/year</strong> economic loss (1.5L deaths + injuries) <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Logistics inefficiency: 6% GDP excess</strong> (14% vs 8% global)‚Äî‚Çπ13.2L Cr/year <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Transit subsidy drain:</strong> 100% opex dependency; no city breaks even‚Äîexpansion impossible <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Benefits</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ30,000 Cr health costs avoided</strong> from 15% vehicular PM2.5 reduction <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ50,000 Cr congestion savings</strong> via 33% penalty reduction (demand management) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ1 lakh Cr crash cost reduction</strong> from 50% pedestrian/cyclist death drop <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ6.6 lakh Cr logistics savings</strong> from 3% efficiency gain (11% GDP target) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50 MtCO2e avoided/year:</strong> Climate co-benefit (17% transport emissions baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ50,000 Cr congestion revenue:</strong> Self-funding transit expansion from pricing <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Transit expansion ROI: 3x</strong> via congestion savings + health benefits + fare revenue <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EV subsidy reallocation:</strong> ‚Çπ26K Cr FAME to charging infra‚Äîunlocks 30% penetration <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Cycling infrastructure: 10:1 ROI</strong> via health + congestion + emissions benefits <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Freight rail electrification:</strong> ‚Çπ5K Cr investment ‚Üí ‚Çπ20K Cr logistics cost savings <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>TOD land value capture:</strong> 50% tax increase funds metro‚Äîself-financing expansion model <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. INVESTMENTS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üíµ Investments: Capital Allocation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capex (Capital Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>50,000 electric buses:</strong> ‚Çπ1,00,000 crore (‚Çπ2 crore per bus; 100 cities) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>500 km metro expansion:</strong> ‚Çπ1,50,000 crore (‚Çπ300 crore/km; 10 metros)</li>
                            <li><strong>100,000 public EV chargers:</strong> ‚Çπ10,000 crore (‚Çπ10 lakh/charger; installation + grid upgrade) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>2,000 km protected cycling lanes:</strong> ‚Çπ4,000 crore (‚Çπ2 crore/km; 20 cities) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Footpath construction:</strong> ‚Çπ6,000 crore (80% arterial coverage; 20 cities)</li>
                            <li><strong>3,000 km freight corridors:</strong> ‚Çπ30,000 crore (rail electrification + terminals) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Total Capex:</strong> ‚Çπ3,00,000 crore (~$37B) over 3 years</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Opex (Operational Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Bus operations subsidy:</strong> ‚Çπ20,000 crore/year (40% opex; 60% fare recovery target) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Metro opex subsidy:</strong> ‚Çπ10,000 crore/year (new 500 km; 60% fare recovery)</li>
                            <li><strong>Charger maintenance:</strong> ‚Çπ1,000 crore/year (100K chargers @ ‚Çπ10 lakh/charger annually)</li>
                            <li><strong>Cycling/walking infrastructure maintenance:</strong> ‚Çπ500 crore/year (2,000 km + footpaths)</li>
                            <li><strong>TROPOMI satellite monitoring:</strong> ‚Çπ100 crore/year (data licensing, analysis, dashboards) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Vision Zero program management:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore/year (training, enforcement, monitoring)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Opex:</strong> ‚Çπ31,800 crore/year (~$4B/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">Note: Capex offset by ‚Çπ50K Cr congestion pricing revenue + TOD land value capture. Opex declining as fare recovery improves (60% target). Net economic benefit ‚Çπ7.8L Cr/year from health + congestion + crash savings.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Urgency-Ranked Priorities</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Partner-driven interventions addressing hidden dynamics, not adding transit capacity alone. Ranked by systemic leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Congestion Pricing + Parking Reform</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Implement zone pricing in 3 metros; ‚Çπ200/hr CBD parking‚Äîgenerate ‚Çπ50K Cr revenue for transit. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Unchecked Vehicle Growth (12% annually)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> Every year of delay = 40M+ new vehicles; congestion ‚Çπ1.5L Cr loss‚Äîpricing creates modal shift + self-funds expansion <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a> <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Vision Zero Street Redesign</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Reallocate 20% road space to pedestrians/cycles; 40 km/h speed limits; protected lanes. <strong>Addresses:</strong> 1.5L Deaths/Year (60% Walkers/Cyclists)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> 400+ daily preventable deaths‚Äîstreet design kills; safety redesign saves ‚Çπ1L Cr crash costs + enables walking/cycling shift <a href="resources.html#ref-mot-road-accidents-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoT Road Accidents India 2024">[13]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Transit Fare Recovery Model</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Dynamic pricing, monthly passes, service frequency standards‚Äîtarget 60% opex recovery. <strong>Addresses:</strong> 100% Subsidy Dependency</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> 0% fare recovery kills expansion‚Äîno city can afford more buses; 60% recovery creates self-funding growth <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: EV Charging Infrastructure Blitz</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Deploy 100K public chargers; mandate 20% building parking‚Äîsolve range anxiety. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Charging Chicken-Egg (12K for 1.5M EVs)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Range anxiety blocks 30% EV adoption target‚Äîinfrastructure unlocks ‚Çπ30K Cr health savings from emissions reduction <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a> <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[180]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: TOD & Parking Mandate Repeal</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Abolish parking minimums; mandate 50% housing within 1km transit‚Äîdesign out car dependency. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Car-Centric Land Use</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Affects new development only; 10-year lag to stock turnover‚Äîbut prevents locking in sprawl for 50 years <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-nmt-policy-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA NMT Policy 2022">[12]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Freight Modal Shift Carbon Tax</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">‚Çπ50/ton-km road freight tax; rail subsidy‚Äîtarget 45% rail share. <strong>Addresses:</strong> 65% Road Freight Dominance</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Requires rail capacity expansion (3-5 years)‚Äîbut critical for logistics cost reduction (14% to 11% GDP) <a href="resources.html#ref-niti-zero-emission-vehicles-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NITI Zero Emission Vehicles 2022">[7]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü¢</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">FOUNDATIONAL: Satellite EV Impact Monitoring</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">TROPOMI NO2 tracking; validate 1.1% drop per 200 EVs‚Äîlink to health cost savings. <strong>Addresses:</strong> EV Benefit Invisibility</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why foundational:</strong> Creates evidence base for subsidy justification‚Äîbut doesn't drive adoption alone; pairs with charging infra <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[179]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="buildings">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Emissions & Carbon</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Buildings account for <strong>17-22% of India's CO‚ÇÇ emissions</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AEEE Embodied Carbon Report">[51]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>40% embodied carbon</strong> (materials/construction), 60% operational (energy use) <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AEEE Embodied Carbon Report">[51]</a></li>
                            <li>Cement capacity: <strong>690M tonnes</strong>, steel production: <strong>152MT/year</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>70% of 2047 infrastructure</strong> not yet built‚Äîcarbon lock-in window <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="RMI Build Right">[50]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Construction Pipeline</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Commercial real estate: <strong>78M sq.ft</strong> absorbed in 2025 <a href="resources.html#ref-jll-office-market-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="JLL Office Market Report">[52]</a></li>
                            <li>Residential: <strong>30M housing units</strong> needed by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-mordor-residential-forecast-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mordor Residential Forecast">[53]</a></li>
                            <li>Urban population: <strong>40% ‚Üí 50%</strong> by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-urban-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Urban Development">[180]</a></li>
                            <li>Construction sector contributes <strong>9% of GDP</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="RMI Build Right">[50]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Cooling Demand Crisis</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>AC peak load: <strong>46 GW (2025) ‚Üí 143 GW (2030)</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-icap-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="India Cooling Action Plan">[6]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>310M room AC units</strong> projected by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-cooling-action-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Cooling Research">[57]</a></li>
                            <li>AC efficiency testing: <strong>only 4 labs nationwide</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-ac-efficiency-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AC Efficiency Standards">[32]</a></li>
                            <li>Heat island effect: Urban areas <strong>3-7¬∞C hotter</strong> than rural <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-cool-roofs-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NRDC Cool Roofs Guide">[7]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Energy Code Compliance</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>ECBC notified: <strong>23 states</strong>, enforced: <strong>&lt;5 states</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-bee-ecbc-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ECBC Compliance Report">[5]</a></li>
                            <li>Only <strong>15 states</strong> adopted ECBC 2017 (latest) <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-building-energy-codes-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NRDC Building Codes Study">[31]</a></li>
                            <li>State Designated Agencies: <strong>~5 staff/state</strong> for all compliance <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-building-energy-codes-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NRDC Building Codes Study">[31]</a></li>
                            <li>Telangana TPA model: Only state with systematic third-party verification <a href="resources.html#ref-telangana-cool-roof-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Telangana Cool Roof Policy">[35]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Green Building Certifications</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>IGBC certified: <strong>10.33B sq.ft</strong> (cumulative) <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IGBC Statistics">[33]</a></li>
                            <li>GRIHA projects: <strong>545 rated</strong> (2024) <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-griha-projects-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="GRIHA Projects Database">[34]</a></li>
                            <li>ASSURE program: <strong>100M sq.ft</strong> target by partners <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-assure-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS ASSURE Program">[54]</a></li>
                            <li>CREDAI commitment: <strong>4,000 green projects</strong> by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-credai-green-projects-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CREDAI Green Initiative">[56]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Construction Pollution</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Construction: <strong>Major PM10/PM2.5 source</strong> in cities <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-dust-mitigation-2017" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB Dust Guidelines">[74]</a></li>
                            <li>Heavy vehicles near sites: <strong>PM10=270¬µg/m¬≥</strong> (WHO limit: 15) <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-road-dust-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Road Dust Study">[77]</a></li>
                            <li>C&D waste: <strong>150-500 MT/year</strong>, &lt;7% recycled <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-cd-waste-management-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB C&D Waste Rules">[95]</a></li>
                            <li>Sand extraction: <strong>700 MT/year</strong>, mostly illegal <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Milestones</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">Targets are organized into <strong>Shift Indicators</strong> (tracking paradigm change) and <strong>Outcome Indicators</strong> (tracking physical results). Shift indicators are leading; outcome indicators are lagging.</p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <!-- Shift Indicators Column -->
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-blue-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üìä</span>
                Shift Indicators (Paradigm Change)
            </h4>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 1: Ontological (Bio-centric)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>30% of new commercial buildings</strong> specify passive cooling as primary strategy <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-cool-roofs-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[7]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>5 architecture schools</strong> with mandatory bioclimatic design curriculum</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 3: Agency (Active Demanders)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>2 major property portals</strong> offer energy rating as search filter</li>
                        <li><strong>10% price premium</strong> correlation with energy performance ratings <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[33]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 4: Governance (Accountability)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>5 states</strong> link OC to ECBC verification (TPA model) <a href="resources.html#ref-telangana-cool-roof-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[35]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>100 TPAs certified</strong> per 1000 building permits in target states</li>
                        <li><strong>10 cities</strong> with public ECBC compliance dashboards <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-building-energy-codes-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[31]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 5: Time Horizon (Lifecycle)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>50% of public tenders &gt;10K sq.ft</strong> require lifecycle cost analysis <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>10 green mortgage products</strong> launched by banks <a href="resources.html#ref-ifc-green-buildings-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[65]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 6: Objectives (Multi-dimensional)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>IGBC/GRIHA updates</strong> include comfort hours + embodied carbon metrics</li>
                        <li><strong>3 states</strong> include resilience features in building codes for vulnerable zones</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Outcome Indicators Column -->
                    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-green-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üìà</span>
                Outcome Indicators (Physical Results)
            </h4>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">High-Performance Buildings</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>10M sq.ft HPB construction</strong> completed (ASSURE Year 1) <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-assure-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[54]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>50% of new commercial buildings</strong> meet ECBC+ standards <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-building-energy-codes-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[31]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Cooling & Comfort</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>200K cool roofs</strong> installed across 10 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-cool-roofs-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[7]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>5 district cooling systems</strong> operational in metros <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-cooling-action-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[57]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>30% peak cooling load reduction</strong> in retrofitted buildings <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-icap-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[6]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Materials & Circularity</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>15% of new construction</strong> uses low-carbon cement alternatives <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>30% C&D waste recycling rate</strong> in top 50 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-cd-waste-management-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[95]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Capacity & Infrastructure</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>10,000 masons/contractors</strong> trained in efficient techniques <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[50]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>20 AC testing labs</strong> operational (up from 4) <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-ac-efficiency-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[32]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Investment Mobilized</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>$2B mobilized</strong> for green building projects <a href="resources.html#ref-ifc-green-buildings-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[65]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>5 embodied carbon LCA tools</strong> adopted by developer associations <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>


            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üèóÔ∏è Building Energy Cascade: Where Thermal Comfort Gets Lost</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Visualizing where thermal comfort gets lost in the building lifecycle ‚Äî from construction materials to operational cooling to actual useful comfort</p>
                <div id="building-emissions-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: AEEE, NRDC, India UNFCCC Third Biennial Report. Interactive diagram shows energy flow from materials ‚Üí construction ‚Üí operations ‚Üí waste heat.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Split incentives:</strong> Developer minimizes upfront cost, buyer pays 20-year energy bills <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="RMI Build Right">[50]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Build-and-sell model:</strong> No developer accountability post-sale; efficiency features never verified</li>
                            <li><strong>FSI gaming:</strong> Green building bonuses claimed, performance not tracked</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>AC as status symbol:</strong> Passive cooling seen as "inferior" despite thermal comfort benefits <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-cooling-action-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Cooling Research">[57]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Fixed 24¬∞C myth:</strong> International hotel standards ignored adaptive thermal comfort zones</li>
                            <li><strong>Cement = development:</strong> Embodied carbon not discussed in construction industry</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>SDA understaffing:</strong> ~5 staff/state for all ECBC compliance‚Äîreal estate growing faster <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-building-energy-codes-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NRDC Building Codes Study">[31]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>AC testing bottleneck:</strong> Only 4 labs nationwide; cannot verify star ratings at scale <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-ac-efficiency-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AC Efficiency Standards">[32]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Mason skills gap:</strong> Informal builders (60% of construction) don't know efficient techniques</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>No post-occupancy tracking:</strong> "Green" buildings' actual energy use unmeasured <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IGBC Statistics">[33]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Compliance blackbox:</strong> Only UP publishes list (129 buildings)‚Äîother states opaque <a href="resources.html#ref-bee-ecbc-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ECBC Compliance Report">[5]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Embodied carbon unknown:</strong> No LCA database for Indian materials/construction methods</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Notification ‚â† enforcement:</strong> 23 states notified ECBC; &lt;5 enforce <a href="resources.html#ref-bee-ecbc-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ECBC Compliance Report">[5]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>OC not linked:</strong> Occupancy certificates issued without ECBC verification (except Telangana)</li>
                            <li><strong>40% emissions ignored:</strong> Codes focus on operational; embodied carbon unregulated <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AEEE Embodied Carbon Report">[51]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Upfront cost barrier:</strong> Efficient features cost 5-15% more; savings over 10+ years <a href="resources.html#ref-ifc-green-buildings-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IFC Green Buildings Investment">[65]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No green mortgages:</strong> Banks don't differentiate efficient buildings in lending rates</li>
                            <li><strong>Developer cashflow:</strong> Margins tight; efficiency de-scoped first during cost cuts</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Sand mafia:</strong> 700 MT/year illegal extraction‚Äîlargest organized crime in India <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Fragmented supply chains:</strong> Low-carbon materials (m-sand, GGBS cement) not stocked by retailers</li>
                            <li><strong>Race to bottom:</strong> Procurement tenders prioritize lowest cost, not life-cycle value</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Six Paradigm Transformations</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-6"><strong>Systemic change requires shifting how we think, who has power, and what we value ‚Äî not just what technologies we deploy.</strong> These six paradigm shifts address the root causes of building sector emissions and inefficiency.</p>

                <!-- Shift 1: Ontological -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">1</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Ontological: Human-centric ‚Üí Bio-centric</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Buildings shift from "machines that produce comfort" to "living systems within ecosystems."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Architects design with climate, not against it</li>
                            <li>Codes reference "thermal comfort hours" not "AC tonnage"</li>
                            <li>Materials evaluated for ecological footprint</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">Major developer launches "zero AC" premium residential project ‚Äî and it sells out at premium prices</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> "AC as status symbol" culture</p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 2: Reframing -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">2</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Reframing: Problem Contributors ‚Üí Solution Mediums</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Buildings shift from "17-22% of emissions" to "regenerative infrastructure that generates, stores, and sequesters."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Net-zero baseline, net-positive aspiration</li>
                            <li>Performance metrics include contributions (kWh generated, liters harvested)</li>
                            <li>C&D waste becomes construction input</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">First state offers FAR bonus for regenerative buildings (not just "green" certification)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> 40% embodied carbon ignored by policy <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 3: Agency -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">3</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Agency: Passive Owners ‚Üí Active Demanders</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Buyers shift from accepting developer offerings to demanding energy ratings like they demand RERA compliance.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Energy performance certificates mandatory at sale/rent</li>
                            <li>Real estate portals display energy ratings prominently</li>
                            <li>Buyers negotiate on lifecycle costs, not just purchase price</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">Housing.com adds "Energy Rating" as default filter; 40% of users apply it within 6 months</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> Split incentives ‚Äî developer minimizes cost, buyer pays 20-year bills <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[50]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 4: Governance -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">4</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Governance: Top-Down Control ‚Üí Collective Action + Structured Accountability</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Shift from "government notifies, nobody enforces" to "third-party verification, public dashboards, professional liability."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>TPA model scaled across states (Telangana replication)</li>
                            <li>ECBC compliance dashboards publicly accessible</li>
                            <li>Architect/engineer professional liability for performance claims</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">First state ties municipal grants to ECBC compliance rates ‚Äî ULBs compete on building performance</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> 23 states notified ECBC, &lt;5 enforce; ~5 SDA staff per state <a href="resources.html#ref-bee-ecbc-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[5]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 5: Time Horizon -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">5</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Time Horizon: Short-Term Fixes ‚Üí Long-Term Solving + Evidence to Adaptation</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Shift from "optimize construction cost" to "optimize 30-year lifecycle performance with continuous evidence loops."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Lifecycle cost analysis mandatory for buildings &gt;10K sq.ft</li>
                            <li>Post-occupancy energy data reported annually</li>
                            <li>Building performance benchmarks publicly available</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">Bank offers 1% lower mortgage rate contingent on annual energy performance reporting</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> Build-and-sell model ‚Äî no developer accountability post-sale; no post-occupancy tracking <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[33]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 6: Objectives -->
                <div class="mb-0">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">6</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Objectives: Single Metric (carbon) ‚Üí Multi-Layered Systems (comfort + resilience + footprint)</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Shift from "green = low operational carbon" to "performance = thermal comfort + air quality + water + materials + resilience + embodied carbon + health."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Building ratings include comfort hours, not just energy use</li>
                            <li>Indoor air quality monitoring becomes standard</li>
                            <li>Climate resilience features required in vulnerable zones</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">IGBC launches "Regenerative Building" certification with 8+ performance dimensions</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> "Green" buildings' actual performance unmeasured; embodied carbon unregulated <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>


            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 6. MARKERS SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">Organized by indicator type: <strong>Leading</strong> (early signals), <strong>Lagging</strong> (confirmation), and <strong>Discourse</strong> (language/narrative changes).</p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <!-- Leading Indicators -->
                    <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-5 h-5 bg-amber-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üîÆ</span>
                Leading Indicators (Early Signals)
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 1:</strong> <span class="text-xs">Architecture competition entries featuring passive cooling (track annually)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 3:</strong> <span class="text-xs">Energy queries in developer sales calls (industry survey) <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[33]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 4:</strong> <span class="text-xs">TPA certification applications per month (track pipeline)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 5:</strong> <span class="text-xs">% of public tenders mentioning "lifecycle cost" (document analysis)</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 6:</strong> <span class="text-xs">Rating system update proposals including new dimensions</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Lagging Indicators -->
                    <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-5 h-5 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">‚úì</span>
                Lagging Indicators (Confirmation)
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>ECBC compliance rates</strong> by state (public dashboards) <a href="resources.html#ref-bee-ecbc-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[5]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>ASSURE sq.ft commitments</strong> vs completed certifications <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-assure-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[54]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Design-to-operation energy gap</strong> in certified buildings (should narrow)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Low-carbon cement market share</strong> (GGBS, fly ash blends) <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Cooling demand growth</strong> vs ICAP projections <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-icap-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[6]</a></span>
                </li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Discourse Markers -->
                    <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-5 h-5 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üí¨</span>
                Discourse Markers (Narrative Shifts)
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Developer marketing</strong> highlights passive cooling, thermal comfort over AC tonnage</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Policy documents</strong> reference "comfort," "health," "resilience" alongside "energy"</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Media coverage</strong> shifts from "green premium" to "efficiency dividend" framing</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Architect RFPs</strong> request whole-life carbon accounting <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Material supplier catalogs</strong> prominently feature low-carbon products</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift-Specific Marker Table -->
                <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
                    <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Shift-by-Shift Progress Tracker</h4>
                    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-xs">
                <thead class="bg-gray-50">
                    <tr>
                        <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Shift</th>
                        <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Baseline Signal</th>
                        <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Year 1 Signal</th>
                        <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Year 3 Signal</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium">#1 Bio-centric</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">AC default in all premium projects</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">2+ "passive-first" projects launched</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">30% commercial specify passive primary</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium">#3 Active Demanders</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">No energy filter on property portals</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">1 portal adds energy rating filter</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">10% price premium for rated buildings</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium">#4 Accountability</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">Only Telangana has TPA model</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">3 states announce TPA replication</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">5 states link OC to ECBC verification</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium">#5 Lifecycle</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">No tenders require LCA</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">5 public agencies pilot LCA requirement</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">50% public tenders &gt;10K sq.ft require LCA</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium">#6 Multi-dimensional</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">Ratings focus on operational energy</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">IGBC announces comfort/embodied metrics</td>
                        <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-600">Multi-dimensional reporting standard</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>


            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 7. STRATEGIES SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-600">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Organized by Shift-Enabling Power</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">Strategies are prioritized by which paradigm shifts they enable. High-leverage strategies enable multiple shifts and address root Hidden Dynamics.</p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

                    <!-- Strategy 1: TPA Ecosystem -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">1. TPA Ecosystem Replication</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">HIGH LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#4 Governance, #5 Time Horizon</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">SDA understaffing; OC not linked to ECBC</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Replicate Telangana TPA model to 5 states ‚Äî third-party assessors verify compliance, OC linked to ECBC verification <a href="resources.html#ref-telangana-cool-roof-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[35]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Train 100 TPAs in 5 states over 3 years</li>
                <li>Cost-recovery model via developer fees</li>
                <li>Public compliance dashboards in all states</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 2: Energy Disclosure -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">2. Energy Disclosure at Transaction</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">HIGH LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#3 Agency, #5 Time Horizon</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Split incentives; Build-and-sell model</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Mandatory energy performance certificates at sale/rent + green mortgage products <a href="resources.html#ref-ifc-green-buildings-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[65]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Real estate portals display energy ratings like RERA compliance</li>
                <li>0.5-1% rate discount for certified efficient buildings</li>
                <li>Builder performance ratings based on post-occupancy data</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 3: Embodied Carbon LCA -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">3. Embodied Carbon LCA Mandates</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">HIGH LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#2 Reframing, #5 Time Horizon, #6 Objectives</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">40% embodied carbon ignored</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Whole-life carbon LCA for public buildings &gt;10K sq.ft + India-specific embodied carbon database <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[51]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Green procurement rules prioritize low-carbon cement/steel</li>
                <li>Developer associations adopt voluntary LCA disclosure</li>
                <li>Material EPDs (Environmental Product Declarations) ecosystem</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 4: Passive-First Thermal Comfort -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">4. Passive-First Thermal Comfort</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">MEDIUM LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#1 Ontological, #6 Objectives</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">AC as status symbol; AC lock-in</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Revise codes to mandate passive cooling measures before AC sizing <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-cool-roofs-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[7]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Cool roof mandates in hot-dry/hot-humid zones</li>
                <li>District cooling pilots in 5 high-density developments <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-cooling-action-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[57]</a></li>
                <li>Adaptive thermal comfort standards (23-27¬∞C range)</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 5: Mason Training -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">5. Informal Builder Capacity</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">MEDIUM LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#4 Governance (inclusive), #2 Reframing</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">60% informal construction unreached by codes</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Mason training + simplified "vernacular energy code" for small builders <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[50]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>10,000 masons trained in passive cooling, low-carbon materials</li>
                <li>Model designs library: pre-approved efficient layouts</li>
                <li>Material labeling at retail: color-coded efficiency ratings</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 6: Rating System Evolution -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">6. Multi-Dimensional Rating Systems</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">FOUNDATIONAL</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#6 Objectives, #2 Reframing</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">No post-occupancy tracking; Certification without verification</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Work with IGBC/GRIHA to add comfort, resilience, embodied carbon, health metrics <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[33]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Comfort hours metric alongside energy use</li>
                <li>Indoor air quality monitoring as standard</li>
                <li>Post-occupancy performance verification</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Strategy-Shift Matrix -->
                <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
                    <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Strategy ‚Üí Shift ‚Üí Hidden Dynamic Matrix</h4>
                    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-xs">
                <thead class="bg-gray-50">
                    <tr>
                        <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Strategy</th>
