            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Externalities</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Cooling energy burden:</strong> 46 GW peak load = ‚Çπ2.3L crore annual grid investment <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-icap-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="India Cooling Action Plan">[6]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Health externality:</strong> Construction dust = ‚Çπ80K crore/year health costs (PM2.5 exposure) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-dust-mitigation-2017" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB Dust Guidelines">[74]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Material depletion:</strong> Sand extraction destroying river ecosystems‚Äîno market price for ecological damage</li>
                            <li><strong>Carbon lock-in:</strong> 70% of 2047 infrastructure not built‚Äîdecisions today lock in 30-year emissions <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="RMI Build Right">[50]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Benefits</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Energy savings:</strong> 30-50% reduction in operational costs for green buildings <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IGBC Statistics">[33]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Property premium:</strong> 10-20% higher resale value, 15% rental premium for certified buildings <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IGBC Statistics">[33]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Avoided grid capacity:</strong> Gujarat ECBC enforcement avoids 6,200 MW by 2050 (‚Çπ31K crore savings) <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-building-energy-codes-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NRDC Building Codes Study">[31]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>GDP contribution:</strong> Construction = 9% of GDP; green shift creates high-skill jobs <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="RMI Build Right">[50]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>$1.4 trillion</strong> green buildings market by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-ifc-green-buildings-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IFC Green Buildings Investment">[65]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>$1.6 trillion</strong> cooling investment opportunity by 2040 <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-greener-cooling-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Greener Cooling">[67]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ31 trillion</strong> ($358B) green infrastructure by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Investment">[178]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>$70-80 billion</strong> green building materials market by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Climate">[179]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. INVESTMENTS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üíµ Investments: Capital Allocation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capex (Capital Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>TPA ecosystem setup:</strong> ‚Çπ50 crore (100 assessors trained, certification systems, software)</li>
                            <li><strong>AC testing lab expansion:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore (16 new labs @ ‚Çπ12.5 crore each) <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-ac-efficiency-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AC Efficiency Standards">[32]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>District cooling pilots:</strong> ‚Çπ500 crore (5 systems in metros) <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-cooling-action-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Cooling Research">[57]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Public compliance dashboards:</strong> ‚Çπ30 crore (software, integration with building dept systems)</li>
                            <li><strong>LCA database development:</strong> ‚Çπ20 crore (Indian materials/construction methods)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Capex:</strong> ‚Çπ800 crore (~$100M) over 3 years</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Opex (Operational Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Mason training programs:</strong> ‚Çπ15 crore/year (10,000 masons @ ‚Çπ15K/person) <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="RMI Build Right">[50]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>TPA operational support:</strong> ‚Çπ10 crore/year (coordination, quality assurance, recertification)</li>
                            <li><strong>Cool roof rebates:</strong> ‚Çπ60 crore/year (200K roofs @ ‚Çπ30K subsidy/roof) <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-cool-roofs-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NRDC Cool Roofs Guide">[7]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green mortgage incentives:</strong> ‚Çπ50 crore/year (interest rate buydown fund for banks)</li>
                            <li><strong>Monitoring & evaluation:</strong> ‚Çπ5 crore/year (dashboard updates, compliance audits)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Opex:</strong> ‚Çπ140 crore/year (~$17M/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">Note: Most capex recoverable via developer fees (TPA model) and energy savings (district cooling). Opex offset by avoided grid investment (6,200 MW = ‚Çπ31K crore savings in Gujarat alone).</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Urgency-Ranked Priorities</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Partner-driven interventions addressing hidden dynamics, not adding capacity. Ranked by leverage potential.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: TPA Ecosystem Replication</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Telangana TPA model to 5 states‚Äîlink OC to ECBC compliance. <strong>Addresses:</strong> ECBC Paper Tiger</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> 70% of 2047 infrastructure being built now‚Äîenforcement gap locks in inefficiency <a href="resources.html#ref-telangana-cool-roof-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Telangana TPA Model">[35]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Embodied Carbon LCA Mandates</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Whole-life carbon accounting for public buildings &gt;10K sq.ft. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Embodied Carbon Blind Spot</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> 40% of emissions ignored; cement/steel demand doubling by 2030‚Äîmust intervene before material lock-in <a href="resources.html#ref-aeee-embodied-carbon-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AEEE Embodied Carbon Report">[51]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Energy Disclosure at Sale</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Mandatory EPCs for property transactions + green mortgages. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Developer Incentive Gap</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Aligns buyer-seller incentives; market-based enforcement more scalable than regulatory <a href="resources.html#ref-ifc-green-buildings-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IFC Green Buildings Investment">[65]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Cool Roof Policy Replication</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Scale Telangana cool roof policy to 10 hot-dry/hot-humid states. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Cooling Lock-in</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Low-cost intervention (‚Çπ30K/roof), 2-7¬∞C temperature reduction, immediate comfort + peak load reduction <a href="resources.html#ref-nrdc-cool-roofs-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NRDC Cool Roofs Guide">[7]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Mason Training at Scale</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">10,000 informal builders trained in efficient techniques. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Informal Construction Shadow</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Reaches 60% of construction; behavior change takes time but compounds <a href="resources.html#ref-rmi-build-right-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="RMI Build Right">[50]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: AC Testing Lab Expansion</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Expand from 4 to 20 labs‚Äîenable star rating verification. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Capacity Bottleneck</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Critical for AC efficiency enforcement but requires capex + 2-year setup time <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-ac-efficiency-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="AC Efficiency Standards">[32]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- AIR QUALITY SECTOR -->
        <div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="air">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Air Quality Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">NCAP Infrastructure & Coverage</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>130 NCAP cities</strong> with ‚Çπ19,614 Cr allocated (75% utilized) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard NCAP 2026">[181]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>500+ CAAQMS stations</strong> operational across 280+ cities <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Sensors 2026">[183]</a></li>
                            <li>Regional distribution: <strong>North 180+</strong>, South 65+, West 75+, East 45+ sensors <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Sensors 2026">[183]</a></li>
                            <li>Only <strong>12% census towns</strong> have monitoring; 47% population outside grid <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Health Burden Crisis</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>0.95M deaths/year</strong> attributable to air pollution (2nd health risk factor) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>27.4M DALYs lost</strong> annually to PM2.5 and ozone exposure <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>$36.8B GDP loss</strong> (1.36% GDP) from health impacts in 2019 <a href="resources.html#ref-gbd-air-pollution-health-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="GBD Air Pollution Health 2019">[68]</a></li>
                            <li>Delhi PM2.5: <strong>~100 ¬µg/m¬≥</strong> (WHO standard: 15 ¬µg/m¬≥) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-naaqms-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB NAAQMS 2025">[36]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Pollution Source Profile</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Road dust: 25-40%</strong> of urban PM2.5/PM10 <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-dust-mitigation-2017" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB Dust Mitigation 2017">[74]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Vehicles: 20-35%</strong> (60-80% at local hotspots) <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-road-dust-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ScienceDirect Road Dust 2021">[77]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Industry: 20-40%</strong> in airshed cities; 81% stacks missing >1000 hrs data <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-industrial-emissions-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Industrial Emissions">[CEEW]</a></li>
                            <li>Only <strong>50 of 130</strong> NCAP cities have source apportionment studies <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Co-Investment Ecosystem</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>AMRUT parks: ‚Çπ1,768 Cr</strong> allocated for green infrastructure <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Investment 2026">[184]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NMT infrastructure: ‚Çπ1,436 Cr</strong> reducing vehicular pollution <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Investment 2026">[184]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>42,500 TPD waste processing</strong> reducing open burning emissions <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Investment 2026">[184]</a></li>
                            <li>Multi-sector convergence multiplies air quality co-benefits <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Investment 2026">[184]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Technology Integration</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>TROPOMI satellite:</strong> Global NO2 tracking at ~1km¬≤ resolution <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[80]</a></li>
                            <li>Validated: <strong>200 ZEVs = 1.1% NO2 reduction</strong> (California study) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Eckel ZEV NO2 California 2025">[80]</a></li>
                            <li>India projection: <strong>2.88 ¬µg/m¬≥ PM2.5 reduction</strong> by 2030 from EV transition <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[82]</a></li>
                            <li>Low-cost sensors: Respirer 2,000+, Google Air View+ 150 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-igbc-statistics-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IGBC Statistics 2024">[33]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">NCAP Budget Allocation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>67% funds to road dust</strong> (mechanized sweeping, water sprinkling) <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>4% to monitoring,</strong> 1% each to industry enforcement and outreach <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>82 cities</strong> utilized &lt;40% of NCAP allocation (2019-2025) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard NCAP 2026">[181]</a></li>
                            <li>Allocation misaligned with source contribution science <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Milestones</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">Targets are organized into <strong>Shift Indicators</strong> (tracking paradigm change) and <strong>Outcome Indicators</strong> (tracking physical results). Shift indicators are leading; outcome indicators are lagging.</p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <!-- Shift Indicators Column -->
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-blue-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üìä</span>
                Shift Indicators (Paradigm Change)
            </h4>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 1: Ontological (Visible Health Commons)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>10 cities</strong> publish daily AQ-health correlation dashboards (admissions vs AQI) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[182]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>1M+ downloads</strong> of personal AQ monitoring apps across NCAP cities</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 2: Reframing (Source Control)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>NCAP fund allocation:</strong> 50% to source control (up from 33%) <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[41]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>5 cities</strong> with real-time source attribution models operational</li>
                        <li><strong>Industrial closure notices</strong> issued within 48 hours of CEMS violation in 50 clusters</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 3: Agency (Active Protectors)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>100+ community sensing networks</strong> active with ward-level data <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[183]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>20 PILs filed</strong> using hyperlocal sensor data as evidence</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 4: Governance (Airshed Coordination)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>3 airshed authorities</strong> operational beyond NCR (Bengaluru, Chennai, Kolkata) <a href="resources.html#ref-caqm-revised-grap-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[79]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>Interstate agreements signed</strong> for 2 airsheds with binding source control commitments</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 5: Time Horizon (Prevention)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>GRAP measures:</strong> 50% prevention-based (up from 10%)</li>
                        <li><strong>5 metros</strong> with 72-hour AQ forecasting triggering proactive industrial coordination</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-1">Shift 6: Objectives (Multi-Pollutant Health)</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>NCAP 2.0 framework</strong> includes NO2, ozone targets alongside PM2.5</li>
                        <li><strong>10 industrial clusters</strong> with health surveillance systems (pollution-linked admissions tracked)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Outcome Indicators Column -->
                    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-green-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üìà</span>
                Outcome Indicators (Physical Results)
            </h4>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Air Quality Improvements</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>20-30% PM2.5 reduction</strong> in 30 NCAP cities vs 2019 baseline <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[181]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>30% reduction</strong> in road dust PM2.5 contribution in 10 target cities <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-dust-mitigation-behaviour-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[78]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>15% NO2 reduction</strong> in metros (satellite-verified via TROPOMI) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[80]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Health Outcomes</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>50,000 avoided premature deaths</strong> annually through NCAP interventions <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[182]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>15% reduction</strong> in respiratory admissions during pollution season in target cities</li>
                        <li><strong>$10B reduction</strong> in annual health burden costs (from $36.8B baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-gbd-air-pollution-health-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[68]</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Industrial Compliance</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>50 industrial clusters</strong> with third-party CEMS verification <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-industrial-emissions-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[CEEW]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>CEMS uptime &gt;90%</strong> in 70% of monitored stacks (up from 19%)</li>
                        <li><strong>Public violator portals</strong> live in 10 states with real-time disclosure</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Monitoring Infrastructure</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>500+ low-cost sensors</strong> deployed with ward-level coverage in 20 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[183]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>60 NCAP cities</strong> with updated source apportionment studies (up from 50) <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[41]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>Open AQ India platform</strong> live with API access for researchers</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Stubble & Open Burning</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>40% reduction</strong> in satellite-detected fire counts (Punjab, Haryana) <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[41]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>10 biomass processing facilities</strong> operational with guaranteed residue purchase</li>
                        <li><strong>5 lakh acres</strong> covered by stubble collection programs at ‚Çπ500/acre</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-800 mb-1">Co-Investment Mobilized</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>‚Çπ10,000 Cr co-investment</strong> across AMRUT, SBM, NMT schemes <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[184]</a></li>
                        <li><strong>100,000 TPD waste processing</strong> capacity added (reducing open burning)</li>
                        <li><strong>15% EV penetration</strong> in target metros with verified NO2 co-benefit</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>


            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üå¨Ô∏è Air Pollution Flow: Sources to Health Impacts</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Visualizing how emissions from transport, industry, construction, and agriculture flow through the atmosphere to cause premature deaths and health burden</p>
                <div id="air-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: CPCB Source Apportionment Studies, GBD 2019, CEEW Industrial Emissions. Interactive diagram shows pollution sources ‚Üí atmospheric mixing ‚Üí health outcomes.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Multi-source pollution:</strong> No single owner‚Äîtransport, industry, construction, stubble burning all contribute <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Trans-boundary excuse:</strong> "Pollution comes from outside" used by cities to avoid local action</li>
                            <li><strong>Fragmented accountability:</strong> MoEFCC (policy), CPCB (monitoring), SPCBs (enforcement)‚Äîno single owner</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"Air pollution is seasonal":</strong> Winter spike narrative ignores year-round health burden <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>"Delhi problem" myth:</strong> 130 NCAP cities exceed standards, not just Delhi <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard NCAP 2026">[181]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Resignation vs action:</strong> "Nothing can be done" narrative blocks community mobilization</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Source apportionment incomplete:</strong> Only 50 of 130 cities have studies; most 5-10 years old <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>SPCB understaffing:</strong> Average 5-10 staff per city for all pollution; enforcement impossible <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-industrial-emissions-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Industrial Emissions">[CEEW]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No real-time attribution:</strong> Cities can't identify sources during pollution spikes to take targeted action</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>CAAQMS coverage uneven:</strong> 180+ North, 65+ South, 25+ Northeast‚Äîpopulation density ignored <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Sensors 2026">[183]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Industrial CEMS gaps:</strong> 81% stacks missing >1000 hrs data; self-reporting unverified <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-industrial-emissions-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Industrial Emissions">[CEEW]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Health-AQ disconnect:</strong> Respiratory admissions spike but no local correlation with AQ data <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>NCAP targets set but enforcement weak:</strong> 20-30% PM2.5 reduction goal by 2024‚Äîunmet in most cities <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard NCAP 2026">[181]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>BS-VI implementation incomplete:</strong> Old vehicles, illegal retrofitting persist <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-road-dust-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ScienceDirect Road Dust 2021">[77]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>GRAP seasonal only:</strong> Emergency measures during winter; no year-round action <a href="resources.html#ref-caqm-revised-grap-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAQM Revised GRAP 2023">[79]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ19,614 Cr allocated but 25% unutilized:</strong> Capacity constraints, approval delays <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard NCAP 2026">[181]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Funding fragmented:</strong> NCAP, XV-FC, state schemes‚Äîno integrated planning <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-naaqms-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB NAAQMS 2025">[36]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No polluter-pays mechanism:</strong> Industries pay penalties, not externality costs (‚Çπ3.28L Cr health burden) <a href="resources.html#ref-gbd-air-pollution-health-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="GBD Air Pollution Health 2019">[68]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Clean tech adoption slow:</strong> EVs at 8% penetration; cleaner fuels not price-competitive <a href="resources.html#ref-ibef-ev-market-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IBEF EV Market 2025">[81]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Price signals weak:</strong> No congestion charges, parking fees don't reflect pollution externality <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-road-dust-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ScienceDirect Road Dust 2021">[77]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Stubble residue no market:</strong> Biomass pellets, biochar have no buyers at scale‚Äîburning remains cheaper <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Six Paradigm Transformations</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-6"><strong>Clean air requires shifting from monitoring pollution to preventing it at source, from reactive crisis response to proactive health protection, and from fragmented accountability to coordinated airshed governance.</strong> These six paradigm shifts address why 0.95M deaths/year persist despite ‚Çπ19,614 Cr NCAP investment.</p>

                <!-- Shift 1: Ontological -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">1</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Ontological: Invisible Externality ‚Üí Visible Health Commons</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Air shifts from "invisible byproduct someone else causes" to "shared health resource we collectively protect."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Health costs attributed to specific pollution sources, not aggregated as "national burden"</li>
                            <li>Personal AQ monitors mainstream (like fitness trackers)</li>
                            <li>Ward-level data empowers residents to connect symptoms to sources</li>
                            <li>Hospital admissions correlated with daily AQ in public dashboards</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">City publishes real-time dashboard showing "respiratory admissions today: 340" alongside AQI ‚Äî and politicians face constituent pressure</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> Health burden invisibility ‚Äî 0.95M deaths/year abstract, not personal <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 2: Reframing -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">2</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Reframing: Monitoring Problem ‚Üí Solving at Source</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Shift from "measuring how bad it is" to "eliminating emissions at origin." Data becomes tool for action, not documentation of failure.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>NCAP funds shift from 67% road dust to source control (industry, transport)</li>
                            <li>Real-time source attribution triggers automatic enforcement (not manual orders)</li>
                            <li>Industrial CEMS data drives closure notices within 48 hours of violation</li>
                            <li>City action plans cite source apportionment, not just "deploy more sensors"</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">NCAP 2.0 framework ties city funding to PM2.5 reduction achieved, not activities completed or sensors deployed</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> Monitoring ‚â† enforcement ‚Äî 500+ CAAQMS stations, but data not driving action <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 3: Agency -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">3</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Agency: Passive Victims ‚Üí Active Protectors</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Citizens shift from "recipients of pollution" to "demanders of clean air" who use hyperlocal data to hold polluters and governments accountable.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Ward-level AQ data published; residents petition ULBs with specific source complaints</li>
                            <li>Community sensing networks identify illegal burning, industrial violations</li>
                            <li>Parents' groups demand AQ monitoring and health protocols in schools</li>
                            <li>Real estate values correlated with AQ ‚Äî buyers demand clean-air neighborhoods</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">RWA files PIL citing ward-level sensor data showing industrial source ‚Äî court orders closure within 30 days</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> "Nothing can be done" resignation ‚Äî community mobilization blocked by lack of hyperlocal data <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Sensors 2026">[183]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 4: Governance -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">4</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Governance: Fragmented City Silos ‚Üí Coordinated Airshed Accountability</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Shift from "each city blames pollution from outside" to "airshed-wide governance where upwind sources are accountable to downwind health."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>NCR CAQM model replicated in Bengaluru, Chennai, Kolkata airsheds</li>
                            <li>Unified source apportionment studies showing trans-boundary vs local contribution</li>
                            <li>Interstate pollution agreements ‚Äî upwind states commit to source control</li>
                            <li>Airshed-level PM2.5 targets replace city-level targets for regional pollutants</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh sign Bengaluru Airshed Agreement with binding source control commitments</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> Trans-boundary excuse ‚Äî "pollution comes from outside" used to avoid local action <a href="resources.html#ref-caqm-revised-grap-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAQM Revised GRAP 2023">[79]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 5: Time Horizon -->
                <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">5</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Time Horizon: Crisis Response ‚Üí Prevention + Early Warning</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Shift from "GRAP triggers during winter emergency" to "year-round prevention with 72-hour forecasting enabling proactive measures."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>GRAP measures 60% prevention-based, 40% response-based (vs 10%/90% today)</li>
                            <li>Construction site permits contingent on dust control compliance history</li>
                            <li>Industrial maintenance schedules coordinated with AQ forecasts</li>
                            <li>Hospital surge protocols activate 48 hours before predicted spike</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">Delhi's November pollution spike 30% lower than previous year ‚Äî attributed to pre-emptive industrial shutdown triggered by 72-hour forecast</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> GRAP reactive not preventive ‚Äî emergency measures during winter; no year-round action <a href="resources.html#ref-caqm-revised-grap-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAQM Revised GRAP 2023">[79]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift 6: Objectives -->
                <div class="mb-0">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">6</span>
            <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Objectives: PM2.5 Only ‚Üí Multi-Pollutant + Health Outcomes</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Shift from "reduce average PM2.5" to "improve health outcomes across all pollutants with environmental justice lens."</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">What This Looks Like</p>
                        <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>NCAP targets include NO2, ozone, CO alongside PM2.5/PM10</li>
                            <li>Health metrics (avoided deaths, respiratory admissions) tracked alongside AQI</li>
                            <li>Environmental justice mapping: low-income neighborhoods get priority intervention</li>
                            <li>Industrial cluster health surveillance with pollution-linked insurance pilots</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-3">
                        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-1">Breakthrough Moment</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">MoEFCC announces "50,000 avoided deaths" as primary NCAP 2.0 success metric, with PM2.5 as secondary indicator</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2"><strong>Addresses Hidden Dynamic:</strong> Single-metric focus ‚Äî PM2.5 average hides hotspots, ozone ignored, health outcomes unmeasured <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a></p>
            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>


            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 6. MARKERS SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">Organized by indicator type: <strong>Leading</strong> (early signals), <strong>Lagging</strong> (confirmation), and <strong>Discourse</strong> (language/narrative changes).</p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <!-- Leading Indicators -->
                    <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-5 h-5 bg-amber-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üîÆ</span>
                Leading Indicators (Early Signals)
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 1:</strong> <span class="text-xs">Personal AQ monitor sales growth rate in NCAP cities (track quarterly)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 2:</strong> <span class="text-xs">% of NCAP city action plans citing source apportionment data <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[41]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 3:</strong> <span class="text-xs">Community sensing network formation rate (new networks per quarter)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 4:</strong> <span class="text-xs">Inter-state meetings on airshed coordination (track MoM documents)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 5:</strong> <span class="text-xs">GRAP order language: % referencing "prevention" vs "emergency response"</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong class="text-xs text-amber-700">Shift 6:</strong> <span class="text-xs">NCAP 2.0 draft framework includes health outcome metrics (yes/no)</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Lagging Indicators -->
                    <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-5 h-5 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">‚úì</span>
                Lagging Indicators (Confirmation)
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>PM2.5 annual trends</strong> in 130 NCAP cities (3-year rolling average) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[181]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>NCAP fund utilization vs PM2.5 reduction correlation</strong> by city (efficiency metric)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Industrial CEMS data completeness</strong> (% stacks with &lt;100 hrs missing annually)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Satellite NO2 trends</strong> in metros (TROPOMI verified vs EV penetration) <a href="resources.html#ref-eckel-zev-no2-california-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[80]</a></span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Respiratory admission rates</strong> during pollution season (% change YoY) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[182]</a></span>
                </li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Discourse Markers -->
                    <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-5 h-5 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs">üí¨</span>
                Discourse Markers (Narrative Shifts)
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Media headlines</strong> shift from "AQI hits 400" to "industrial source caused 200 hospitalizations"</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>GRAP orders</strong> reference "prevention" and "forecast-based action" vs "emergency measures"</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>NCAP communications</strong> report "avoided deaths" alongside PM2.5 reductions</span>
                </li>
                <li class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100">
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>State government statements</strong> acknowledge trans-boundary contribution vs blame "pollution from outside"</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="text-xs"><strong>Real estate listings</strong> in metros highlight "low-pollution zone" or "AQI below 50 area"</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Shift-Specific Marker Table -->
                <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
                    <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Shift-by-Shift Progress Tracker</h4>
                    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-xs">
                <thead class="bg-gray-50">
                    <tr>
                        <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Shift</th>
                        <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Baseline Signal</th>
