            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 7. STRATEGIES SECTION (REWRITTEN) -->
            <!-- ============================================ -->

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-600">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Organized by Shift-Enabling Power</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">Strategies are prioritized by which paradigm shifts they enable. High-leverage strategies enable multiple shifts and address root Hidden Dynamics.</p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

                    <!-- Strategy 1: Outcome-Based NCAP Funding -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">1. Outcome-Based NCAP 2.0 Funding</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">HIGH LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#2 Reframing, #5 Time Horizon, #6 Objectives</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">67% funds to road dust; 82 cities &lt;40% utilization; Monitoring ‚â† action</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Shift NCAP funding criteria from "utilization rate" to "PM2.5 reduction achieved" ‚Äî performance bonuses for 20%+ reduction <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[181]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Reallocate 50% of road dust funds to source control (industrial compliance, EV transition)</li>
                <li>Public ranking of NCAP cities by outcome (not spending) ‚Äî peer pressure accountability</li>
                <li>Require city action plans to cite source apportionment before fund release</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 2: Third-Party Industrial Compliance -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">2. Third-Party Industrial CEMS Verification</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">HIGH LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#2 Reframing, #4 Governance, #1 Ontological</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">81% stacks missing &gt;1000 hrs data; Self-reporting unverified</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Mandate independent CEMS audits for 50 industrial clusters + public disclosure of violators <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-industrial-emissions-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[CEEW]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Link consent-to-operate renewals to CEMS uptime (&gt;90% required)</li>
                <li>48-hour closure notice protocol for verified exceedances</li>
                <li>Pollution tax pilots in 3 clusters ‚Äî revenue funds clean tech transition</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 3: Regional Airshed Governance -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">3. Regional Airshed Governance Replication</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">HIGH LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#4 Governance, #5 Time Horizon</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Trans-boundary excuse; Fragmented accountability across states</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Replicate NCR CAQM model in Bengaluru, Chennai, Kolkata airsheds ‚Äî coordinated enforcement across 3+ states <a href="resources.html#ref-caqm-revised-grap-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[79]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Unified source apportionment studies showing trans-boundary vs local contribution</li>
                <li>Interstate pollution agreements with binding source control commitments</li>
                <li>Joint monitoring networks ‚Äî sensors at state borders track pollution flow</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 4: Health-AQ Surveillance Integration -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">4. Health-AQ Surveillance Integration</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">HIGH LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#1 Ontological, #6 Objectives</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Health burden invisibility; No local AQ-health correlation</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Partner with 50+ hospitals in 10 metros ‚Äî track respiratory admissions vs AQ; publish daily correlation dashboards <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[182]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>48-hour early warning system ‚Äî hospital preparedness alerts before predicted spikes</li>
                <li>Attribute health costs to polluters ‚Äî industries in airshed fund community health programs</li>
                <li>Pollution-linked insurance pilots ‚Äî premiums vary by ward-level AQ</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 5: Real-Time Source Attribution -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">5. Real-Time Source Attribution</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">MEDIUM LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#2 Reframing, #3 Agency</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Only 50/130 cities have source studies; Studies 5-10 years old</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Deploy real-time attribution models in 5 cities ‚Äî combine CAAQMS, satellite, low-cost sensors for dynamic source identification <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[41]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Update source apportionment studies in 30 NCAP cities (receptor modeling)</li>
                <li>Public dashboards showing source contribution by hour ‚Äî transparency drives action</li>
                <li>Integrate attribution data into GRAP triggers ‚Äî targeted enforcement during spikes</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 6: Hyperlocal Community Sensing -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">6. Hyperlocal Community Sensing Networks</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">MEDIUM LEVERAGE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#3 Agency, #1 Ontological</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">12% census towns monitored; 47% population outside grid</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Deploy 500+ low-cost sensors at ward level in 20 cities ‚Äî train 100+ community groups on data interpretation <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[183]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Open AQ India platform with API access for researchers, media</li>
                <li>Link hyperlocal data to GRAP triggers ‚Äî automated construction site shutdowns at hotspots</li>
                <li>Ward-specific NCAP action plans ‚Äî residents demand targeted interventions</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 7: Stubble Residue Value Chains -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">7. Stubble Residue Value Chains</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">FOUNDATIONAL</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#2 Reframing, #5 Time Horizon</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Burning free; alternatives cost ‚Çπ1000+/acre; No residue market</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Establish 10 biomass pellet/biochar facilities in Punjab, Haryana ‚Äî guaranteed residue purchase price + farmer payment <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[41]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Link to biogas plants, thermal power co-firing ‚Äî create commodity market at scale</li>
                <li>Pay farmers ‚Çπ500/acre for residue collection ‚Äî make not burning profitable</li>
                <li>Enforce penalties only after market alternative operational in district</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy 8: Forecast-Based GRAP -->
                    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">8. Forecast-Based Prevention Protocol</h4>
                <span class="text-xs bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded font-medium">FOUNDATIONAL</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-3">
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 mb-1">Enables Shifts</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">#5 Time Horizon</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded p-2 border border-gray-100">
                    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Addresses Hidden Dynamics</p>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">GRAP seasonal only; Emergency measures without prevention</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong> Revise GRAP to 60% prevention-based measures + 72-hour forecasting system triggering proactive actions <a href="resources.html#ref-caqm-revised-grap-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline">[79]</a></p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                <li>Industrial maintenance schedules coordinated with AQ forecasts</li>
                <li>Construction permits contingent on dust control compliance history</li>
                <li>Year-round implementation vs winter-only emergency response</li>
            </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Strategy-Shift Matrix -->
                <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
                    <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Strategy ‚Üí Shift ‚Üí Hidden Dynamic Matrix</h4>
                    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-xs">
