            <!-- ============================================ -->

<!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Externalities</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Health burden: ‚Çπ3.28 Lakh Cr/year</strong> (1.36% GDP) from 0.95M deaths, 27.4M DALYs <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a> <a href="resources.html#ref-gbd-air-pollution-health-2019" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="GBD Air Pollution Health 2019">[68]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Productivity loss: 1.4B working days</strong> lost annually to sick leave from air pollution <a href="resources.html#ref-cleanairfund-economic-benefits-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Clean Air Fund Economic Benefits 2021">[69]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Agriculture impacts:</strong> Ozone reducing crop yields; stubble burning reducing soil health</li>
                            <li><strong>Road dust re-suspension:</strong> ‚Çπ500+ Cr/year on mechanized sweeping; pollution returns in hours <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-dust-mitigation-behaviour-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Dust Mitigation Behaviour 2024">[78]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Benefits</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>$95B GDP gain (3%)</strong> from achieving safe air quality levels nationally <a href="resources.html#ref-cleanairfund-economic-benefits-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Clean Air Fund Economic Benefits 2021">[69]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>1.7M premature deaths avoided</strong> annually (18% of all deaths preventable) <a href="resources.html#ref-cleanairfund-economic-benefits-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Clean Air Fund Economic Benefits 2021">[69,70]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>$6B higher revenues</strong> from increased worker productivity and reduced absenteeism <a href="resources.html#ref-cleanairfund-economic-benefits-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Clean Air Fund Economic Benefits 2021">[69]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>23% CO2 reduction by 2030:</strong> Clean air pathway co-benefit (transport, industry efficiency) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-greener-cooling-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Greener Cooling 2022">[67]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ19,614 Cr NCAP allocation:</strong> 25% unutilized; reallocation to source control creates 3x health benefit <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard NCAP 2026">[181]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ5,000 Cr co-investment:</strong> AMRUT parks, NMT, waste processing‚Äîmultiplier air quality gains <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-investment-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Investment 2026">[184]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Pollution tax revenue potential:</strong> ‚Çπ10,000+ Cr/year if industries pay health externality costs</li>
                            <li><strong>EV transition health dividend:</strong> 16,700-70,400 avoided deaths/year by 2040 from vehicle electrification <a href="resources.html#ref-icct-ev-health-impacts-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICCT EV Health Impacts 2022">[82]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. INVESTMENTS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üíµ Investments: Capital Allocation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capex (Capital Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Low-cost sensor network:</strong> ‚Çπ100 crore (500 sensors @ ‚Çπ20 lakh each; installation, calibration) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Sensors 2026">[183]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Source attribution models:</strong> ‚Çπ50 crore (5 cities; receptor modeling, software, training)</li>
                            <li><strong>CEMS audit infrastructure:</strong> ‚Çπ150 crore (50 clusters; third-party verification systems)</li>
                            <li><strong>Stubble residue processing:</strong> ‚Çπ300 crore (10 biomass pellet/biochar facilities @ ‚Çπ30 crore each)</li>
                            <li><strong>Regional airshed coordination systems:</strong> ‚Çπ50 crore (3 airsheds; unified monitoring, modeling platforms)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Capex:</strong> ‚Çπ650 crore (~$80M) over 3 years</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Opex (Operational Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Sensor network maintenance:</strong> ‚Çπ20 crore/year (calibration, data hosting, quality assurance)</li>
                            <li><strong>Source apportionment study updates:</strong> ‚Çπ30 crore/year (30 cities @ ‚Çπ1 crore/city)</li>
                            <li><strong>CEMS third-party audits:</strong> ‚Çπ40 crore/year (50 clusters @ ‚Çπ80 lakh/cluster)</li>
                            <li><strong>Stubble residue purchase subsidy:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore/year (5 lakh acres @ ‚Çπ500/acre farmer payment)</li>
                            <li><strong>Community sensing training:</strong> ‚Çπ10 crore/year (100 groups; workshops, data tools, advocacy support)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Opex:</strong> ‚Çπ300 crore/year (~$37M/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">Note: Capex recoverable via pollution taxes (‚Çπ10K+ Cr potential) and NCAP reallocation. Opex offset by avoided health costs (‚Çπ3.28L Cr burden ‚Üí $95B GDP gain from clean air).</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Urgency-Ranked Priorities</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Partner-driven interventions addressing hidden dynamics, not adding monitoring capacity. Ranked by health impact leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Outcome-Based NCAP Funding</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Shift funding from "utilization" to "PM2.5 reduction achieved"‚Äîreallocate 50% dust funds to source control. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Budget Misallocation (67% to dust)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> ‚Çπ19,614 Cr allocated; 82 cities utilized &lt;40%‚Äîfixing allocation creates 3x health impact without new funds <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-ncap-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard NCAP 2026">[181]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Industrial CEMS Third-Party Audits</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Mandate independent verification for 50 clusters; public violator disclosure. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Industrial Political Economy (20-40% PM2.5, 1% funds)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> 81% stacks missing >1000 hrs data‚Äîindustries emit but self-report; enforcement gap causes 0.3M deaths/year <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-industrial-emissions-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Industrial Emissions">[CEEW]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Real-Time Source Attribution</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Deploy dynamic attribution models in 5 cities‚Äîidentify sources during spikes for targeted enforcement. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Source Attribution Dodge (50/130 cities have studies)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Cities blame "pollution from outside" to avoid action‚Äîreal-time data enables targeted source control vs symbolic dust sweeping <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Regional Airshed Governance</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Replicate NCR CAQM in Bengaluru, Chennai airsheds‚Äî3+ states coordinated enforcement. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Trans-Boundary Excuse</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Metro airsheds span multiple states; unilateral action fails‚ÄîNCR CAQM model shows 15-20% reduction possible with coordination <a href="resources.html#ref-caqm-revised-grap-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAQM Revised GRAP 2023">[79]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Hyperlocal Community Sensing</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Deploy 500+ low-cost sensors at ward level in 20 cities‚Äîempower residents with neighborhood data. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Monitoring Coverage Crisis (12% census towns)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> 47% population outside CAAQMS grid‚Äîhyperlocal data democratizes air quality action, but requires community mobilization infrastructure <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-sensors-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Sensors 2026">[183]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Health-AQ Surveillance Integration</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Partner with 50+ hospitals‚Äîtrack respiratory admissions vs AQ spikes; early warnings. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Health Data Disconnect</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> ‚Çπ3.28L Cr health burden unattributed to polluters‚Äîlinking AQ-health data enables pollution-linked insurance, cost recovery from industries <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-aq-dashboard-health-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB AQ Dashboard Health 2026">[182]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü¢</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">FOUNDATIONAL: Stubble Residue Value Chains</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Establish 10 biomass pellet/biochar facilities; pay farmers ‚Çπ500/acre for residue. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Stubble Burning Stalemate</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why foundational:</strong> Seasonal but politically sensitive‚Äîcreates market alternative to burning; requires 2-3 years for facilities + farmer adoption before enforcement viable <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-aq-monitoring-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE AQ Monitoring 2024">[41]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- NEIGHBOURHOODS SECTOR -->
<div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="waste">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Waste System Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Waste Generation & Growth</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>160,000 TPD urban waste</strong> (58.4M tonnes/year, 2.8% annual growth) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li>Per capita: <strong>0.38 kg/day</strong> (projected 0.75 kg/day by 2050) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>250M tonnes legacy waste</strong> at 2,300+ dumpsites nationwide <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li>Projected: <strong>172M tonnes by 2030</strong> (4.3% CAGR); <strong>468M tonnes by 2050</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li>Composition: <strong>60% organic</strong>, 15% plastic, 10% paper, 15% other <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Collection & Segregation Gap</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>70% waste collected</strong> officially (112,000 TPD); 30% unaccounted <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>15-20% household segregation compliance</strong> despite 2016 rules <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li>Only <strong>Pune, Bengaluru, Indore</strong> enforce bulk generator segregation <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Single-bin collection trucks</strong> mix segregated waste in 60% cities <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li>Self-reported data: <strong>97% collection claimed</strong> vs ground reality 70% <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Processing Capacity Deficit</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>42,500 TPD processing capacity</strong> vs 160,000 TPD generated (27% coverage) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26 Climate">[184]</a></li>
                            <li>Composting: <strong>14,200 TPD</strong>; WtE: <strong>9,800 TPD</strong>; Bio-CNG: <strong>3,200 TPD</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>4,000+ processing plants</strong> but only 25% operate at capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-sustainable-swm-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Sustainable SWM 2024">[122]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>117,500 TPD infrastructure gap</strong> (73% of waste has nowhere to go) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26 Climate">[184]</a></li>
                            <li>C&D waste: <strong>7,300 TPD capacity</strong> vs 34,000 TPD generation (21% coverage) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-climate-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26 Climate">[184]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Specialized Waste Streams</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Plastic: <strong>3.5M tonnes/year</strong>, 25-30% recycling rate (up from 8%) <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li>E-waste: <strong>1.1M tonnes/year</strong>, 6.8% CAGR (fastest growing stream) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-ewaste-annual-2023-24" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB E-waste Annual 2023-24">[94]</a></li>
                            <li>C&D waste: <strong>12.4M tonnes/year</strong>, 7-8% annual growth <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-cd-waste-management-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB C&D Waste 2025">[95]</a></li>
                            <li>Hazardous: <strong>4.9M tonnes/year</strong>, 40% unaccounted/illegal dumping <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li>Biomedical: <strong>0.1M tonnes/year</strong>, 50% incineration capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Informal Sector Paradox</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>4M+ informal waste pickers</strong>, &lt;20% integrated with formal systems <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>70-80% plastic recycling</strong> done by informal sector (official systems fail) <a href="resources.html#ref-iwp-informal-plastic-collection-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IWP Informal Plastic Collection 2024">[132]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ30,000 Cr/year recyclable value</strong> recovered by informal workers <a href="resources.html#ref-globalrecycling-dry-waste-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Global Recycling Dry Waste 2024">[131]</a></li>
                            <li>Aggregators capture <strong>90% of value</strong>; pickers get 5-10% <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li>Municipal savings: <strong>‚Çπ55 Cr/year</strong> from 1.5M pickers (unpaid labor) <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Budget & Financial Crisis</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>60-70% ULB budget</strong> on street sweeping; &lt;5% on treatment <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li>User fee collection: <strong>&lt;30%</strong> of households pay waste charges <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ79,000 Cr NGT penalties</strong> levied on municipalities‚Äîmostly uncollected <a href="resources.html#ref-ngt-environmental-compensation-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NGT Environmental Compensation 2024">[87]</a></li>
                            <li>Tipping fees: <strong>‚Çπ200-400/tonne</strong> vs ‚Çπ800-1200 cost recovery needed <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li>SBM 2.0: <strong>‚Çπ30,980 Cr budget</strong> (2021-26) but ULB capacity gap persists <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">EPR & Extended Producer Responsibility</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>8,500+ manufacturers registered</strong> under EPR for plastic/e-waste <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li>Blockchain EPR: <strong>34 states operational</strong>, 12.4M+ credits traded (USD 187M market) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Gaming the system:</strong> Credits traded without actual recycling verification <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li>Plastic ban: <strong>SUP banned 2022</strong> but enforcement theatre‚Äîusage continues <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li>Compliance rate: <strong>&lt;40% manufacturers</strong> meet collection targets <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Technology Adoption</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Digital tracking: <strong>87% ULBs enrolled</strong> on CPCB systems (data quality unverified) <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li>AI segregation: <strong>156 cities deployed</strong>, 97.2% accuracy, 32% cost reduction <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li>IoT fleet tracking: <strong>89 cities live</strong>, +24% route efficiency, ‚Çπ450 Cr fuel savings <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li>Smart bins: <strong>4,850+ deployed</strong> for fill-level monitoring <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>3,200+ MRFs operational</strong> (+28% new facilities since 2020) <a href="resources.html#ref-kushaagra-mrf-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Kushaagra MRF India 2024">[124]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Circular Economy Milestones</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Processing Capacity Utilization</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>75% plant capacity utilization</strong> (from 25% baseline)‚Äîuse what we have first <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-sustainable-swm-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Sustainable SWM 2024">[122]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>60,000 TPD new capacity</strong> added: 80% composting/bio-CNG, 20% WtE <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bio-CNG: 12,000 TPD</strong> operational (from 3,200 TPD baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>C&D waste: 15,000 TPD capacity</strong> (from 7,300 TPD)‚Äîrecycle construction debris <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-cd-waste-management-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB C&D Waste 2025">[95]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>&lt;20% waste to landfill</strong> (from 73% baseline)‚Äîresidual waste only <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Segregation & Collection</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>60% household segregation compliance</strong> (from 15-20% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100% segregated collection</strong> in 50 pilot cities (no single-bin trucks) <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>85% waste collection coverage</strong> (from 70% baseline)‚Äîclose the gap <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bulk generator compliance: 80%</strong> (hotels, malls, hospitals segregate at source) <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>AI segregation: 300 cities</strong> (from 156 baseline)‚Äîautomate sorting <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Informal Sector Integration</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>75% waste picker formalization</strong> (from &lt;20% baseline)‚Äîdignity + fair wages <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>500 picker cooperatives</strong> operational with direct market access <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>40% value retention</strong> by pickers (from 5-10% baseline)‚Äîcut middlemen <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Social protection coverage: 2M workers</strong> (health, insurance, pension) <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Recognition in policy:</strong> Waste workers as municipal employees in 20 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Recycling & Circularity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Plastic recycling: 50%</strong> (from 25-30% baseline)‚Äîclose the loop <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>E-waste collection: 70%</strong> (from current 30%)‚Äîtoxic waste off streets <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-ewaste-annual-2023-24" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB E-waste Annual 2023-24">[94]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Organic waste: 90% composted</strong> or bio-CNG (from 30% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>MRF coverage: 5,000 facilities</strong> (from 3,200 baseline)‚Äîdecentralized sorting <a href="resources.html#ref-kushaagra-mrf-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Kushaagra MRF India 2024">[124]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Secondary material market: ‚Çπ50,000 Cr/year</strong> (from ‚Çπ30,000 Cr baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-globalrecycling-dry-waste-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Global Recycling Dry Waste 2024">[131]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Legacy Waste Remediation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>500 hectares remediated</strong> (from 320 baseline)‚Äîunlock land value <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>300 active remediation projects</strong> (from 156 baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50M tonnes legacy waste processed</strong> (20% of 250M tonne backlog) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100% leachate treatment</strong> at capped dumpsites (stop groundwater contamination) <a href="resources.html#ref-cwe-landfill-management-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CWE Landfill Management 2024">[123]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Independent verification</strong> of remediation (no "moving waste elsewhere") <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Budget & Finance Rebalancing</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Budget flip: 40% on treatment</strong> (from &lt;5% baseline)‚Äîshift from sweeping <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>User fee collection: 70%</strong> (from &lt;30% baseline)‚Äîcost recovery <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tipping fees: ‚Çπ800/tonne</strong> (from ‚Çπ200-400 baseline)‚Äîfull cost recovery <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Outcome-based contracts: 50% of PPPs</strong> (reward diversion, not collection) <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green bonds: ‚Çπ40,000 Cr mobilized</strong> for waste-to-value infrastructure <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Circular Economy 2025">[89]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">EPR Enforcement & Accountability</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>EPR compliance: 80%</strong> (from &lt;40% baseline)‚Äîmanufacturers pay their share <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Verified recycling credits:</strong> Blockchain tracking with on-ground audits <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Plastic ban enforcement:</strong> ‚Çπ10,000 fines automated via AI detection <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>E-waste take-back: 15,000+ collection points</strong> by manufacturers <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-ewaste-annual-2023-24" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB E-waste Annual 2023-24">[94]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NGT penalty collection: 50%</strong> (‚Çπ40,000 Cr of ‚Çπ79,000 Cr backlog) <a href="resources.html#ref-ngt-environmental-compensation-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NGT Environmental Compensation 2024">[87]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üóëÔ∏è Waste Flow: Generation to Disposal</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">From household generation through collection and segregation to treatment‚Äîhighlighting where material value is lost</p>
                <div id="waste-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: CPCB Annual Report 2024-25, Economic Survey 2025-26 Climate Chapter, TERI Waste Study 2023. Interactive diagram shows 160,000 TPD waste ‚Üí collection gap ‚Üí segregation failure ‚Üí treatment deficit ‚Üí landfill leakage.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">India has 4,000+ processing plants but only 25% operate at capacity. The problem isn't technology‚Äîit's incentives, ownership confusion, and who captures value from waste.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"Waste = municipality's problem":</strong> Citizens expect collection but resist segregation or fees <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>First-mile collection gaps:</strong> 30% waste uncollected‚Äîno formal system in slums <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bulk generator non-compliance:</strong> Hotels, malls dump mixed waste‚Äîonly 3 cities enforce penalties <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Fragmented ownership:</strong> ULBs (collection), State (policy), Centre (rules)‚Äîaccountability vacuum</li>
                            <li><strong>No citizen demand:</strong> Waste "out of sight, out of mind"‚Äîno electoral pressure for change</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"Throwaway culture":</strong> Disposable = convenience‚Äîno circular mindset in consumption <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Circular Economy 2025">[88]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>"Pickers = untouchables":</strong> 4M waste workers stigmatized despite doing 80% recycling <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>"Tech will fix it" myth:</strong> AI segregation hyped; household behavior unchanged (15% compliance) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>"Cleanliness = sweeping streets":</strong> Swachh Bharat metrics count toilets/sweeping, not waste reduction</li>
                            <li><strong>"Waste = dirty, recycling = poor":</strong> Middle class won't segregate‚Äî"maid's job"</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>ULB technical staff shortage:</strong> Only 20% cities have waste management professionals <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Plant operation incompetence:</strong> 75% plants idle due to lack of trained operators <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-sustainable-swm-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Sustainable SWM 2024">[122]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No waste composition data:</strong> Cities don't audit waste streams‚Äîplanning by guesswork <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Enforcement collapse:</strong> Segregation mandates exist; zero inspectors to verify compliance</li>
                            <li><strong>Contractor dependency:</strong> ULBs outsource everything‚Äîlose in-house knowledge and control</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"97% collection" claimed:</strong> Self-reported by ULBs; ground reality 70%‚Äîno verification <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Processing data "wildly at odds":</strong> Official stats vs TERI audit show 50% discrepancy <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Informal sector unquantified:</strong> 4M workers, ‚Çπ30K Cr value‚Äînot in official statistics <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No waste audits:</strong> Cities don't track composition, seasonality, or hotspots <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Digital tracking theatre:</strong> 87% ULBs on CPCB portal but data entry unverified <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>EPR non-compliance:</strong> &lt;40% manufacturers meet collection targets‚Äîno penalty enforcement <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Plastic ban theatre:</strong> SUP banned 2022; no fines levied; usage continues unchecked <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Segregation rules ignored:</strong> 2016 mandate; 8 years later 15% compliance; zero penalties <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NGT penalties uncollected:</strong> ‚Çπ79,000 Cr levied; &lt;10% recovered‚Äîno enforcement mechanism <a href="resources.html#ref-ngt-environmental-compensation-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NGT Environmental Compensation 2024">[87]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>WtE lobby capture:</strong> ‚Çπ500+ Cr plants need feedstock forever‚Äîundermine recycling targets</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Budget perversity: &lt;5% on treatment:</strong> 70% on sweeping‚Äîwrong end of problem <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>User fee non-collection:</strong> &lt;30% households pay‚Äîno revenue for services <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tipping fees below cost:</strong> ‚Çπ200-400/tonne charged vs ‚Çπ800-1200 needed‚Äîplants lose money <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tonnage contracts perverse incentive:</strong> PPPs paid per tonne collected, not diverted‚Äîmaximize waste <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Carbon finance untapped:</strong> Landfill gas/WTE can earn ‚Çπ5-20 lakh/MW/year‚Äînot monetized</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Secondary material markets fragmented:</strong> No aggregation‚Äîpickers sell to 100+ middlemen <a href="resources.html#ref-globalrecycling-dry-waste-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Global Recycling Dry Waste 2024">[131]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EPR credit gaming:</strong> Blockchain shows trades; on-ground recycling unverified <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No demand for recycled content:</strong> Virgin plastic cheaper‚Äîmanufacturers won't buy recycled <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Circular Economy 2025">[88]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>E-waste export loophole:</strong> "Refurbished" label hides illegal exports to Africa <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-ewaste-annual-2023-24" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB E-waste Annual 2023-24">[94]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Biomining scams:</strong> Remediation contracts "process" waste by moving it elsewhere</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Transformation Vision</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-4"><strong>Waste systems where prevention is prioritized, materials circulate in closed loops, organics return to soil, informal workers are formalized with dignity, and residual waste approaches zero.</strong></p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What Changes</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>From collection to prevention:</strong> Metrics shift from tonnes processed to tonnes reduced <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Circular Economy 2025">[88]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From dumping to circularity:</strong> 80% waste diverted‚Äîonly residual to engineered landfills <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From informal to formalized:</strong> 3M waste pickers get contracts, social protection, fair prices <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From sweeping to treatment:</strong> Budget flips‚Äî40% on processing, 30% on prevention, 30% on collection <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From tonnage to outcome contracts:</strong> PPPs rewarded for recycling rates, not collection volume <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Breakthrough Moments</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Segregation becomes norm:</strong> 60% compliance‚Äîkids teach parents; social proof cascades <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Picker cooperatives thrive:</strong> 500 cooperatives get 40% of ‚Çπ50K Cr recycling market value <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EPR enforcement real:</strong> 80% manufacturers comply; verified recycling‚Äîno credit gaming <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Legacy waste unlocks land:</strong> 500 hectares remediated = ‚Çπ25,000 Cr real estate value <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Circular economy visible:</strong> ‚Çπ3.5 trillion market by 2030‚Äîinvestors flood waste-to-value sector <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Circular Economy 2025">[89]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. MARKERS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Quantitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Plant capacity utilization:</strong> 75% target (from 25% baseline)‚Äîefficiency over new build <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-sustainable-swm-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Sustainable SWM 2024">[122]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Household segregation compliance:</strong> 60% (from 15-20%)‚Äîbehavior shift <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Waste picker formalization:</strong> 75% of 4M workers (from &lt;20%) <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Plastic recycling rate:</strong> 50% (from 25-30%)‚ÄîEPR working <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Landfill diversion:</strong> 80% waste treated (from 27% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Budget reallocation:</strong> 40% on treatment (from &lt;5%)‚Äîsystemic priority shift <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bio-CNG output:</strong> 12,000 TPD (from 3,200 TPD)‚Äîorganic waste valorization <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Legacy waste remediated:</strong> 500 hectares (from 320)‚Äîland reclamation <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Qualitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Narrative shift:</strong> Media covers "picker cooperatives thrive" not "ULBs fail to collect waste"</li>
                            <li><strong>Policy enforcement real:</strong> SUP ban fines automated via AI; ‚Çπ10K penalties actually levied <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Contract structure change:</strong> 50% of PPPs outcome-based (reward recycling, not tonnage) <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community mobilization:</strong> RWAs demand segregated collection‚Äîbottom-up pressure</li>
                            <li><strong>Informal sector recognition:</strong> 20 cities integrate pickers as municipal employees <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>EPR transparency:</strong> Blockchain credits audited on-ground‚Äîgaming exposed <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Independent verification norm:</strong> Third-party waste audits standard in 100 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-state-waste-management-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Waste Management 2023">[119]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Circular economy investments:</strong> VC funding floods waste-to-value startups‚Äîmarket signal</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7. STRATEGIES -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-600">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Intervention Pathways</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Utilize Existing Plants Before Building New</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 4,000+ plants at 25% capacity; 117,500 TPD gap <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-sustainable-swm-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Sustainable SWM 2024">[122]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Feedstock assurance contracts:</strong> ULBs guarantee segregated waste supply to plants</li>
                            <li><strong>Operator training programs:</strong> 75% plants idle due to technical incompetence‚Äîbuild capacity</li>
                            <li><strong>Performance incentives:</strong> Bonus payments for &gt;70% capacity utilization</li>
                            <li><strong>Segregated collection mandate:</strong> End single-bin trucks‚Äîplants need quality feedstock</li>
                            <li><strong>Target: 75% utilization (from 25%)</strong> = 90,000 TPD capacity unlocked‚Äîno new build needed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Waste Picker Formalization & Cooperatives</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 4M workers do 80% recycling; get 5-10% value <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Hasiru Dala model scale-up:</strong> Picker cooperatives in 100 cities with direct market access</li>
                            <li><strong>Municipal contracts for cooperatives:</strong> ULBs pay fair wages for segregation/collection services</li>
                            <li><strong>Social protection coverage:</strong> Health insurance, pension, accident coverage for 2M workers</li>
                            <li><strong>MRF ownership transfer:</strong> Picker cooperatives operate 500 facilities‚Äîvalue retention</li>
                            <li><strong>Target: 75% formalization; 40% value share</strong> (from &lt;20%, 5-10%)‚Äîequity + efficiency</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Outcome-Based Contracts (Not Tonnage)</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> PPPs paid per tonne collected‚Äîincentive to maximize waste <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Diversion-based payments:</strong> ‚Çπ1,500/tonne recycled vs ‚Çπ500/tonne collected</li>
                            <li><strong>Recycling rate targets:</strong> Contracts require 70% diversion to earn full payment</li>
                            <li><strong>Waste reduction bonuses:</strong> Pay contractors for reducing per-capita waste generation</li>
                            <li><strong>Independent verification:</strong> Third-party audits of recycling claims‚Äîno self-reporting</li>
                            <li><strong>Target: 50% of PPPs outcome-based</strong> by Year 3‚Äîalign incentives with goals</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. EPR Enforcement with Verified Recycling</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> &lt;40% EPR compliance; credit gaming rampant <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-plastic-waste-rules-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Plastic Waste Rules 2024">[93]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>On-ground audits:</strong> Blockchain EPR credits verified by physical site inspections</li>
                            <li><strong>Penalty automation:</strong> ‚Çπ10 lakh/month fines auto-levied on non-compliant manufacturers</li>
                            <li><strong>Take-back mandates:</strong> 15,000 collection points by e-waste/battery manufacturers</li>
                            <li><strong>Recycled content quotas:</strong> 30% recycled plastic mandatory in new packaging by 2028</li>
                            <li><strong>Target: 80% EPR compliance</strong> (from &lt;40%)‚Äîproducers pay for end-of-life</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Budget Flip: Treatment Over Sweeping</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 70% budget on sweeping; &lt;5% on treatment <a href="resources.html#ref-epw-swm-institutional-framework-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="EPW SWM Framework 2023">[120]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Reallocate 40% to treatment:</strong> Composting, MRFs, bio-CNG plants‚Äîshift priorities</li>
                            <li><strong>User fee collection drive:</strong> 70% collection rate (from &lt;30%)‚Äîcost recovery</li>
                            <li><strong>Tipping fee increase:</strong> ‚Çπ800/tonne (from ‚Çπ200-400)‚Äîfull cost recovery for processors</li>
                            <li><strong>Ring-fence treatment funds:</strong> Earmark SBM grants; no diversion to sweeping</li>
                            <li><strong>Target: 40% treatment, 30% prevention, 30% collection</strong>‚Äîinverse of current 70/25/5</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Segregation Enforcement with AI + Social Pressure</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 15-20% compliance despite 2016 mandate <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>AI bin monitoring:</strong> Smart bins detect contamination‚Äîinstant SMS fines (‚Çπ500/violation)</li>
                            <li><strong>Community champions:</strong> RWA leaders trained; peer pressure cascades‚Äî60% compliance target</li>
                            <li><strong>School curriculum:</strong> Kids learn segregation; teach parents‚Äîgenerational shift</li>
                            <li><strong>Color-coded infrastructure:</strong> Wet/dry/hazardous bins at every household‚Äîno excuse</li>
                            <li><strong>Target: 60% compliance (from 15-20%)</strong>‚Äîbehavior change via tech + social norms</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Legacy Waste Remediation with Independent Verification</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 250M tonnes legacy waste; biomining scams rampant <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Third-party oversight:</strong> Independent engineers verify remediation‚Äîno "moving waste"</li>
                            <li><strong>Land value capture:</strong> 50% of unlocked real estate value funds remediation‚Äîself-financing</li>
                            <li><strong>Leachate treatment mandatory:</strong> All capped dumps treat groundwater contamination</li>
                            <li><strong>Public dashboards:</strong> Monthly satellite imagery shows remediation progress‚Äîaccountability</li>
                            <li><strong>Target: 500 hectares remediated</strong> = ‚Çπ25,000 Cr land value unlocked + pollution stopped</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Externalities</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Land degradation: ‚Çπ15,000 Cr/year</strong> from 2,300+ dumpsites (250M tonnes legacy waste) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Health costs: ‚Çπ8,000 Cr/year</strong> from dumpsite pollution (respiratory, vector-borne diseases)</li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater contamination:</strong> Leachate affects 100M+ people‚Äîtreatment costs incalculable</li>
                            <li><strong>Methane emissions: 12 MtCO2e/year</strong> from organic waste dumping <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-biomethanation-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Biomethanation 2024">[90]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Material value lost: ‚Çπ30,000 Cr/year</strong> recyclables to landfills <a href="resources.html#ref-globalrecycling-dry-waste-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Global Recycling Dry Waste 2024">[131]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Informal sector exploitation:</strong> 4M workers generate ‚Çπ30K Cr; get ‚Çπ3K Cr (10% share) <a href="resources.html#ref-ilo-informal-waste-sector-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ILO Informal Waste Sector 2023">[96]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Benefits</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Circular economy value: ‚Çπ3.5 trillion/year by 2030</strong> (waste-to-resource transition) <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Circular Economy 2025">[89]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bio-CNG revenue: ‚Çπ2,460 Cr/year</strong> from 50% wet waste processing <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-biomethanation-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Biomethanation 2024">[90]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Recycling market growth: ‚Çπ50,000 Cr/year</strong> (from ‚Çπ30K Cr)‚Äîformal sector capture <a href="resources.html#ref-globalrecycling-dry-waste-potential-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Global Recycling Dry Waste 2024">[131]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Legacy waste land unlock: ‚Çπ25,000 Cr</strong> real estate value from 500 hectares remediated <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Carbon credits: ‚Çπ5-20 lakh/MW/year</strong> from landfill gas/WtE projects</li>
                            <li><strong>Collection cost savings: ‚Çπ1,200 Cr/year</strong> from IoT route optimization <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-annual-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Annual 2024">[83]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity & Employment</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Market size: USD 12.84 billion (2025) ‚Üí USD 18.65 billion (2034)</strong> at 4.3% CAGR <a href="resources.html#ref-mordor-waste-management-market-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mordor Waste Market 2025">[91]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>SBM 2.0 budget: ‚Çπ30,980 Cr (2021-26)</strong>‚Äîpublic investment anchor <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-sbm-progress-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA SBM Progress 2024">[84]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green bonds: ‚Çπ40,000 Cr mobilized</strong> for waste-to-value infrastructure <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Circular Economy 2025">[89]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Employment: 2.4M jobs created</strong> in formal waste sector <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-circular-economy-potential-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Circular Economy 2025">[88]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Plastic recycling jobs: 1.9M by 2047</strong> (circular economy transition) <a href="resources.html#ref-ceew-green-jobs-waste-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CEEW Green Jobs Waste 2024">[100]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>PPP pipeline: USD 400M+ (West India)</strong>‚ÄîMaharashtra USD 287M <a href="resources.html#ref-iig-waste-pipeline-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIG Waste Pipeline 2025">[92]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Partner-Driven Interventions</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Investment opportunities that address hidden dynamics and unlock systemic change‚Äînot just add capacity.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">üë∑</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Waste Picker Cooperatives</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Hasiru Dala model‚Äîformalize 3M workers; 40% value retention; social protection; MRF ownership</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Informal Sector Paradox</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">üìã</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Outcome-Based Contracts</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Replace tonnage PPPs with diversion-based payments‚Äî‚Çπ1,500/tonne recycled vs ‚Çπ500 collected</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Perverse Incentives</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">üìä</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Independent Waste Audits</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Third-party verification of 97% collection claims‚ÄîGPS tracking, weighbridges, satellite monitoring</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Data Integrity Crisis</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">üè≠</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Plant Utilization Programs</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Feedstock assurance + operator training‚Äî75% utilization of 4,000 plants before new build</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Capacity Underutilization</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">ü§ñ</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">AI Segregation Scale-Up</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">300 cities (from 156)‚Äî97.2% accuracy, 32% cost reduction, instant fine automation</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Lab vs Reality Gap</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">‚ôªÔ∏è</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">EPR Verified Recycling</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">On-ground audits of blockchain credits‚Äî80% compliance, no gaming, recycled content quotas</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Policy Non-Enforcement</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">üå±</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Bio-CNG Plant Network</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">12,000 TPD capacity‚Äî‚Çπ2,460 Cr/year revenue, 10M tonnes CO‚ÇÇ avoided, organic waste valorization</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Supply Obsession</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">üèóÔ∏è</div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Legacy Waste Remediation Oversight</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Independent verification; land value capture‚Äî500 hectares, ‚Çπ25K Cr real estate unlocked</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Dynamic: Political Economy</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. REGIONAL STRATEGY -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üó∫Ô∏è Regional Strategy: Tier-Based Implementation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Tier 1 Cities (10 metros)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Focus:</strong> Utilize existing 75% of 4,000 plants; scale picker cooperatives; EPR enforcement</li>
                            <li><strong>Tech:</strong> AI segregation 100% coverage; IoT fleet tracking; blockchain EPR audits</li>
                            <li><strong>Outcome contracts:</strong> 100% PPPs diversion-based by Year 3</li>
                            <li><strong>Target:</strong> 80% waste diverted; &lt;20% to engineered landfills</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment:</strong> ‚Çπ15,000 Cr‚Äîtech + formalization + legacy remediation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Tier 2 Cities (50 cities)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Focus:</strong> Decentralized MRFs (3,200 ‚Üí 5,000); bio-CNG for organic waste; bulk generator enforcement</li>
                            <li><strong>Tech:</strong> Smart bins; digital tracking; AI segregation in 50% cities</li>
                            <li><strong>Segregation drive:</strong> 60% household compliance via RWA champions + school programs</li>
                            <li><strong>Target:</strong> 70% waste diverted; close collection gap to 85%</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment:</strong> ‚Çπ10,000 Cr‚ÄîMRF network + bio-CNG plants + collection infra</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Tier 3/4 Cities (&gt;100 cities)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Focus:</strong> Basic segregated collection; community composting; informal sector integration</li>
                            <li><strong>Low-tech solutions:</strong> Two-bin system; ward-level MRFs; picker cooperatives</li>
                            <li><strong>Capacity building:</strong> ULB staff training; enforcement of 2016 rules</li>
                            <li><strong>Target:</strong> 50% waste diverted; 100% segregated collection (no single-bin trucks)</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment:</strong> ‚Çπ5,000 Cr‚Äîcollection vehicles + MRFs + training programs</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
<div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="water">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Water Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Rural Water Supply (JJM)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>81.31% rural tap connections</strong> (15.7 Cr households covered under JJM) <a href="resources.html#ref-jjm-dashboard-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Jal Jeevan Mission Dashboard 2025">[104]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ3.6 Lakh Cr invested</strong> since 2019 (60:40 Centre:State funding) <a href="resources.html#ref-dea-economic-survey-water-2026" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Economic Survey 2025-26: Water">[178]</a></li>
                            <li>Remaining <strong>18.69% gap</strong> concentrated in UP, Bihar, WB, Jharkhand <a href="resources.html#ref-jjm-dashboard-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Jal Jeevan Mission Dashboard 2025">[104]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Functionality crisis:</strong> 10-15% taps non-functional within 2 years due to O&M gaps <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                            <li>Source sustainability unclear: <strong>40% JJM schemes</strong> rely on over-exploited aquifers <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Urban Water Supply Crisis</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>70% urban coverage</strong> but only <strong>2-3 hrs/day supply</strong> in 60% cities <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-urban-water-supply-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Urban Water Supply 2023">[111]</a></li>
                            <li>Design: <strong>135 LPCD</strong> (liters per capita per day) vs actual: <strong>70-90 LPCD</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>40-50% Non-Revenue Water (NRW):</strong> Leaks, theft, unmeasured supply drain budgets <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tanker economy:</strong> Bengaluru spends ‚Çπ500 Cr/year on private water trucks <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-tanker-economy-bangalore-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Tanker Economy Bangalore 2024">[146]</a> <a href="resources.html#ref-wateralternatives-mafias-waterscape-2014" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Water Alternatives: Mafias Waterscape 2014">[147]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Metering: &lt;30%</strong> households billed on consumption; rest flat rates (no conservation incentive) <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Groundwater Depletion</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>89% groundwater extraction</strong> for irrigation; 85% free electricity in Punjab, Haryana <a href="resources.html#ref-iwp-rice-wheat-subsidies-groundwater-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IWP Rice-Wheat Subsidies Groundwater 2024">[151]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>1,186 over-exploited blocks</strong> (30% of assessed units) across 17 states <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                            <li>Water table dropping <strong>1-2 meters/year</strong> in Northwest India <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-groundwater-depletion-food-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Nature: Groundwater Depletion Food Security 2022">[152]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No regulation:</strong> Groundwater abstraction license-free in most states; open-access tragedy <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Dying Wisdom 2024">[116]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>25% urban water</strong> from groundwater (unmetered borewells in Bengaluru, Chennai) <a href="resources.html#ref-atree-bengaluru-water-future-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ATREE Bengaluru Water Future 2023">[118]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wastewater Treatment Gap</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>72,368 MLD sewage generated;</strong> only <strong>31,841 MLD treatment capacity</strong> (44% gap) <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-stp-inventory-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB STP Inventory 2024">[107]</a></li>
                            <li>Of 1,640 STPs, <strong>522 (32%) non-functional</strong> due to O&M failures, power costs <a href="resources.html#ref-sandrp-non-functional-stp-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="SANDRP Non-Functional STP 2025">[143]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>70% sewage untreated</strong> flows into rivers, lakes, groundwater‚Äîpollution crisis <a href="resources.html#ref-nmcg-namami-gange-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NMCG Namami Gange 2024">[108]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>&lt;5% treated wastewater reused</strong> (vs Israel 90%, Singapore 40%) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Regulatory gap:</strong> Discharge standards weak; industries discharge untreated effluent into STPs <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Water Reuse Roadblocks 2024">[144]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Utility Financial Distress</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Tariffs recover 30-40% O&M costs</strong> only; capital costs never recovered <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Non-creditworthy utilities:</strong> Cannot borrow for NRW reduction, metering upgrades <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Cross-subsidies fail:</strong> Rich bypass grid via borewells; poor pay high tanker rates <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Political tariff freeze:</strong> No increase in 10-15 years in many cities‚Äîutilities bankrupt <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP operational costs unrecoverable:</strong> Power ‚Çπ20-30 Cr/year; no revenue from reuse <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Water-Energy Nexus</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>7% national electricity</strong> consumed by water pumping (surface + groundwater) <a href="resources.html#ref-iea-water-energy-nexus-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IEA Water-Energy Nexus 2024">[106]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Agricultural pumps:</strong> 21 million energized (85% free/subsidized electricity) <a href="resources.html#ref-iwp-rice-wheat-subsidies-groundwater-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IWP Rice-Wheat Subsidies Groundwater 2024">[151]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Urban water supply: 3-4% city budgets</strong> on electricity for pumping, treatment <a href="resources.html#ref-iea-water-energy-nexus-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IEA Water-Energy Nexus 2024">[106]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wastewater treatment energy-intensive:</strong> ‚Çπ5-8/m¬≥ operational cost; makes reuse unviable <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NRW = wasted energy:</strong> 40-50% treated water lost ‚Üí 40-50% pumping energy wasted <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Milestones</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Urban Metering & NRW Reduction</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>10 cities with 80%+ metering</strong> coverage (smart meters with real-time data) <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NRW reduced to 25%</strong> in pilot cities (from 40-50% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Consumption-based billing:</strong> 50% households shifted from flat to volumetric tariffs <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tariff reforms:</strong> 5 utilities achieving 75%+ O&M cost recovery (creditworthy) <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wastewater Reuse & Circular Economy</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>25% of treated wastewater reused</strong> (vs current 5%)‚Äîindustrial cooling, horticulture, aquifer recharge <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100 STPs with dual-pipe systems</strong> supplying reclaimed water to industries, parks <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Water Reuse Roadblocks 2024">[144]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wastewater pricing:</strong> Reclaimed water sold at ‚Çπ15-20/m¬≥ (vs ‚Çπ30-40 potable water) <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP operational cost recovery:</strong> 20% via reuse revenue + energy cogeneration <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Groundwater Governance</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>5 states with groundwater abstraction licensing</strong> in over-exploited blocks <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>200 recharge structures operational</strong> in urban areas (AMRUT 2.0 co-investment) <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PIB AMRUT 2.0 Framework 2021">[145]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Aquifer mapping completed</strong> in 10 cities‚Äîreal-time water table monitoring <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-artificial-recharge-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Artificial Recharge 2024">[117]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Rainwater harvesting (RWH) compliance:</strong> 50% new buildings in 20 cities (enforcement via building permits) <a href="resources.html#ref-kgwa-rwh-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="KGWA RWH Compliance 2023">[115]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">JJM Functionality Assurance</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>10 states with O&M fund pooling</strong>‚Äîpanchayat contributions matched by state (sustainability) <a href="resources.html#ref-jjm-dashboard-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Jal Jeevan Mission Dashboard 2025">[104]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Source sustainability audits:</strong> 30% JJM schemes assessed for aquifer over-extraction <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>IoT sensor retrofits:</strong> 50,000 village schemes with real-time flow/pressure monitoring <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Non-functionality reduced to &lt;5%</strong> via predictive maintenance systems <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Equity & Slum Access</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>100 informal settlements</strong> with piped connections (vs tanker dependence) <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tanker economy shrinkage:</strong> 30% reduction in private water truck sales (Bengaluru pilot) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-tanker-economy-bangalore-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Tanker Economy Bangalore 2024">[146]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Lifeline tariff structures:</strong> First 50 LPCD free; progressive pricing above (affordability + conservation) <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Gender impact tracking:</strong> Women's water collection time reduced by 50% in JJM villages <a href="resources.html#ref-nfhs-water-sanitation-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NFHS Water Sanitation 2021">[109]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Institutional Capacity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Water regulators established</strong> in 5 states‚Äîtariff approval, service quality standards <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>500 WTP/STP operators trained</strong> in energy-efficient operations, reuse systems <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-stp-inventory-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB STP Inventory 2024">[107]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Utility performance benchmarking:</strong> 50 cities publishing NRW, cost recovery, hours of supply data <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Public disclosure portals:</strong> Real-time water quality, supply hours, tariff data in 20 cities <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üíß Urban Water Cycle: Source to Sink</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">From source abstraction through distribution losses to wastewater‚Äîshowing where efficiency and reuse create leverage</p>
                <div id="water-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: CPCB STP Inventory 2024, NIUA Service Benchmarks, World Bank Water Security. Interactive diagram shows water flow ‚Üí NRW losses ‚Üí wastewater generation ‚Üí reuse potential.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Free/subsidized water expectation:</strong> "Water is a right" ‚Üí tariff hikes politically toxic; utilities chronically underfunded <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater as open access:</strong> No owner ‚Üí everyone extracts; tragedy of commons in 1,186 over-exploited blocks <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Dying Wisdom 2024">[116]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Fragmented urban governance:</strong> Water supply (ULB), sewage (parastatal), groundwater (state)‚Äîno single owner <a href="resources.html#ref-banerjee-urban-self-governance-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Banerjee Urban Self-Governance 2021">[149]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM ownership ambiguity:</strong> Village panchayat "owns" O&M but lacks funds, technical capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tanker mafia vested interests:</strong> Private operators profit from scarcity; resist grid expansion <a href="resources.html#ref-wateralternatives-mafias-waterscape-2014" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Water Alternatives: Mafias Waterscape 2014">[147]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"Water is free natural resource":</strong> Cultural expectation of free/cheap water blocks tariff reforms needed for sustainability <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wastewater stigma:</strong> "Dirty water" narrative prevents acceptance of treated reuse for industry, parks <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Water Reuse Roadblocks 2024">[144]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Metering resistance:</strong> Households see meters as "revenue extraction," not conservation tool <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Monsoon dependence myth:</strong> "Rain will fill tanks" delays conservation action till crisis hits <a href="resources.html#ref-atree-bengaluru-water-future-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ATREE Bengaluru Water Future 2023">[118]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>"Supply-side solution only":</strong> Focus on new dams, interbasin transfers ignores demand management (NRW, reuse) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>WTP operator training gaps:</strong> 60% operators lack certification; energy efficiency, water quality optimization not taught <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-stp-inventory-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB STP Inventory 2024">[107]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NRW reduction expertise scarce:</strong> Leak detection, pressure management require specialized skills absent in most utilities <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Panchayat O&M capacity zero:</strong> JJM schemes handed over but no training on pump repair, water testing <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP operational complexity:</strong> 32% non-functional STPs due to inability to operate tertiary treatment, handle industrial toxics <a href="resources.html#ref-sandrp-non-functional-stp-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="SANDRP Non-Functional STP 2025">[143]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tariff modeling skills absent:</strong> Utilities can't design progressive tariffs (lifeline + conservation pricing) <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Per capita consumption unknown:</strong> &lt;30% metering ‚Üí utilities don't know who uses how much; tariff design impossible <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Aquifer depletion rates unmapped:</strong> Groundwater table data exists but not real-time, not publicly accessible <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NRW measurement inconsistent:</strong> Cities self-report 15-20% but audits show 40-50%‚Äîunderreporting hides problem <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP performance data missing:</strong> 1,640 STPs but only 500 report actual vs design flow; efficiency unknown <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-stp-inventory-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB STP Inventory 2024">[107]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM functionality not tracked:</strong> 81% tap connections but no IoT data on hours of supply, pressure, quality <a href="resources.html#ref-jjm-dashboard-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Jal Jeevan Mission Dashboard 2025">[104]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Groundwater abstraction unregulated:</strong> License-free extraction in most states; no enforcement in over-exploited blocks <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Dying Wisdom 2024">[116]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Treated wastewater discharge standards weak:</strong> No incentive for tertiary treatment; industries discharge into STPs <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Water Reuse Roadblocks 2024">[144]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>RWH mandates unenforced:</strong> 10+ states have laws but no building permit checks; &lt;20% compliance <a href="resources.html#ref-kgwa-rwh-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="KGWA RWH Compliance 2023">[115]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No water regulator in most states:</strong> Tariffs set politically, not by independent regulator; cost recovery impossible <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP O&M standards absent:</strong> No minimum uptime, energy efficiency norms‚Äîoperators run plants inefficiently <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Tariffs cover 30-40% O&M only:</strong> No capital recovery; utilities depend on grants‚Äînon-creditworthy <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NRW reduction ROI unknown:</strong> Fixing 40% leaks saves ‚Çπ100+ Cr/year but utilities can't borrow for pipes <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP power costs unrecoverable:</strong> ‚Çπ20-30 Cr/year electricity but no revenue from reuse‚Äîoperations unsustainable <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Cross-subsidy model broken:</strong> Rich extract groundwater (bypass tariff); poor pay ‚Çπ50-100/tanker <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM capital-heavy, O&M unfunded:</strong> ‚Çπ3.6L Cr capex but no recurring budget for repairs, electricity <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Wastewater reuse market absent:</strong> No buyers at scale for reclaimed water; industries prefer "free" groundwater <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Decentralized tech supply chains thin:</strong> Modular STPs, smart meters available but procurement specs favor large centralized systems <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tanker economy distorts prices:</strong> ‚Çπ500 Cr/year Bengaluru tanker market blocks utility reform incentives <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-tanker-economy-bangalore-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Tanker Economy Bangalore 2024">[146]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Recharge structure market immature:</strong> No standardized designs; each city reinvents wheel at 3x cost <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-artificial-recharge-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Artificial Recharge 2024">[117]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Performance contracts rare:</strong> O&M outsourcing on "cost-plus" not "service-level"‚Äîno efficiency incentive <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Transformation Vision</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-4"><strong>Water systems where every drop is metered, wastewater is a resource, aquifers are recharged, utilities are creditworthy, and access is equitable.</strong></p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What Changes</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>From flat tariffs to volumetric pricing:</strong> 80% households billed on consumption ‚Üí conservation incentive built-in <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From NRW tolerance to zero-loss mindset:</strong> 40% leakage normalized ‚Üí 25% target with leak detection tech, pressure zones <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From wastewater disposal to reuse revenue:</strong> STPs as cost centers ‚Üí revenue generators (industrial sales, aquifer recharge credits) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From open-access to regulated groundwater:</strong> 1,186 over-exploited blocks ‚Üí licensing, real-time monitoring, abstraction caps <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Dying Wisdom 2024">[116]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From grant-dependent to creditworthy utilities:</strong> 30-40% cost recovery ‚Üí 75%+ (tariff reform + NRW reduction) enables borrowing <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From tanker dependence to piped equity:</strong> Slums paying ‚Çπ50-100/tanker ‚Üí lifeline tariff (first 50 LPCD free) <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Breakthrough Moments</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Real-time metering transparency:</strong> Every household sees consumption dashboard ‚Üí 15-20% demand reduction without new supply <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wastewater-as-commodity market:</strong> Industries buy reclaimed water at ‚Çπ15/m¬≥ (vs ‚Çπ40 potable)‚ÄîSTP operational costs recovered <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Aquifer recharge performance contracts:</strong> Recharge structures paid per million liters recharged (verified by piezometers)‚Äîaccountability built-in <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-artificial-recharge-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Artificial Recharge 2024">[117]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Independent water regulators:</strong> Tariff hikes approved based on cost-of-service ‚Üí depoliticized pricing <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM IoT sensor retrofits:</strong> 50,000 village schemes with predictive maintenance ‚Üí non-functionality drops from 15% to &lt;5% <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tanker mafia disruption:</strong> 24/7 piped supply + metering ‚Üí ‚Çπ500 Cr Bengaluru tanker market shrinks 30% <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-tanker-economy-bangalore-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Tanker Economy Bangalore 2024">[146]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. MARKERS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Quantitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>NRW reduction trend:</strong> 40% baseline ‚Üí 25% target (city-by-city leakage audits) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Metering penetration:</strong> % households with smart meters (80% target) <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wastewater reuse rate:</strong> 5% baseline ‚Üí 25% target (MLD reused vs generated) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Utility cost recovery ratio:</strong> Tariff revenue √∑ O&M costs (75%+ = creditworthy) <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater table stabilization:</strong> Piezometer data in over-exploited blocks (1-2m/year depletion ‚Üí flat) <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP operational efficiency:</strong> Actual vs design flow (% capacity utilization) + energy per m¬≥ treated <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-stp-inventory-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB STP Inventory 2024">[107]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM functionality rate:</strong> % taps with &gt;8 hrs/day supply (IoT sensor verified) <a href="resources.html#ref-jjm-dashboard-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Jal Jeevan Mission Dashboard 2025">[104]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tanker economy shrinkage:</strong> Private water truck sales trend (30% reduction target) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-tanker-economy-bangalore-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Tanker Economy Bangalore 2024">[146]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Qualitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Tariff reform political feasibility:</strong> Number of ULBs approving volumetric tariffs without backlash <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wastewater reuse acceptance:</strong> Industries publicly sourcing reclaimed water for cooling, horticulture <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>State regulator establishment:</strong> Number of states with independent water tariff authorities operational <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater abstraction licensing uptake:</strong> States enforcing borewell permits in over-exploited blocks <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Dying Wisdom 2024">[116]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community-led O&M models:</strong> Panchayats successfully pooling funds for JJM scheme sustainability <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Utility performance benchmarking transparency:</strong> Cities publishing real-time NRW, supply hours, tariff data <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Slum piped connection expansion:</strong> Informal settlements demanding grid access vs tanker dependence <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>RWH enforcement via building permits:</strong> Municipalities rejecting approvals for non-compliance <a href="resources.html#ref-kgwa-rwh-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="KGWA RWH Compliance 2023">[115]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7. STRATEGIES -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-600">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Intervention Pathways</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Citywide Smart Metering & NRW Reduction</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 40-50% NRW, &lt;30% metering ‚Üí utilities don't know consumption, can't price water <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Deploy smart meters at 80% households in 10 cities‚Äîreal-time consumption dashboards for residents</li>
                            <li>Leak detection surveys + pressure management zones ‚Üí reduce NRW from 40% to 25%</li>
                            <li>Shift from flat tariffs to volumetric pricing (first 50 LPCD lifeline + progressive tiers)</li>
                            <li>Public disclosure: NRW, hours of supply, tariff benchmarks ‚Üí peer pressure accountability <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Wastewater-to-Resource Value Chains</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 70% sewage untreated; &lt;5% reused ‚Üí pollution + missed revenue <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Dual-pipe systems in 100 STPs‚Äîsupply reclaimed water to industries, parks, aquifer recharge</li>
                            <li>Wastewater pricing: Sell reclaimed water at ‚Çπ15-20/m¬≥ (vs ‚Çπ40 potable)‚Äîrevenue offsets STP operational costs</li>
                            <li>Performance contracts for STP O&M: Pay operators per m¬≥ reused (not flat fee)‚Äîefficiency incentive</li>
                            <li>Energy cogeneration from sludge: Biogas from anaerobic digesters ‚Üí offset electricity costs <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Groundwater Governance & Recharge Infrastructure</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 1,186 over-exploited blocks; abstraction unregulated; open-access tragedy <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Dying Wisdom 2024">[116]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Groundwater abstraction licensing in 5 states (over-exploited blocks)‚Äîborewell permits tied to recharge compliance</li>
                            <li>Real-time aquifer monitoring: 10 cities with piezometer networks ‚Üí public water table dashboards</li>
                            <li>Recharge structure performance contracts: Pay per million liters recharged (sensor-verified)‚Äînot lump-sum capex <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-artificial-recharge-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Artificial Recharge 2024">[117]</a></li>
                            <li>RWH enforcement via building permits: Municipalities reject approvals without functional RWH systems <a href="resources.html#ref-kgwa-rwh-compliance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="KGWA RWH Compliance 2023">[115]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Utility Creditworthiness via Tariff Reform</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 30-40% cost recovery ‚Üí utilities non-creditworthy; can't borrow for NRW reduction <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Establish independent water regulators in 5 states‚Äîtariff approval based on cost-of-service (depoliticized)</li>
                            <li>Tariff design workshops: Progressive pricing (lifeline + conservation tiers)‚Äîaffordability + sustainability</li>
                            <li>Utility performance contracts: Link grants to 75%+ cost recovery achievement‚Äîaccountability built-in</li>
                            <li>Public campaigns: "Pay for water, not for tankers" messaging ‚Üí shift narrative from "free water right" to "service quality" <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. JJM Functionality Assurance via IoT + O&M Pooling</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 10-15% JJM taps non-functional within 2 years; panchayat O&M capacity zero <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>IoT sensor retrofits: 50,000 village schemes with real-time flow, pressure, quality monitoring ‚Üí predictive maintenance</li>
                            <li>O&M fund pooling: Panchayat contributions matched by state (‚Çπ2-5 per household/month)‚Äîsustainability fund</li>
                            <li>Mobile repair teams: District-level technicians trained on pump repair, water testing ‚Üí 24-hour response SLA</li>
                            <li>Source sustainability audits: 30% JJM schemes assessed for aquifer over-extraction; failing schemes get recharge infrastructure <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Slum Water Equity via Piped Expansion</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Informal settlements pay ‚Çπ50-100/tanker; tanker mafia profits from scarcity <a href="resources.html#ref-wateralternatives-mafias-waterscape-2014" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Water Alternatives: Mafias Waterscape 2014">[147]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Piped connections to 100 informal settlements‚Äîprepaid smart meters with lifeline tariff (first 50 LPCD free)</li>
                            <li>Community water committees: Residents co-manage supply, report issues ‚Üí ownership + accountability</li>
                            <li>Tanker economy disruption tracking: Monitor private water truck sales reduction (30% target)</li>
                            <li>Gender impact measurement: Women's water collection time reduction (50% target) in JJM + slum schemes <a href="resources.html#ref-nfhs-water-sanitation-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NFHS Water Sanitation 2021">[109]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Water-Energy Efficiency Integration</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 7% national electricity for water pumping; 40% NRW = wasted energy <a href="resources.html#ref-iea-water-energy-nexus-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IEA Water-Energy Nexus 2024">[106]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>WTP/STP energy audits: Optimize pumping schedules, aeration systems ‚Üí 20-30% energy reduction</li>
                            <li>Solar-powered village schemes: 10,000 JJM pumps solarized ‚Üí eliminate electricity O&M burden</li>
                            <li>Pressure management zones: Reduce pumping pressure in low-demand areas ‚Üí save energy + reduce leaks</li>
                            <li>NRW-energy co-benefit tracking: 40% leak reduction = 40% pumping energy saved ‚Üí quantify climate benefits <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Externalities</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>NRW economic loss: ‚Çπ20,000+ Cr/year</strong> (40-50% of treated water lost to leaks, theft) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Utility revenue gap: ‚Çπ15,000+ Cr/year</strong> (30-40% cost recovery ‚Üí grant dependence) <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP operational deficits: ‚Çπ5,000+ Cr/year</strong> (power costs unrecovered; 32% plants non-functional) <a href="resources.html#ref-indiaspend-sewage-treatment-rehaul-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IndiaSpend Sewage Treatment Rehaul 2024">[142]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tanker economy: ‚Çπ10,000+ Cr/year</strong> (private water trucks; poor pay 10x grid tariff) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-tanker-economy-bangalore-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Tanker Economy Bangalore 2024">[146]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater depletion externality:</strong> Agricultural productivity decline; borewell depths 200m+ (drilling cost ‚Çπ5L+) <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-groundwater-depletion-food-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Nature: Groundwater Depletion Food Security 2022">[152]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Untreated sewage pollution:</strong> River cleaning costs (Namami Gange ‚Çπ20,000 Cr) + health impacts <a href="resources.html#ref-nmcg-namami-gange-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NMCG Namami Gange 2024">[108]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Benefits</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>NRW reduction savings: ‚Çπ15,000 Cr/year</strong> (40% ‚Üí 25% leakage = 15% water + energy saved) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wastewater reuse revenue: ‚Çπ5,000+ Cr/year</strong> (25% reuse at ‚Çπ15/m¬≥ ‚Üí industrial sales, aquifer credits) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Metering-driven conservation: 15-20% demand reduction</strong> ‚Üí defer ‚Çπ50,000+ Cr new source investments <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Utility creditworthiness unlocks: ‚Çπ1 Lakh Cr borrowing</strong> (75% cost recovery ‚Üí municipal bond access) <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater table stabilization:</strong> Avoid ‚Çπ10,000+ Cr/year in deeper borewell drilling, crop loss <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Gender dividend: 2+ hours/day saved</strong> (women's water collection time ‚Üí education, livelihoods) <a href="resources.html#ref-nfhs-water-sanitation-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NFHS Water Sanitation 2021">[109]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>AMRUT 2.0: ‚Çπ2.77 Lakh Cr</strong> allocated (water supply, sewerage, recharge structures) <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PIB AMRUT 2.0 Framework 2021">[145]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM continuation: ‚Çπ1+ Lakh Cr</strong> for O&M sustainability, IoT retrofits, source resilience <a href="resources.html#ref-jjm-dashboard-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Jal Jeevan Mission Dashboard 2025">[104]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NRW reduction ROI: 3-5 years payback</strong> (meter + leak detection capex vs water + energy saved) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP reuse infrastructure: ‚Çπ10,000 Cr</strong> (dual pipes, tertiary treatment) ‚Üí ‚Çπ5,000 Cr/year revenue <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater recharge: ‚Çπ5,000 Cr</strong> (200 structures @ ‚Çπ25 Cr each) ‚Üí stabilize ‚Çπ10K+ Cr/year losses <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-artificial-recharge-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Artificial Recharge 2024">[117]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Climate finance eligibility:</strong> Water efficiency, reuse projects qualify for green bonds, concessional loans <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. INVESTMENTS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üíµ Investments: Capital Allocation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capex (Capital Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Smart metering (10 cities):</strong> ‚Çπ2,000 crore (5M meters @ ‚Çπ4,000 each; installation, backend systems) <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-service-benchmarks-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Service Benchmarks 2024">[114]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NRW reduction infrastructure:</strong> ‚Çπ1,500 crore (leak detection, pressure zones, pipe rehabilitation) <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>STP dual-pipe systems (100 plants):</strong> ‚Çπ3,000 crore (distribution network for reclaimed water) <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater recharge structures (200):</strong> ‚Çπ5,000 crore (percolation tanks, injection wells, managed aquifer recharge) <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-artificial-recharge-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Artificial Recharge 2024">[117]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM IoT sensor retrofits (50,000 schemes):</strong> ‚Çπ500 crore (flow, pressure, quality sensors + data platforms) <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Slum piped connections (100 settlements):</strong> ‚Çπ1,000 crore (last-mile network, prepaid meters) <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Total Capex:</strong> ‚Çπ13,000 crore (~$1.6B) over 3 years</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Opex (Operational Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Meter data management & customer portals:</strong> ‚Çπ100 crore/year (cloud infrastructure, helpdesk, billing systems)</li>
                            <li><strong>NRW monitoring & leak repair teams:</strong> ‚Çπ300 crore/year (10 cities; acoustic sensors, rapid response crews)</li>
                            <li><strong>STP reuse market development:</strong> ‚Çπ150 crore/year (dual-pipe O&M, industrial buyer acquisition, quality assurance)</li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater monitoring network:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore/year (piezometer maintenance, data portals, compliance audits) <a href="resources.html#ref-cgwb-groundwater-resources-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CGWB Groundwater Resources 2024">[15]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>JJM mobile repair teams:</strong> ‚Çπ400 crore/year (district-level technicians, spare parts, water testing kits)</li>
                            <li><strong>Utility capacity building:</strong> ‚Çπ50 crore/year (tariff modeling, regulator training, performance benchmarking)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Opex:</strong> ‚Çπ1,200 crore/year (~$145M/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">Note: Capex recoverable via NRW savings (‚Çπ15K Cr/year), wastewater reuse revenue (‚Çπ5K Cr/year), and tariff reform (75% cost recovery unlocks borrowing). Opex offset by avoided tanker economy costs (‚Çπ10K Cr/year) and deferred new source investments (‚Çπ50K+ Cr).</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Urgency-Ranked Priorities</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Partner-driven interventions addressing hidden dynamics, not adding infrastructure capacity. Ranked by leverage potential and systemic impact.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Utility Tariff Reform & Regulator Establishment</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Establish independent regulators in 5 states; shift tariffs from flat to volumetric with lifeline pricing. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Utility Non-Creditworthiness (30-40% cost recovery)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> Without tariff reform, utilities remain grant-dependent, can't borrow for NRW reduction‚Äîperpetual infrastructure decay cycle. Depoliticized regulator unlocks ‚Çπ1L Cr borrowing capacity. <a href="resources.html#ref-iihs-water-security-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIHS Water Security 2024">[112]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Citywide Smart Metering & NRW Reduction</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Deploy 80% metering in 10 cities; reduce NRW from 40% to 25% via leak detection + pressure zones. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Water Loss Economic Drain (‚Çπ20K Cr/year)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> 40% NRW = 40% pumping energy wasted; metering enables volumetric tariffs (conservation incentive). 3-5 year ROI on meter investment via water + energy savings. <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Water Security 2022">[105]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Wastewater-to-Resource Value Chains</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Dual-pipe systems in 100 STPs; sell reclaimed water at ‚Çπ15/m¬≥ to industries. <strong>Addresses:</strong> STP Operational Deficits (‚Çπ5K Cr/year) + Sewage Pollution</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> 70% sewage untreated ‚Üí river pollution; &lt;5% reuse ‚Üí missed revenue. Reuse market creates STP cost recovery (20% via industrial sales + biogas cogeneration). <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-wastewater-reuse-circularity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="DTE Wastewater Reuse Circularity 2024">[148]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Groundwater Abstraction Licensing & Recharge</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Regulate abstraction in 1,186 over-exploited blocks; deploy 200 recharge structures with performance contracts. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Open-Access Tragedy (water table dropping 1-2m/year)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Unregulated extraction threatens JJM source sustainability (40% schemes rely on over-exploited aquifers). Recharge + licensing stabilize water tables ‚Üí avoid ‚Çπ10K+ Cr/year in deeper borewell costs. <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Dying Wisdom 2024">[116]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: JJM Functionality Assurance via IoT + O&M Pooling</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">IoT sensors in 50,000 schemes; panchayat O&M fund pooling matched by state. <strong>Addresses:</strong> JJM Tap Non-Functionality (10-15% within 2 years)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> ‚Çπ3.6L Cr capex at risk if schemes fail due to O&M gaps. IoT + pooled funds enable predictive maintenance ‚Üí reduce non-functionality from 15% to &lt;5%. <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-water-environment-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE Water Environment 2024">[110]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Slum Piped Connection Expansion</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Piped access to 100 informal settlements; lifeline tariff (first 50 LPCD free) + prepaid meters. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Tanker Economy Inequity (poor pay 10x grid tariff)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Tanker mafia profits ‚Çπ10K Cr/year from scarcity; slums pay ‚Çπ50-100/tanker. Piped expansion shrinks tanker market 30% ‚Üí savings fund grid extension. Gender dividend: 2+ hrs/day saved. <a href="resources.html#ref-wateraid-urban-water-equity-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WaterAid Urban Water Equity 2024">[113]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü¢</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">LOWER: Water-Energy Efficiency Integration</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">WTP/STP energy audits; solarize 10,000 JJM pumps; pressure management zones. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Water-Energy Nexus (7% electricity for pumping; 40% NRW = wasted energy)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why lower:</strong> Co-benefit of NRW reduction (addressed above); solarization saves ‚Çπ1K+ Cr/year electricity O&M but requires JJM functionality first. Energy efficiency secondary to tariff + NRW reforms. <a href="resources.html#ref-iea-water-energy-nexus-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IEA Water-Energy Nexus 2024">[106]</a></p>
                    </div>
        </div>
                </div>
            </div>
<div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="notf">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Neighbourhood Governance Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Ward Committee Infrastructure</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>4,000+ ULBs mandated</strong> ward committees under 74th Amendment <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-74th-amendment-implementation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA 74th Amendment Implementation 2023">[133]</a></li>
                            <li>Functional in <strong>&lt;30% municipalities</strong>‚Äîmost exist on paper only <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Area sabhas mandated</strong> but held in &lt;10% wards (Bengaluru, Kerala exceptions) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No devolved budgets:</strong> Ward committees can't allocate funds independently <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-74th-amendment-implementation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA 74th Amendment Implementation 2023">[133]</a></li>
                            <li>Meetings: <strong>Quarterly at best</strong>, annual reports rare, no citizen participation <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Participatory Budgeting Pilots</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>&lt;10 cities</strong> with participatory budgeting (PB) pilots (Pune, Shimoga, Kerala) <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>&lt;5% municipal budget</strong> allocated through PB where it exists <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li>Ward funds: <strong>2-5% of ULB budget</strong>‚Äîtoo small for infrastructure needs <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Elite capture:</strong> Middle-class RWA demands dominate vs slum/informal needs <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li>Participation rates: <strong>&lt;2% residents</strong> attend ward meetings where held <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">RWA & Civic Association Landscape</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>100,000+ RWAs registered</strong> nationwide, governance fragmented <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No legal framework:</strong> RWAs have power without accountability mechanisms <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Class segregation:</strong> Gated communities vs slums‚Äîunequal civic voice <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li>Street-level issues: <strong>Potholes, lighting, parking</strong> unsolved for months/years <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NIMBYism prevalent:</strong> Bus stops, shelters, hawker zones blocked by resident groups <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Service Delivery Gaps</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Grievance redressal: 15-30 day average</strong> for basic ward issues <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Citizen helplines:</strong> 60% complaints unresolved or closed without action <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No hyperlocal data:</strong> Ward-level service quality unmeasured (waste collection, lighting, water) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li>Service standards: <strong>City-wide benchmarks ignore</strong> intra-city disparities <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Co-production absent:</strong> Residents = service recipients, not partners in delivery <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Community Commons & Public Spaces</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Parks: 0.5-2 sqm/capita</strong> vs WHO standard 9 sqm/capita <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>70% parks</strong> lack maintenance‚Äîcommunity stewardship rare <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Footpaths: 20-30%</strong> occupied by encroachments, no street-level enforcement <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li>Community centers: <strong>Exist but underutilized</strong>‚Äîno neighborhood programming <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Commons as parking:</strong> Playgrounds converted to vehicle storage <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Digital Infrastructure for Civic Engagement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>311 systems:</strong> Deployed in 50+ cities, but 60% complaints unresolved <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ward dashboards absent:</strong> No real-time service data at neighbourhood level <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bangalore One model:</strong> Citizen service centers in 7-8 cities, not scaled <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li>Participation platforms: <strong>Top-down surveys</strong> vs bottom-up deliberation <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Digital divide:</strong> 40% residents lack smartphone access for civic apps <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capacity & Knowledge Gaps</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward committee training: Absent</strong> in 90% municipalities <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-74th-amendment-implementation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA 74th Amendment Implementation 2023">[133]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No facilitation cadre:</strong> ULBs lack staff to run participatory processes <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Conflict resolution skills missing:</strong> Ward-level disputes escalate needlessly <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li>Budget literacy: <strong>&lt;5% residents</strong> understand municipal finance <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Civic curriculum absent:</strong> Schools don't teach local governance or participation <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Cross-Sector Neighbourhood Integration</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Waste segregation:</strong> 15-20% compliance‚Äîrequires street-level nudging <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Park maintenance:</strong> Community adoption in &lt;10% parks <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Rainwater harvesting:</strong> Mandatory but 60% non-compliance‚Äîno neighborhood enforcement <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li>Energy audits: <strong>Building-level mandates</strong> ignored‚Äîneighborhood collective action missing <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NMT infrastructure:</strong> Footpaths, cycle tracks planned centrally‚Äîno resident input <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Participatory Governance Milestones</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Ward Committee Activation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>500 wards</strong> with functional committees (quarterly meetings, public reports) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Area sabhas held annually</strong> in 250 wards‚Äîminimum 100 resident participation <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ward fund discretion: 10%</strong> of ULB budget allocated (from 2-5% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Digital ward dashboards live</strong> in 100 wards (real-time service data) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Participatory Budgeting Scale</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>20 cities</strong> with participatory budgeting operational (from &lt;10 baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>15% municipal budget</strong> allocated through PB (from &lt;5% baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>25% resident participation</strong> in PB processes (online + offline) <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Gender parity mandated:</strong> 50% PB votes/delegates from women residents <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Service Co-Production</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>500 parks</strong> under community stewardship agreements <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100 wards</strong> with resident-led waste segregation monitoring <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50% grievance resolution</strong> through ward-level committees (decentralized) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>200 neighborhood compacts</strong> (residents + ULB agree on service standards) <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capacity Building</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>5,000 ward committee members trained</strong> (budget literacy, facilitation, conflict resolution) <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-74th-amendment-implementation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA 74th Amendment Implementation 2023">[133]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>500 ULB facilitators certified</strong> in participatory governance methods <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Civic curriculum piloted</strong> in 100 schools (local governance modules) <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>10,000 residents</strong> trained in hyperlocal data interpretation (service dashboards) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Equity & Inclusion</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>RWA framework legislation</strong> in 5 states (accountability, inclusion, transparency) <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50% slum/informal settlement</strong> representation in ward committees <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Zero tolerance NIMBYism policy:</strong> Public infrastructure projects protected from elite veto <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Multi-lingual engagement:</strong> Ward materials in 3+ local languages <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Grievance Redressal Transformation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>7-day average resolution</strong> for street-level issues (from 15-30 day baseline) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>75% complaint closure rate</strong> (from 40% baseline)‚Äîaction-verified <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Public ward scorecards</strong> in 200 wards (service delivery vs resident satisfaction) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>SMS/WhatsApp integration:</strong> Grievance updates sent to residents in real-time <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üèòÔ∏è Civic Participation Flow: Demand to Delivery</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">From citizen issues through governance mechanisms to service delivery‚Äîhighlighting where participation breaks down</p>
                <div id="neighbourhoods-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022, PRIA Participatory Budgeting Studies. Interactive diagram shows citizen demands ‚Üí governance structures ‚Üí service outcomes.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether participatory governance succeeds or fails. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Residents as service recipients:</strong> "Government should fix it" mindset‚Äînot co-producers <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>RWA power without accountability:</strong> Elite groups wield influence but face no transparency rules <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Invisible urban poor:</strong> Slum residents excluded from ward-level decisions <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ward councillor gatekeeping:</strong> Committees controlled by elected rep, not residents <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"It's the government's job":</strong> Civic apathy justified as proper division of labor <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NIMBYism normalized:</strong> "Not in my backyard" seen as legitimate concern vs public good <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Elite capture accepted:</strong> "Educated people should decide" excludes working-class voice <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Participation as complaint:</strong> Civic engagement = lodge complaint, not co-create solutions <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward committee training absent:</strong> Members don't know their mandate or powers <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-74th-amendment-implementation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA 74th Amendment Implementation 2023">[133]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Facilitator shortage:</strong> ULBs lack staff skilled in participatory methods <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Conflict resolution gaps:</strong> Ward disputes escalate‚Äîno mediation capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Budget literacy near zero:</strong> Residents can't engage without understanding municipal finance <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Hyperlocal need assessment missing:</strong> City-wide data hides ward-level disparities <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Participation quality unmeasured:</strong> Area sabha attendance tracked, not deliberation depth <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No ward-level dashboards:</strong> Real-time service data unavailable to residents <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grievance data siloed:</strong> ULBs don't publish resolution rates, issue types by ward <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>74th Amendment weak implementation:</strong> Ward committees exist on paper, no teeth <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-74th-amendment-implementation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA 74th Amendment Implementation 2023">[133]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ward fund discretion limited:</strong> 2-5% budget too small to matter <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No RWA accountability framework:</strong> Resident groups wield power without legal oversight <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Area sabha mandate ignored:</strong> No penalties for ULBs that skip community meetings <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward funds 2-5% of ULB budget:</strong> Too small for real infrastructure investment <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>No participatory budgeting at scale:</strong> &lt;10 cities allocate &lt;5% budget this way <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community co-funding rare:</strong> Residents willing to pay for local upgrades but no mechanism <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Facilitation costs unfunded:</strong> Participatory processes require staff‚Äînot budgeted <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Local service providers bypassed:</strong> Central procurement ignores neighborhood vendors <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community contracts rare:</strong> Resident groups can't bid for park maintenance, waste collection <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Performance bonds absent:</strong> Contractors deliver shoddy work‚Äîno resident recourse <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tech platforms centralized:</strong> Civic apps built top-down, not co-designed with residents <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Transformation Vision</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-4"><strong>Neighbourhoods where governance is participatory, services are co-produced, commons are stewarded collectively, and decision-making power is decentralized to the street level.</strong></p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What Changes</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>From consultative to co-decision:</strong> Ward committees control 15-20% ULB budget‚Äîreal power <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From recipient to co-producer:</strong> Residents maintain parks, monitor waste, enforce hyperlocal rules <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From city-wide to hyperlocal:</strong> Service standards set by ward, not centrally‚Äîhonor context <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From elite capture to inclusive:</strong> 50% slum/informal representation in ward committees <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From complaint to problem-solving:</strong> Civic engagement = deliberation + action, not just grievance <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Breakthrough Moments</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward dashboards go live:</strong> Residents see real-time waste collection, lighting status‚Äîdemand accountability <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Participatory budgeting at 15%:</strong> Residents vote on ‚Çπ500+ Cr infrastructure‚Äîno centralized diktat <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community service contracts:</strong> RWAs bid for park maintenance, waste monitoring‚Äîearn revenue + ownership <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NIMBYism challenged:</strong> RWA legal framework requires transparency, inclusion‚Äîelite veto power checked <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Civic curriculum scales:</strong> 10,000+ students learn local governance‚Äînext generation of active citizens <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. MARKERS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Quantitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward committee meetings per year:</strong> Quarterly minimum (4+) vs baseline &lt;2 <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Area sabha participation rate:</strong> 100+ residents attending vs baseline 10-20 <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>% ULB budget through PB:</strong> 15% target vs baseline &lt;5% <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ward fund allocation:</strong> 10% ULB budget vs baseline 2-5% <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grievance resolution time:</strong> 7-day average vs baseline 15-30 days <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Complaint closure rate:</strong> 75% action-verified vs baseline 40% <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community stewardship agreements:</strong> 500 parks vs baseline &lt;50 <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ward dashboard deployment:</strong> 100 wards with real-time service data <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Qualitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward committee public reports:</strong> Quarterly activity + budget updates published online <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Inclusive participation:</strong> 50% slum/informal settlement residents in committees <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Service co-production examples:</strong> Resident groups monitoring waste segregation, maintaining parks <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>RWA accountability framework:</strong> 5 states legislate transparency, inclusion mandates <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Media coverage shift:</strong> From "corruption complaint" to "ward-level innovation" stories</li>
                            <li><strong>Budget literacy events:</strong> Ward-level sessions on municipal finance attended by 100+ residents <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Civic curriculum adoption:</strong> 100 schools teaching local governance modules <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>NIMBYism challenged:</strong> Public infrastructure projects proceed despite elite opposition <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7. STRATEGIES -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-600">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Intervention Pathways</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ward Committee Activation Program</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Functional in &lt;30% municipalities‚Äîexist on paper only <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Train 5,000 ward committee members: budget literacy, facilitation, conflict resolution</li>
                            <li>Deploy 500 ULB facilitators certified in participatory governance methods</li>
                            <li>Mandate quarterly meetings with public reports published online‚Äîtransparency accountability</li>
                            <li>Increase ward fund discretion from 2-5% to 10% of ULB budget‚Äîreal decision-making power</li>
                            <li>Link ward performance scorecards to fund allocation‚Äîoutcome-based incentives</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Participatory Budgeting Scale-Up</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> &lt;10 cities with PB, &lt;5% budget allocated <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Launch PB in 20 cities (10 new + 10 scale-ups)‚Äîallocate 15% municipal budget through resident vote</li>
                            <li>Build digital + offline platforms: online voting + ward-level assemblies for inclusive participation</li>
                            <li>Mandate 50% gender parity in PB delegates‚Äîprevent elite male capture</li>
                            <li>Create peer learning network‚Äîcities share methodologies, avoid reinventing the wheel</li>
                            <li>Independent evaluation: Measure participation depth, not just attendance numbers</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Ward-Level Service Dashboards</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> No hyperlocal data‚Äîresidents can't demand accountability <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Deploy real-time dashboards in 100 wards‚Äîwaste collection, lighting, water supply status</li>
                            <li>Public API for researchers, media, RWAs‚Äîdemocratize access to service data</li>
                            <li>SMS/WhatsApp alerts: Notify residents when complaints resolved or service scheduled</li>
                            <li>Link to grievance redressal: Publish ward-level resolution rates, issue types publicly</li>
                            <li>Train 10,000 residents in data interpretation‚Äîconvert information into advocacy</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Community Service Co-Production</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Residents = service recipients, not partners <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>500 park stewardship agreements‚ÄîRWAs/community groups maintain, ULB provides tools</li>
                            <li>100 ward waste segregation monitoring programs‚Äîresidents audit compliance, report violations</li>
                            <li>200 neighborhood compacts‚Äîresidents + ULB agree on service standards, penalties for non-delivery</li>
                            <li>Community procurement: Allow RWAs to bid for local service contracts (park cleaning, waste collection)</li>
                            <li>Revenue share model: Communities earn 30% of cost savings from co-produced services</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. RWA Accountability Framework</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 100,000+ RWAs wield power without legal oversight <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Model legislation in 5 states: RWA registration requires transparency (budgets, minutes), inclusion (tenant voting rights)</li>
                            <li>Anti-NIMBYism clause: Public infrastructure projects protected from elite veto‚Äîhearings yes, blocking no</li>
                            <li>Slum area recognition: Informal settlement RWAs get equal legal standing as gated community RWAs</li>
                            <li>Conflict of interest rules: RWA office-bearers can't simultaneously be ward committee members</li>
                            <li>Audit mechanisms: Resident-led financial audits mandatory for RWAs controlling &gt;‚Çπ10 lakh/year</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Hyperlocal Civic Education</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Residents don't know ward committees exist or their rights <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Civic curriculum in 100 schools: Local governance modules (ward committees, PB, how municipal budgets work)</li>
                            <li>Ward-level budget literacy sessions: Train 10,000 residents to read municipal budgets, ask informed questions</li>
                            <li>Media partnerships: Local journalism covering ward-level governance, not just city hall drama</li>
                            <li>Multi-lingual materials: Ward committee guides in 3+ local languages‚Äîreach migrant workers, linguistic minorities</li>
                            <li>Youth civic fellows: 500 college students placed in wards for 6-month participatory governance projects</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Grievance Redressal Transformation</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 15-30 day resolution, 60% unresolved <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Ward-level complaint committees: 50% grievances resolved locally within 7 days vs escalating to ULB</li>
                            <li>SMS/WhatsApp integration: Real-time updates to residents on complaint status‚Äîtransparency builds trust</li>
                            <li>Public ward scorecards: Publish resolution rates, issue types by ward‚Äîpeer pressure accountability</li>
                            <li>Resident verification: Complaints marked "resolved" only after resident confirms action taken</li>
                            <li>Escalation protocol: Auto-escalate to councillor/commissioner if ward committee fails to resolve in 14 days</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Inefficiencies</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Service delivery inefficiency:</strong> Street-level issues (potholes, lighting) cost 2-3x more to fix due to delay <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Grievance redressal waste:</strong> ‚Çπ500+ Cr/year on call centers, helplines with 60% unresolved complaints <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Park maintenance cost:</strong> ‚Çπ100-200 per sqm/year when outsourced vs ‚Çπ30-50 with community stewardship <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Elite capture externality:</strong> NIMBY veto blocks bus stops, public housing‚Äîreduces urban accessibility <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Civic apathy cost:</strong> Low segregation compliance, no community enforcement drives waste processing deficit <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Benefits</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ2,000 Cr cost savings:</strong> Community co-production reduces park maintenance, waste monitoring, grievance costs by 40% <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Property value increase:</strong> 10-15% higher in neighborhoods with functional ward committees <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-ease-living-index-2025" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA Ease of Living Index 2025">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Waste segregation dividend:</strong> 60% compliance unlocks ‚Çπ1,000+ Cr in recyclable material value <a href="resources.html#ref-cpcb-swm-consolidated-2020-21" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPCB SWM Consolidated 2020-21">[85]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Civic engagement multiplier:</strong> PB cities see 20-30% higher citizen satisfaction, willing to pay higher property taxes <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Social capital ROI:</strong> Every ‚Çπ1 invested in facilitation/training yields ‚Çπ5 in volunteer labor + community contributions <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward fund multiplication:</strong> Increase from 2-5% to 10% = ‚Çπ3,000+ Cr/year hyperlocal investment <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Participatory budgeting scale:</strong> 15% allocation in 20 cities = ‚Çπ5,000+ Cr/year resident-driven priorities <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community co-funding potential:</strong> Middle-class willingness to pay for local upgrades taps ‚Çπ500+ Cr/year <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Service contract revenue:</strong> RWA/community groups bidding for maintenance contracts creates ‚Çπ200+ Cr local economy <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tech platform market:</strong> Ward dashboards, PB software, civic apps create ‚Çπ100+ Cr govtech opportunity <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. INVESTMENTS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üíµ Investments: Capital Allocation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capex (Capital Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward dashboard infrastructure:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore (100 wards @ ‚Çπ2 crore: sensors, software, data integration) <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Participatory budgeting platforms:</strong> ‚Çπ50 crore (20 cities; digital voting, offline assembly kits, training)</li>
                            <li><strong>Community center upgrades:</strong> ‚Çπ150 crore (500 centers @ ‚Çπ30 lakh: furniture, tech, accessibility improvements)</li>
                            <li><strong>Civic education materials:</strong> ‚Çπ20 crore (curriculum development, teacher training, multi-lingual guides)</li>
                            <li><strong>Grievance system upgrades:</strong> ‚Çπ30 crore (ward-level complaint tracking, SMS/WhatsApp integration, resident verification)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Capex:</strong> ‚Çπ450 crore (~$55M) over 3 years</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Opex (Operational Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ward committee training:</strong> ‚Çπ25 crore/year (5,000 members @ ‚Çπ50,000/member: workshops, materials, fellowships)</li>
                            <li><strong>ULB facilitator salaries:</strong> ‚Çπ75 crore/year (500 facilitators @ ‚Çπ15 lakh/year salary + benefits)</li>
                            <li><strong>Participatory budgeting operations:</strong> ‚Çπ40 crore/year (20 cities @ ‚Çπ2 crore: facilitation, assemblies, verification)</li>
                            <li><strong>Ward dashboard maintenance:</strong> ‚Çπ20 crore/year (data hosting, sensor calibration, software updates)</li>
                            <li><strong>Community stewardship support:</strong> ‚Çπ30 crore/year (500 parks @ ‚Çπ6 lakh/park: tools, materials, RWA coordination)</li>
                            <li><strong>Civic education programs:</strong> ‚Çπ10 crore/year (teacher training, student projects, youth civic fellows)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Opex:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore/year (~$25M/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">Note: Opex offset by ‚Çπ2,000+ Cr cost savings from community co-production (park maintenance, waste monitoring, grievance resolution). Capex recoverable via increased property tax revenue (10-15% value increase in functional wards).</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Urgency-Ranked Priorities</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Partner-driven interventions addressing hidden dynamics in neighbourhood governance. Ranked by leverage potential.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Ward Dashboard Deployment</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Deploy real-time service dashboards in 100 wards‚Äîwaste, lighting, water visible to residents. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Hyperlocal Data Void</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> No accountability without visibility‚Äîdashboards unlock resident advocacy + ward-level enforcement within 6 months <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Participatory Budgeting Scale-Up</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Launch PB in 20 cities with 15% budget allocation‚Äîreal resident decision-making power. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Ward Fund Powerlessness</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> &lt;5% budget in &lt;10 cities = symbolic participation‚Äîscaling to 15% creates material impact + resident ownership <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Ward Committee Activation</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Train 5,000 members, deploy 500 facilitators‚Äîmake committees functional, not symbolic. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Paper Tiger Ward Committees</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> 74th Amendment infrastructure exists‚Äîactivation training + facilitators + fund devolution converts paper to power <a href="resources.html#ref-mohua-74th-amendment-implementation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoHUA 74th Amendment Implementation 2023">[133]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: RWA Accountability Framework</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Model legislation in 5 states: RWA transparency, inclusion, anti-NIMBY rules. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Elite Capture Unchecked</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> 100,000+ RWAs wield power without accountability‚Äîframework checks elite veto, protects public infrastructure <a href="resources.html#ref-cprglobal-urban-governance-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CPR Global Urban Governance 2023">[136]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Community Service Co-Production</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">500 park stewardship agreements, 100 waste monitoring programs‚Äîresidents as partners. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Resident as Recipient</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Requires cultural shift from consumer to co-producer‚Äîworks best after dashboard visibility + PB legitimacy established <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Grievance Redressal Transformation</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Ward-level complaint committees, SMS updates, resident verification‚Äîfix resolution gap. <strong>Addresses:</strong> 60% Unresolved Complaints</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Low-hanging fruit‚Äîdecentralizing to ward level cuts 15-30 day resolution to 7 days, builds resident trust <a href="resources.html#ref-janaagraha-city-systems-report-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Janaagraha City Systems Report 2022">[134]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü¢</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">FOUNDATIONAL: Hyperlocal Civic Education</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Civic curriculum in 100 schools, budget literacy for 10,000 residents‚Äîbuild participation capacity. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Budget Literacy Zero</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why foundational:</strong> Long-term investment‚Äîstudents become active citizens in 5-10 years; adult training enables immediate PB participation <a href="resources.html#ref-pria-participatory-budgeting-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PRIA Participatory Budgeting India 2024">[135]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="food">
            <!-- Baseline -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Baseline (Current Status)</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Food Loss & Waste</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>78.2 million tonnes</strong> food wasted annually <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[144]</a></li>
                            <li>Value of loss: <strong>‚Çπ92,000 crore/year</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[144]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>40% of fruits/vegetables</strong> lost before reaching markets <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[145]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>64.1 MT CO‚ÇÇe</strong> emissions from post-harvest losses <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[144]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Cold Chain Gap</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li>Only <strong>500 of 125,000</strong> needed rural packhouses exist <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[145]</a></li>
                            <li>Cold storage <strong>70% for potatoes only</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[145]</a></li>
                            <li>Reefer trucks: <strong>9,000 vs 62,000 needed</strong> <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[145]</a></li>
                            <li>Horticulture gets <strong>&lt;4% of cold storage</strong> capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[145]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Production & Nutrition</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>MSP covers only 23 crops</strong> ‚Äî biased toward rice/wheat <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-tanker-economy-bangalore-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[146]</a></li>
                            <li>Rice/wheat: <strong>95% of MSP procurement</strong> value <a href="resources.html#ref-nccd-cold-chain-assessment-2023" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[153]</a></li>
                            <li>Millet farmers get <strong>33-42%</strong> of rice/wheat farmer income <a href="resources.html#ref-cacp-msp-reports-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[154]</a></li>
                            <li>Crop diversification increases income <strong>~13%</strong> but lacks MSP support <a href="resources.html#ref-iwp-rice-wheat-subsidies-groundwater-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[155]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Soil & Water Degradation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ2.54 lakh crore/year</strong> lost to land degradation (~2% GDP) <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-millet-farming-hidden-side-2025" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[156]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>97.9 Mha</strong> (30% of land) degraded; 74M tonnes nutrients lost/year <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-millet-farming-hidden-side-2025" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[156]</a></li>
                            <li>Punjab/Haryana: <strong>109 km¬≥/year</strong> aquifer depletion <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[157]</a></li>
                            <li>Groundwater extraction <strong>&gt;100%</strong> in Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[157]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Fertilizer Imbalance</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li>NPK ratio: <strong>10.9:4.4:1</strong> (actual) vs <strong>4:2:1</strong> (ideal) <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-land-degradation-economics-2018" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[158]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ1.68 lakh crore</strong> fertilizer subsidy (FY25-26) <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-land-degradation-economics-2018" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[158]</a></li>
                            <li>Urea over-subsidized ‚Üí nitrogen excess ‚Üí soil degradation</li>
                            <li>Groundwater nitrate contamination in north/west India <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-land-degradation-economics-2018" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[158]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Food Loss Cascade -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
                    <span style="font-size: 1.25rem;">üåæ</span> The Food Loss Cascade
                    <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: normal; color: #6b7280; margin-left: auto;">67 MT (‚Çπ92,000 Cr) lost before it reaches consumers</span>
                </h3>
                <p style="color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;">16% of food production never reaches consumers. No cold chain, no packhouses, no grading infrastructure. Farmers bear 90% of loss burden while getting 25% of retail price.</p>

                <!-- Interactive Sankey Diagram -->
                <div id="food-sankey" style="height: 600px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>

                <!-- Key Statistics Grid -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Cold Chain Catastrophe</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li>India: <strong>4%</strong> food in cold chain vs <strong>50%</strong> global average <a href="resources.html#ref-wateralternatives-mafias-waterscape-2014" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[147]</a></li>
                            <li>Warehousing shortfall: <strong>15M MT</strong> gap (vs 60M MT need) <a href="resources.html#ref-wateralternatives-mafias-waterscape-2014" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[147]</a></li>
                            <li>Transport loss: 3.2% due to no refrigeration</li>
                            <li>FPOs lack capital for packhouse + cold storage</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Middlemen Value Capture</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li>Farmer gets <strong>25%</strong> of retail price</li>
                            <li>Middlemen take <strong>65%</strong> (5-7 intermediaries)</li>
                            <li>No direct farm-to-retail linkages at scale</li>
                            <li>MSP system benefits 6% of farmers (Punjab/Haryana)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Infrastructure Missing</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Zero</strong> packhouses at farm-gate for most FPOs</li>
                            <li>No grading/sorting ‚Üí 15-20% price loss</li>
                            <li>FPO capital access: <strong>&lt;10%</strong> get institutional credit</li>
                            <li>‚Çπ92K Cr annual loss = 2x farmer welfare spending</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #6b7280; margin-top: 1rem;">Sources: ICAR Post-Harvest Loss Study, NABARD FPO Survey, NCCD Infrastructure Gap Report</p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Shift</h3>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Nutrition & Sustainability System</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li>Minimize loss across value chain</li>
                            <li>Dietary diversity and millet revival</li>
                            <li>Rural cold chain infrastructure</li>
                            <li>Farmer-to-fork efficiency</li>
                            <li>Water-smart crop diversification</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Targets</h3>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Year 3 Milestones</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li>50% reduction in food loss (target crops)</li>
                            <li>1,000 rural packhouses commissioned</li>
                            <li>5 states with millet MSP expansion</li>
                            <li>10 FPOs with viable cold chain access</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #6b7280; margin-top: 0.5rem;">Source: Program targets based on <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024">[144,145,146]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Food Systems Gap -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.05) 0%, transparent 100%);">
                <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
                    <span style="font-size: 1.25rem;">üåæ</span> Hidden Dynamics: The Subsidy-Degradation Trap
                    <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: normal; color: #6b7280; margin-left: auto;">Why market incentives destroy long-term agricultural assets</span>
                </h3>
                <p style="color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;">MSP + fertilizer subsidies create a rational trap: farmers maximize short-term income by growing rice/wheat while destroying soil, water, and nutrition.</p>

                <!-- Evidence Cards -->
                <div class="focus-grid" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-150">
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">‚Çπ2.54L Cr</div>
                        <div class="evidence-context">Annual economic loss from land degradation (~2% of GDP) <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-millet-farming-hidden-side-2025" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[156]</a></div>
                        <div class="evidence-implication"><strong>Dynamic:</strong> MSP-driven monoculture depletes soil while subsidies mask true costs</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-150">
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">109 km¬≥/yr</div>
                        <div class="evidence-context">Aquifer depletion in Punjab/Haryana ‚Äî world's 2nd most overexploited <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></div>
                        <div class="evidence-implication"><strong>Dynamic:</strong> Rice-wheat accounts for 95% crop area; 50% of groundwater decline from MSP rice</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-150">
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">10.9:4.4:1</div>
                        <div class="evidence-context">Actual NPK ratio vs 4:2:1 ideal ‚Äî urea subsidies distort application <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-land-degradation-economics-2018" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[158]</a></div>
                        <div class="evidence-implication"><strong>Dynamic:</strong> ‚Çπ1.19L Cr urea subsidy ‚Üí nitrogen excess ‚Üí soil & water contamination</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-150">
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">33-42%</div>
                        <div class="evidence-context">Millet farmer income vs rice/wheat farmers <a href="resources.html#ref-cacp-msp-reports-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[154]</a></div>
                        <div class="evidence-implication"><strong>Dynamic:</strong> Without equivalent MSP, diversification is economically irrational</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Key Statistics Grid -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">MSP Lock-In</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ2.5 lakh crore</strong> annual MSP procurement ‚Äî 95%+ rice/wheat <a href="resources.html#ref-nccd-cold-chain-assessment-2023" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[153]</a></li>
                            <li>Punjab spends <strong>‚Çπ39,000/ha</strong> on fertilizer + power subsidies for rice <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></li>
                            <li>30% over-production of water-intensive crops due to MSP <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Asset Destruction</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>97.9 Mha</strong> (30% of land) degraded <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-millet-farming-hidden-side-2025" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[156]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>74 million tonnes</strong> nutrients lost to erosion annually <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-millet-farming-hidden-side-2025" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[156]</a></li>
                            <li>By 2050: <strong>$1.73 trillion</strong> projected loss from degradation + climate <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-millet-farming-hidden-side-2025" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[156]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Groundwater Crisis</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li>Borewells now <strong>80-200 feet</strong> (vs 30 feet a decade ago) <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>92-96%</strong> of groundwater withdrawal for irrigation <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></li>
                            <li>Extraction >100% of recharge in Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">FPO Evidence (What Works)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>22% higher</strong> price realization for FPO members <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-groundwater-depletion-food-security-2022" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[159]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>39% higher</strong> annual agricultural income <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-groundwater-depletion-food-security-2022" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[159]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>49% lower</strong> poverty incidence among FPO farmers <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-groundwater-depletion-food-security-2022" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[159]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Strategies -->
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Strategies</h3>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Addressing Hidden Dynamics</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>MSP Lock-In:</strong> Expand MSP to millets with equivalent procurement; Haryana model (‚Çπ17,500/ha for crop switch) <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Soil Degradation:</strong> Balanced fertilization incentives; recalibrate urea vs P&K subsidies <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-land-degradation-economics-2018" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[158]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Groundwater:</strong> Synchronize paddy sowing with monsoon (Punjab 2009 Act model); metered electricity <a href="resources.html#ref-springer-crop-diversification-income-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Cold Chain:</strong> Multi-commodity cold stores; break potato monopoly; horticulture-specific subsidies</li>
                            <li><strong>Last-Mile:</strong> FPO strengthening ‚Äî 22% higher price realization proven <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-groundwater-depletion-food-security-2022" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[159]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>PDS Path:</strong> Millet inclusion (Odisha Millet Mission model); nutrition-based entitlements</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Investment & Impact</h3>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Required</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ1.7 lakh crore</strong> for 35MT additional cold chain capacity <a href="resources.html#ref-pib-amrut-2-framework-2021" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[145]</a></li>
                            <li>125,000 packhouses needed across rural India</li>
                            <li>Fertilizer subsidy rebalancing (‚Çπ1.68L Cr envelope exists)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Economic Returns</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ92,000 Cr/year</strong> food loss avoided <a href="resources.html#ref-dte-water-reuse-roadblocks-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[144]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ2.54L Cr/year</strong> soil degradation avoided <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-millet-farming-hidden-side-2025" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[156]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>39% higher income</strong> for FPO farmers <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-groundwater-depletion-food-security-2022" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[159]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>13% income increase</strong> from crop diversification <a href="resources.html#ref-iwp-rice-wheat-subsidies-groundwater-2024" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">[155]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- BIODIVERSITY SECTOR -->

<div class="sector-content-panel hidden" id="biodiversity">
            <!-- 1. BASELINE -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-gray-400">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä Baseline: Current Biodiversity Status</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Forest Cover & Quality Crisis</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>24.62% total green cover</strong> (forest 21.76% + tree cover 2.91%) = 809,537 sq km <a href="resources.html#ref-fsi-forest-report-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="FSI India State of Forest Report 2023">[162]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>24,651 sq km dense forest lost</strong> (2003-2023)‚Äîreplaced by plantations, not natural regeneration <a href="resources.html#ref-fsi-forest-report-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="FSI India State of Forest Report 2023">[162]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>44% of tree cover loss</strong> from forest fires since 2001; climate change increasing fire frequency <a href="resources.html#ref-gfw-india-forest-loss-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Global Forest Watch 2024">[163]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>CFR recognition: only 5%</strong> of eligible forest land under Forest Rights Act (2006) <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></li>
                            <li>Monoculture plantations counted as "forest"‚Äîbiodiversity value near zero <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Protected Areas & Wildlife</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>870+ protected areas</strong> (national parks, sanctuaries) covering ~5% of geographic area <a href="resources.html#ref-wii-protected-areas-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WII Protected Areas 2023">[158]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>India ranks 176/180</strong> on Yale Nature Conservation Index‚Äîprotection exists but management poor <a href="resources.html#ref-yale-epi-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Yale EPI 2024">[164]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>70%+ tiger reserves lack functional corridors</strong>‚Äîfragmented by roads, railways, canals <a href="resources.html#ref-wti-wildlife-corridors-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WTI Wildlife Corridors 2022">[159]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>2,727 human deaths</strong> from elephant attacks (2019-2024)‚Äîhabitat fragmentation driving conflict <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-human-wildlife-conflict-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC HWC Report 2024">[167]</a></li>
                            <li>Invasive <strong>Lantana covers 40%</strong> of tiger reserve area‚Äîoutcompeting native species <a href="resources.html#ref-joshi-lantana-invasion-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Joshi Lantana Invasion 2020">[166]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wetlands & Water Ecosystems</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>757,060 wetlands</strong> mapped, covering 4.63% of country (152,600 sq km) <a href="resources.html#ref-sac-wetland-atlas-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="SAC Wetland Atlas 2023">[163]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50%+ wetlands degraded</strong>‚Äîfilled for real estate, polluted by sewage/industrial effluents <a href="resources.html#ref-wetlands-international-india-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Wetlands International 2022">[164]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Bengaluru lost 79% water bodies</strong> (1973-2017)‚Äîsimilar patterns in most cities <a href="resources.html#ref-iisc-bengaluru-lakes-2018" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IISc Bengaluru Lakes 2018">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>75 Ramsar sites</strong> designated (up from 26 in 2019)‚Äîinternational recognition expanding <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-wetland-rules-review-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Wetland Rules 2023">[166]</a></li>
                            <li>Wetland Rules (2017) poorly enforced‚Äîstate authorities lack capacity to prosecute <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-wetland-rules-review-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC Wetland Rules 2023">[166]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Urban Green Cover Deficit</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Most cities have <strong>&lt;10% tree canopy</strong> cover‚ÄîWHO recommends 30% <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-urban-green-cover-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Urban Green Cover 2022">[168]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>5-10x disparity</strong> in tree cover between affluent vs informal settlements <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-urban-forest-equity-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Urban Forest Equity 2023">[169]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>80,000+ trees felled</strong> in Delhi (2016-2022) for metro, flyovers‚Äîmature trees lost <a href="resources.html#ref-delhi-tree-felling-data-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Delhi Tree Felling 2022">[170]</a></li>
                            <li>Urban tree census <strong>missing/outdated</strong> in most cities‚Äîno GIS mapping of species, age, canopy <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-tree-census-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Tree Census 2022">[171]</a></li>
                            <li>Municipal urban forestry capacity gaps‚Äîreliance on ornamental exotics, not native species <a href="resources.html#ref-iifm-urban-forestry-capacity-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIFM Urban Forestry 2021">[172]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Finance & Institutional Gaps</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>CAMPA: ‚Çπ66,000+ Cr accumulated</strong> but &lt;40% utilized; survival rate only 7.5% <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Conservation needs: ‚Çπ81,664 Cr/year</strong> (2025-30) vs ‚Çπ32,207 Cr total (2018-22) <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-biodiversity-finance-needs-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mongabay Biodiversity Finance 2024">[175]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Finance gap: ‚Çπ49,000+ Cr/year</strong>‚Äîbiodiversity credit market potential $2B by 2030 <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-biodiversity-finance-needs-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mongabay Biodiversity Finance 2024">[175]</a></li>
                            <li>Green bonds for biodiversity rare‚Äîcapital markets finance solar/wind, not ecosystem restoration <a href="resources.html#ref-cbi-green-bonds-india-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CBI Green Bonds 2023">[175]</a></li>
                            <li>PES mechanisms absent‚Äîcommunities protecting forests not compensated for services <a href="resources.html#ref-iifm-pes-india-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIFM PES 2022">[176]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Ecosystem Service Value</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>1/3 of India's GDP depends on nature</strong>‚Äîecosystem decline threatens economic growth <a href="resources.html#ref-wef-india-economy-nature-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WEF India Economy Nature 2024">[169]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Forest ecosystem services: $744B/year</strong> (habitat $303B, biodiversity $419B) <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-forest-ecosystem-services-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ScienceDirect Forest Services 2024">[170]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Pollination services: ‚Çπ1.12 lakh Cr/year</strong> ($22.5B)‚Äî8.72% of agricultural value <a href="resources.html#ref-icar-pollination-benefits-2017" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICAR Pollination 2017">[171]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ecosystem decline costs 5.7% GDP annually</strong>‚Äînot reflected in economic accounts <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-natural-capital-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Natural Capital 2024">[168]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Forest carbon stock: 7,204M tonnes</strong>‚Äîsink value ‚Çπ6 lakh Cr ($120B) at $5/tonne <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-forest-ecosystem-services-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ScienceDirect Forest Services 2024">[170]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. TARGETS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Targets: Year 3 Natural Capital Milestones</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Community Forest Rights Acceleration</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>25% CFR recognition</strong> (from 5% baseline)‚Äî5x increase in community-managed forests <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50,000 CFR titles granted</strong> (from ~6,300 baseline)‚Äîfast-track pending claims</li>
                            <li><strong>‚Çπ10,000 Cr CAMPA</strong> directed to CFR communities for restoration, monitoring, livelihoods <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>100 CFR peer learning networks</strong> established for sustainable NTFP harvesting, fire management</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wildlife Corridor Protection</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>50 critical corridors mapped</strong> with GIS‚Äîelephant, tiger, leopard movement paths <a href="resources.html#ref-wti-wildlife-corridors-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WTI Wildlife Corridors 2022">[159]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>20 corridors designated</strong> as eco-sensitive zones with legal protection</li>
                            <li><strong>10 infrastructure retrofits</strong>‚Äîunderpasses/overpasses on highways cutting corridors</li>
                            <li><strong>50% reduction in HWC deaths</strong> (from 500+/year baseline) via corridor connectivity <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-human-wildlife-conflict-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC HWC Report 2024">[167]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Urban Green Cover Equity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>20 cities with GIS tree census</strong>‚Äîspecies, age, canopy cover mapped by ward <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-tree-census-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Tree Census 2022">[171]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>15% canopy cover in underserved wards</strong> (from &lt;5% baseline)‚Äîequity-focused planting</li>
                            <li><strong>Native species nursery network:</strong> 100 nurseries stocking bioregion-specific palettes</li>
                            <li><strong>500 municipal urban foresters trained</strong> in ecological design, native species propagation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wetland Protection & Restoration</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>200 urban wetlands restored</strong>‚Äîsewage diversion, invasive removal, native vegetation <a href="resources.html#ref-wetlands-international-india-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Wetlands International 2022">[164]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>State wetland authorities activated</strong> in 15 states‚Äîenforcement capacity built</li>
                            <li><strong>100 Ramsar sites</strong> (from 75 baseline)‚Äîinternational recognition driving protection</li>
                            <li><strong>Zero tolerance for encroachment:</strong> 50 prosecutions completed with penalties enforced</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Natural Capital Accounting</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>5 states with NCA frameworks</strong>‚Äîecosystem service valuation in state GDP accounts <a href="resources.html#ref-orf-greening-gdp-natural-capital-2018" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ORF Greening GDP 2018">[176]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Ecosystem service valuation mandatory</strong> in EIAs for projects &gt;‚Çπ100 Cr <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-natural-capital-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Natural Capital 2024">[168]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Biodiversity offsets: 2x restoration</strong> required for forest clearing (monitored 20 years)</li>
                            <li><strong>500 planners/economists trained</strong> in natural capital accounting methods</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">CAMPA Fund Redesign</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>75% CAMPA utilization</strong> (from &lt;40% baseline)‚Äîsimplified disbursement <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>50% allocated to ANR</strong> (Assisted Natural Regeneration)‚Äîcheaper, more biodiverse than plantations</li>
                            <li><strong>30% to CFR communities</strong> and wetland restoration‚Äîempower local stewardship</li>
                            <li><strong>Public CAMPA dashboard:</strong> Every project mapped with satellite-verified survival rates</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. SANKEY DIAGRAM -->
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-transparent border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üå≥ Natural Capital Cascade: Ecosystems to Human Wellbeing</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Visualizing how forests, wetlands, and biodiversity generate ecosystem services that flow into economic value and human wellbeing‚Äîhighlighting where value is lost and can be restored</p>
                <div id="biodiversity-sankey" style="height: 500px; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Source: FSI 2023, World Bank Natural Capital 2024, ScienceDirect Forest Services 2024. Interactive diagram shows natural ecosystems ‚Üí ecosystem services ‚Üí economic value ‚Üí development decisions ‚Üí feedback loops.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. HIDDEN DYNAMICS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üîç Hidden Dynamics: The Systemic Barriers</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether biodiversity interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Ownership & Demands</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Commons as "unowned":</strong> Forests seen as available land for development, not community resource <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Forest land = "development opportunity":</strong> Political pressure to divert for industry, infrastructure, mining</li>
                            <li><strong>Indigenous rights denied:</strong> CFR claims systematically rejected‚Äîonly 6,300 titles vs 200,000+ claims <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wetlands claimed by developers:</strong> "Wasteland" to be "reclaimed" and made "productive"</li>
                            <li><strong>Wildlife corridors unrecognized:</strong> Not in land records‚Äîencroached without ecological assessment</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Culture & Narrative</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>"Development vs environment" binary:</strong> Conservation framed as anti-progress, obstacle to jobs and growth</li>
                            <li><strong>"Nature = outside cities":</strong> Biodiversity seen as forest/wildlife concern, not urban planning priority</li>
                            <li><strong>Wildlife = threat:</strong> Human-animal conflict covered as "attack" stories, not habitat fragmentation consequences <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-human-wildlife-conflict-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC HWC Report 2024">[167]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Tree planting as greenwashing:</strong> Numbers celebrated (X million planted!) without survival/ecological value tracking</li>
                            <li><strong>Indigenous knowledge dismissed:</strong> Community conservation models invisible in policy discourse</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Capacity & Skills</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ecological restoration expertise scarce:</strong> Forest departments lack ANR, soil bioengineering capacity</li>
                            <li><strong>Urban forestry gaps:</strong> Municipal planners untrained in native species, ecological design <a href="resources.html#ref-iifm-urban-forestry-capacity-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="IIFM Urban Forestry 2021">[172]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wetland management skills absent:</strong> City corporations don't know how to revive lakes, restore hydrology</li>
                            <li><strong>Wildlife corridor design limited:</strong> Planners can't map animal movement, design crossings <a href="resources.html#ref-wti-wildlife-corridors-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WTI Wildlife Corridors 2022">[159]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Natural capital accounting missing:</strong> Economists can't value biodiversity loss, integrate into cost-benefit <a href="resources.html#ref-orf-greening-gdp-natural-capital-2018" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ORF Greening GDP 2018">[176]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Data & Evidence</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Urban tree census missing:</strong> Most cities lack GIS inventory of species, age, canopy by neighborhood <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-tree-census-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Tree Census 2022">[171]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green cover equity unmapped:</strong> No data on tree cover disparity between rich/poor areas</li>
                            <li><strong>Biodiversity loss unquantified:</strong> Species extinction, population declines not systematically monitored</li>
                            <li><strong>Wildlife corridor fragmentation unmapped:</strong> No GIS analysis of where roads/railways cut movement paths</li>
                            <li><strong>CAMPA outcomes opaque:</strong> No public dashboard of projects, survival rates, ecological outcomes <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Policy & Regulation</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Forest clearance rubber-stamped:</strong> FAC meetings approve 90%+ projects with weak scrutiny <a href="resources.html#ref-elaw-forest-clearance-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ELAW Forest Clearance 2022">[179]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wetland protection unenforced:</strong> Rules exist but state committees inactive, prosecutions rare</li>
                            <li><strong>EIA diluted (2020):</strong> Post-facto clearances allowed, public hearing weakened, exemptions expanded <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-eia-notification-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC EIA 2020">[180]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wildlife corridors legally unprotected:</strong> No enforceable restrictions on linear infrastructure</li>
                            <li><strong>Biodiversity offsets absent:</strong> No requirement to restore 2x habitat when clearing forests</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Finance & Capital</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>CAMPA funds underutilized:</strong> ‚Çπ66,000+ Cr accumulated but &lt;40% spent due to rigid procedures <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Green bonds for biodiversity rare:</strong> Capital markets ignore forest restoration, wetland revival <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-biodiversity-finance-needs-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mongabay Biodiversity Finance 2024">[175]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>PES mechanisms absent:</strong> Communities protecting watersheds not compensated for services</li>
                            <li><strong>Urban forestry budgets minuscule:</strong> 1-2% of municipal budgets; no maintenance funding <a href="resources.html#ref-niua-urban-green-cover-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="NIUA Urban Green Cover 2022">[168]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Conservation ROI uncalculated:</strong> No business case showing water security, flood mitigation value</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Market & Procurement</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Native species nurseries limited:</strong> Most stock ornamental exotics; local ecotypes hard to procure at scale</li>
                            <li><strong>Ecological restoration supply chains thin:</strong> Few firms with ANR, wetland revival expertise</li>
                            <li><strong>Tender specs prioritize survival %:</strong> Contractors plant monocultures (eucalyptus, acacia) not biodiversity <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Community enterprises rare:</strong> CFR holders lack market linkages for NTFP, ecotourism, carbon credits</li>
                            <li><strong>Green infrastructure procurement absent:</strong> No mandates for bioswales, green roofs in public works</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. SHIFT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üåü Shift: The Transformation Vision</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-900 mb-4"><strong>Landscapes where forests regrow through community stewardship, urban green cover expands equitably, wetlands are protected not filled, wildlife corridors reconnect habitats, and natural capital is accounted in development decisions.</strong></p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What Changes</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>From plantation targets to biodiversity outcomes:</strong> CAMPA metrics shift from saplings planted to ecosystem health <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From state control to community stewardship:</strong> 25% forest land under CFR‚Äîcommunity management outperforms top-down <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From development vs nature to development with nature:</strong> Corridor assessments mandatory in all linear infrastructure EIAs</li>
                            <li><strong>From GDP to Green GDP:</strong> Natural capital depreciation visible in state accounts‚Äîecosystem loss costs 5.7% GDP <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-natural-capital-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Natural Capital 2024">[168]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>From ornamental to native:</strong> Municipal planting shifts to bioregion-specific species palettes</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Breakthrough Moments</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>CFR communities thrive:</strong> 50,000 titles granted‚Äîcommunity forests show higher biodiversity than state-managed <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wildlife corridors reconnect:</strong> First underpasses operational‚Äîelephant conflict deaths drop 50% <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-human-wildlife-conflict-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC HWC Report 2024">[167]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Urban green equity visible:</strong> Ward-level canopy maps show disparity‚Äîbudget allocation inverts to prioritize underserved</li>
                            <li><strong>Wetland encroachment prosecuted:</strong> 50 cases completed‚Äîdevelopers pay restoration costs, land reclaimed</li>
                            <li><strong>PES payments flow:</strong> Upstream communities receive payments from downstream cities for watershed protection</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. MARKERS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üìà Markers: Progress Indicators</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Quantitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>CFR titles granted:</strong> 50,000 target (from 6,300 baseline)‚Äîcommunity control of forests <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Dense forest cover trend:</strong> Halt decline in natural forest (24,651 sq km lost since 2003) <a href="resources.html#ref-fsi-forest-report-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="FSI Forest Report 2023">[162]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>CAMPA utilization rate:</strong> 75% target (from &lt;40% baseline) with satellite-verified survival <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>HWC deaths reduction:</strong> 50% reduction (from 500+/year baseline) via corridor connectivity <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-human-wildlife-conflict-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC HWC Report 2024">[167]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Urban canopy equity index:</strong> Disparity between affluent/underserved wards (10x ‚Üí 3x target) <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-urban-forest-equity-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Urban Forest Equity 2023">[169]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Wetland encroachment prosecutions:</strong> 50 cases completed with restoration orders enforced</li>
                            <li><strong>Corridor legal protection:</strong> 20 corridors with eco-sensitive zone designation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Qualitative Signals</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Media narrative shift:</strong> From "development blocked by forest rules" to "community forest success story"</li>
                            <li><strong>FAC scrutiny strengthens:</strong> Forest clearance rejection rate increases; cumulative impact assessments mandated</li>
                            <li><strong>State NCA adoption:</strong> 5 states integrate ecosystem valuation into planning commission decisions <a href="resources.html#ref-orf-greening-gdp-natural-capital-2018" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ORF Greening GDP 2018">[176]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Infrastructure agencies engage:</strong> Railways, NHAI proactively designing wildlife crossings pre-approval</li>
                            <li><strong>CFR peer networks active:</strong> 100 networks sharing NTFP harvesting, fire management, carbon credit models</li>
                            <li><strong>Native nursery market emerges:</strong> 100 nurseries supplying bioregion-specific species at scale</li>
                            <li><strong>Urban residents demand equity:</strong> Ward committees advocate for canopy increase in underserved areas</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7. STRATEGIES -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-teal-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è Strategies: Intervention Pathways</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Community Forest Rights Acceleration</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Only 5% eligible forest land under CFR despite 2006 Act <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Fast-track 50,000 pending CFR claims with time-bound approvals, legal aid for communities</li>
                            <li>Build 100 CFR holder peer networks for sustainable NTFP harvesting, fire management</li>
                            <li>Direct ‚Çπ10,000 Cr CAMPA to CFR communities for restoration, monitoring, value-addition</li>
                            <li>Create market linkages for community forest products (honey, bamboo, medicinal plants)</li>
                            <li>Establish PES schemes‚Äîcommunities paid for watershed protection, carbon sequestration</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Wildlife Corridor Protection & Retrofit</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 70%+ tiger reserves lack functional corridors; 2,727 HWC deaths <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-human-wildlife-conflict-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC HWC Report 2024">[167]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>GIS mapping of 50 critical elephant, tiger, leopard corridors using GPS collar, camera trap data</li>
                            <li>Designate 20 corridors as eco-sensitive zones with legal protection against development</li>
                            <li>Retrofit 10 existing highways/railways with underpasses/overpasses in key segments</li>
                            <li>Compensate farmers in corridors for crop/livestock damage‚Äîopportunity cost payments</li>
                            <li>Mandate corridor assessments in all linear infrastructure EIAs‚Äîmitigation before approval</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Urban Green Cover Equity Program</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 5-10x disparity in tree cover between affluent vs informal settlements <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-urban-forest-equity-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Urban Forest Equity 2023">[169]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>GIS-based urban tree census in 20 cities‚Äîmap species, age, canopy by ward</li>
                            <li>Invert budget allocation‚Äîmaximize investment in underserved areas based on equity gap</li>
                            <li>Mandate native species in public planting‚Äîdevelop bioregion-specific palettes</li>
                            <li>Require green infrastructure (green roofs, bioswales) in all new development codes</li>
                            <li>Train 500 municipal urban foresters in ecological design, long-term maintenance</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Wetland Protection & Restoration</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> 50%+ wetlands degraded; encroachment continues unpunished <a href="resources.html#ref-wetlands-international-india-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Wetlands International 2022">[164]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Activate state wetland authorities in 15 states‚Äîstaff, budget, enforcement powers</li>
                            <li>Launch urban lake restoration program in 200 lakes‚Äîsewage diversion, invasive removal</li>
                            <li>Prosecute 50 encroachment cases with heavy penalties‚Äîrestoration bonds from violators</li>
                            <li>Create public wetland parks with trails, education centers showing ecosystem services</li>
                            <li>Monitor quarterly via satellite‚Äîpollution levels, encroachment, biodiversity (bird counts)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Natural Capital Accounting Integration</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Ecosystem decline costs 5.7% GDP but invisible in accounts <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-natural-capital-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Natural Capital 2024">[168]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Develop India-specific NCA framework‚Äîadapt SEEA for local ecosystems, data availability <a href="resources.html#ref-orf-greening-gdp-natural-capital-2018" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ORF Greening GDP 2018">[176]</a></li>
                            <li>Mandate ecosystem service valuation in EIAs‚Äîquantify water, carbon, pollination impacts</li>
                            <li>Require biodiversity offsets‚Äî2x restoration for clearing, monitored 20 years</li>
                            <li>Integrate into state GDP accounts‚Äîtrack forest cover, wetland area as natural capital stocks</li>
                            <li>Train 500 economists/planners in NCA methods‚ÄîMoEFCC, state PCBs, planning commissions</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. CAMPA Fund Redesign</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> ‚Çπ66,000+ Cr accumulated but &lt;40% utilized; 7.5% survival <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Reframe metrics‚Äîsuccess = biodiversity increase, carbon sequestration, not saplings planted</li>
                            <li>Allocate 50% to Assisted Natural Regeneration (ANR)‚Äîcheaper, faster, more biodiverse</li>
                            <li>Direct 30% to CFR communities and wetland restoration‚Äîempower local stewardship</li>
                            <li>Create public dashboard‚Äîmap every project, track survival with satellite data, citizen reporting</li>
                            <li>Simplify disbursement‚Äî60-day approval cycles, multiyear grants, reduced bureaucratic hurdles</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Invasive Species Removal at Scale</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Lantana covers 40% of tiger reserves; outcompetes native species <a href="resources.html#ref-joshi-lantana-invasion-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Joshi Lantana Invasion 2020">[166]</a></p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Intervention:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Launch invasive removal program in 20 tiger reserves‚Äîprioritize prey habitat restoration</li>
                            <li>Create employment for local communities‚Äîremoval labor-intensive, sustainable livelihoods</li>
                            <li>Convert biomass to value products‚ÄîLantana furniture, biochar for soil amendment</li>
                            <li>Replant with native species after removal‚Äîrestore understory for prey species</li>
                            <li>Monitor regrowth quarterly‚Äîrapid response teams for reinfestation hotspots</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 8. ECONOMIC IMPACT -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üí∞ Economic Impact: Costs, Externalities, Opportunities</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Costs & Externalities</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Ecosystem decline costs 5.7% GDP annually</strong>‚Äînot reflected in economic accounts <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-natural-capital-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Natural Capital 2024">[168]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Human-wildlife conflict: $33,268 per incident</strong> total cost; 0.8-1M hectares crops damaged annually <a href="resources.html#ref-pnas-human-wildlife-conflict-cost-2021" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="PNAS HWC Cost 2021">[172]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>24,651 sq km dense forest lost</strong> (2003-2023)‚Äîreplaced by monocultures with zero biodiversity <a href="resources.html#ref-fsi-forest-report-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="FSI Forest Report 2023">[162]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>CAMPA survival rate only 7.5%</strong>‚Äî‚Çπ60,000+ Cr spent on plantations that fail <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>400M people depend on Western Ghats</strong> for water/food‚Äî30% of species in 5% of land at risk <a href="resources.html#ref-frontiers-western-ghats-valuation-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Frontiers Western Ghats 2023">[173]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Ecosystem Service Value</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Forest ecosystem services: $744B/year</strong> (habitat $303B, biodiversity $419B, supporting services) <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-forest-ecosystem-services-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ScienceDirect Forest Services 2024">[170]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Forest carbon sink: ‚Çπ6 lakh Cr ($120B)</strong> at $5/tonne; 7,204M tonnes stock <a href="resources.html#ref-sciencedirect-forest-ecosystem-services-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ScienceDirect Forest Services 2024">[170]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Pollination services: ‚Çπ1.12 lakh Cr/year</strong> ($22.5B)‚Äî8.72% of agricultural value <a href="resources.html#ref-icar-pollination-benefits-2017" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="ICAR Pollination 2017">[171]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Mangrove flood protection: Top 5 globally</strong>‚Äî15M more people would flood if lost <a href="resources.html#ref-nature-mangrove-flood-protection-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Nature Mangrove Protection 2024">[174]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>1/3 of India's GDP depends on nature</strong>‚Äîconservation = economic security <a href="resources.html#ref-wef-india-economy-nature-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="WEF India Economy Nature 2024">[169]</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Investment Opportunity</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Conservation needs: ‚Çπ81,664 Cr/year</strong> (2025-30); finance gap ‚Çπ49,000+ Cr/year <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-biodiversity-finance-needs-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mongabay Biodiversity Finance 2024">[175]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Biodiversity credit market: $2B by 2030</strong>‚Äîemerging global mechanism <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-biodiversity-finance-needs-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mongabay Biodiversity Finance 2024">[175]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>20x ROI on nature investment</strong>‚ÄîUNEP estimate on conservation returns <a href="resources.html#ref-mongabay-biodiversity-finance-needs-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Mongabay Biodiversity Finance 2024">[175]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>CAMPA funds: ‚Çπ66,000+ Cr available</strong>‚Äîunderutilized; redesign unlocks impact <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>PES revenue potential:</strong> Downstream cities pay upstream communities for watershed services</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 9. INVESTMENTS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-pink-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üíµ Investments: Capital Allocation</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Capex (Capital Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>CFR community infrastructure:</strong> ‚Çπ500 crore (50,000 communities @ ‚Çπ1 lakh each; restoration equipment, NTFP processing)</li>
                            <li><strong>Wildlife corridor infrastructure:</strong> ‚Çπ1,000 crore (10 underpasses/overpasses @ ‚Çπ100 crore each)</li>
                            <li><strong>Urban tree census & planting:</strong> ‚Çπ400 crore (20 cities @ ‚Çπ20 crore; GIS mapping, native nurseries, planting)</li>
                            <li><strong>Wetland restoration:</strong> ‚Çπ600 crore (200 wetlands @ ‚Çπ3 crore each; sewage diversion, invasive removal)</li>
                            <li><strong>Native species nursery network:</strong> ‚Çπ100 crore (100 nurseries @ ‚Çπ1 crore each; propagation facilities)</li>
                            <li><strong>NCA framework development:</strong> ‚Çπ50 crore (5 states; ecosystem mapping, valuation methodology, training)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Capex:</strong> ‚Çπ2,650 crore (~$320M) over 3 years</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Opex (Operational Expenditure)</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>CFR community support:</strong> ‚Çπ200 crore/year (peer networks, legal aid, market linkages, NTFP buyer aggregation)</li>
                            <li><strong>Corridor monitoring & HWC response:</strong> ‚Çπ100 crore/year (camera traps, GPS collars, rapid response teams)</li>
                            <li><strong>Urban forestry maintenance:</strong> ‚Çπ150 crore/year (20 cities; pruning, watering, pest management, monitoring)</li>
                            <li><strong>Wetland authority operations:</strong> ‚Çπ75 crore/year (15 states; staff, enforcement, quarterly monitoring)</li>
                            <li><strong>Invasive species removal:</strong> ‚Çπ150 crore/year (20 reserves; labor, native replanting, regrowth monitoring)</li>
                            <li><strong>NCA capacity building:</strong> ‚Çπ25 crore/year (500 economists/planners trained; state-level implementation support)</li>
                            <li><strong>Total Opex:</strong> ‚Çπ700 crore/year (~$85M/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">Note: Capex primarily from CAMPA fund reallocation (‚Çπ66,000+ Cr available). Opex offset by ecosystem service value (‚Çπ744B/year) and PES mechanisms. 20x ROI on nature investment (UNEP) justifies expenditure.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 10. FOCUS AREAS -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm mb-8 border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéØ Focus Areas: Urgency-Ranked Priorities</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-4">Partner-driven interventions addressing hidden dynamics, not adding protected area coverage. Ranked by leverage potential and systemic impact.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: Community Forest Rights Acceleration</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Fast-track 50,000 CFR claims; direct ‚Çπ10,000 Cr CAMPA to communities; build 100 peer networks. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Indigenous Rights Denial (5% CFR recognition)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> Community stewardship outperforms state management‚Äîlower costs, better biodiversity, reduced conflict. Pending claims risk rejection; political window may close. <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-fra-implementation-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CSE FRA Implementation 2022">[157]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">URGENT: CAMPA Fund Redesign</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Shift from plantations to ANR (50%); redirect to CFR communities (30%); public dashboard with satellite verification. <strong>Addresses:</strong> CAMPA Underutilization (‚Çπ66K Cr stuck; 7.5% survival)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why urgent:</strong> ‚Çπ66,000+ Cr sitting idle while forests degrade; ANR 3x cheaper and more biodiverse than plantations. Redesign creates 10x impact without new funds. <a href="resources.html#ref-cag-campa-audit-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="CAG CAMPA Audit 2023">[165]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Wildlife Corridor Protection</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Map 50 corridors; designate 20 as ESZs; retrofit 10 highways with underpasses. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Corridor Fragmentation (70%+ reserves lack connectivity; 2,727 HWC deaths)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Corridors being paved over every month‚Äîonce fragmented, reconnection 10x harder. 50% HWC reduction possible via connectivity. <a href="resources.html#ref-moefcc-human-wildlife-conflict-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="MoEFCC HWC Report 2024">[167]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü†</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">HIGH: Wetland Encroachment Enforcement</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Activate 15 state authorities; prosecute 50 cases; restore 200 urban wetlands. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Wetland Degradation (50%+ degraded; encroachment unpunished)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why high:</strong> Wetlands being filled for real estate daily‚Äîevery month of delay = permanent loss. Prosecution creates deterrent effect; restoration demonstrates reversibility. <a href="resources.html#ref-wetlands-international-india-2022" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Wetlands International 2022">[164]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Urban Green Cover Equity</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">GIS tree census in 20 cities; invert budget to underserved wards; native species mandate. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Urban Canopy Disparity (5-10x gap between affluent/poor areas)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Equity invisible until measured‚Äîcensus creates political pressure; heat deaths rising in underserved areas. Requires 2-3 year implementation but foundational. <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-urban-forest-equity-2023" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="TERI Urban Forest Equity 2023">[169]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü°</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">MEDIUM: Natural Capital Accounting Integration</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">NCA framework in 5 states; mandatory EIA valuation; train 500 planners. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Invisible Ecosystem Costs (5.7% GDP lost but not in accounts)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why medium:</strong> Changes decision-making framework permanently‚Äîonce biodiversity loss visible in GDP, political incentives shift. Requires 2-3 years for methodology but transformational. <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-natural-capital-india-2024" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="World Bank Natural Capital 2024">[168]</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                            <span class="text-2xl">üü¢</span>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">FOUNDATIONAL: Invasive Species Removal</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Launch removal program in 20 tiger reserves; community employment; biomass to products. <strong>Addresses:</strong> Invasive Dominance (Lantana covers 40% of tiger reserves)</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Why foundational:</strong> Slow spread‚Äîurgent but not emergency. Creates employment; builds local capacity for ongoing management. Requires 3-5 year commitment for ecosystem restoration. <a href="resources.html#ref-joshi-lantana-invasion-2020" class="text-xs text-primary hover:underline" title="Joshi Lantana Invasion 2020">[166]</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

